230 #define MI_PROBE_RAISE_SIZE 34
231 
232 ULONG MiProbeRaises[MI_PROBE_RAISE_SIZE];
233 
234 #define MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES(i) \
235  ASSERT (i < MI_PROBE_RAISE_SIZE); \
236  MiProbeRaises[i] += 1;
237 
238 //
239 // Note: this should be > 2041 to account for the cache manager's
240 // aggressive zeroing logic.
241 //
242 
243 ULONG MmReferenceCountCheck = MAXUSHORT / 2;
244 
245 ULONG MiMdlsAdjusted = FALSE;
246 
247 typedef enum _MI_LOCK_USED_FOR_PROBE {
248  LOCK_TYPE_NONE = 0,
249  LOCK_TYPE_AWE = 1, // This must come first (code depends on it).
250  LOCK_TYPE_WS = 2,
251  LOCK_TYPE_PFN = 3
252 } MI_LOCK_USED_FOR_PROBE, *PMI_LOCK_USED_FOR_PROBE;

254 
255 VOID
256 MmProbeAndLockPages (
257  __inout PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
258  __in KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
259  __in LOCK_OPERATION Operation
260  )
261 
262 /*++
263 
264 Routine Description:
265 
266  This routine probes the specified pages, makes the pages resident and
267  locks the physical pages mapped by the virtual pages in memory. The
268  Memory descriptor list is updated to describe the physical pages.
269 
270 Arguments:
271 
272  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List
273  (MDL). The supplied MDL must supply a virtual
274  address, byte offset and length field. The
275  physical page portion of the MDL is updated when
276  the pages are locked in memory.
277 
278  AccessMode - Supplies the access mode in which to probe the arguments.
279  One of KernelMode or UserMode.
280 
281  Operation - Supplies the operation type. One of IoReadAccess, IoWriteAccess
282  or IoModifyAccess.
283 
284 Return Value:
285 
286  None - exceptions are raised.
287 
288 Environment:
289 
290  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL and below for pageable addresses,
291  DISPATCH_LEVEL and below for non-pageable addresses.
292 
293 --*/
294 
295 {
296  ULONG Processor;
297  LOGICAL PfnHeldToo;
298  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
299  MMPTE PteContents;
300  PMMPTE LastPte;
301  PMMPTE PointerPte;
302  PMMPTE PointerPde;
303  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
304  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
305  PVOID Va;
306  PVOID EndVa;
307  PVOID AlignedVa;
308  PMMPFN Pfn1;
309  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
310  PFN_NUMBER LastPageFrameIndex;
311  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
312  KIRQL OldIrql;
313  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPagesToLock;
314  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPagesSpanned;
315  NTSTATUS status;
316  NTSTATUS ProbeStatus;
317  PETHREAD Thread;
318  ULONG SavedState;
319  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
320  PCHAR StartVa;
321  PVOID CallingAddress;
322  PVOID CallersCaller;
323  PAWEINFO AweInfo;
324  PEX_PUSH_LOCK PushLock;
325  TABLE_SEARCH_RESULT SearchResult;
326  LONG EntryCounter;
327  MI_LOCK_USED_FOR_PROBE LockType;
328 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
329  MMPTE BogusPte;
330 
331  BogusPte.u.Long = (ULONG64)-1;
332 #endif
333 
334 
335 Top:
336 
337  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
338  ASSERT (((ULONG)MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset & ~(PAGE_SIZE - 1)) == 0);
339 
340  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
341 
342  ASSERT (((ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa & (PAGE_SIZE - 1)) == 0);
343  AlignedVa = (PVOID)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa;
344 
345  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (
346  MDL_PAGES_LOCKED |
347  MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA |
348  MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL |
349  MDL_PARTIAL |
350  MDL_IO_SPACE)) == 0);
351 
352  Va = (PCHAR)AlignedVa + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset;
353  StartVa = Va;
354 
355  //
356  // Endva is one byte past the end of the buffer, if ACCESS_MODE is not
357  // kernel, make sure the EndVa is in user space AND the byte count
358  // does not cause it to wrap.
359  //
360 
361  EndVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Va + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
362 
363  if ((AccessMode != KernelMode) &&
364  ((EndVa > (PVOID)MM_USER_PROBE_ADDRESS) || (Va >= EndVa))) {
365 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
366  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
367  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (0);
368  ExRaiseStatus (STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION);
369  }
370 
371  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
372 
373  NumberOfPagesToLock = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (Va,
374  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
375 
376  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock != 0);
377 
378  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
379 
380  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (Thread);
381 
382  if (CurrentProcess->AweInfo != NULL) {
383 
384  AweInfo = CurrentProcess->AweInfo;
385 
386  //
387  // Block APCs to prevent recursive pushlock scenarios as
388  // this is not supported.
389  //
390 
391  KeEnterGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
392 
393  PushLock = ExAcquireCacheAwarePushLockShared (AweInfo->PushLock);
394 
395  //
396  // Provide a fast path for transfers that are within
397  // a single AWE region.
398  //
399 
400  Processor = KeGetCurrentProcessorNumber ();
401  PhysicalView = AweInfo->PhysicalViewHint[Processor];
402 
403  if ((PhysicalView != NULL) &&
404  ((PVOID)StartVa >= MI_VPN_TO_VA (PhysicalView->StartingVpn)) &&
405  ((PVOID)((PCHAR)EndVa - 1) <= MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (PhysicalView->EndingVpn))) {
406  NOTHING;
407  }
408  else {
409 
410  //
411  // Lookup the element and save the result.
412  //
413 
414  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (&AweInfo->AweVadRoot,
415  MI_VA_TO_VPN (StartVa),
416  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
417  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
418  ((PVOID)StartVa >= MI_VPN_TO_VA (PhysicalView->StartingVpn)) &&
419  ((PVOID)((PCHAR)EndVa - 1) <= MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (PhysicalView->EndingVpn))) {
420  AweInfo->PhysicalViewHint[Processor] = PhysicalView;
421  }
422  else {
423  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
424  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
425  goto DefaultProbeAndLock;
426  }
427  }
428 
429  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = CurrentProcess;
430 
431  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= (MDL_PAGES_LOCKED | MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE);
432 
433  if (PhysicalView->VadType == VadAwe) {
434 
435  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
436  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PCHAR)EndVa - 1);
437 
438  do {
439  PteContents = *PointerPte;
440 
441  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
442 
443  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
444  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
445 
446  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
447  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (9);
448  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
449  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
450  }
451 
452  //
453  // This is an AWE frame - it is either
454  // noaccess, readonly or readwrite.
455  //
456 
457  if ((PteContents.u.Hard.Owner == MI_PTE_OWNER_KERNEL) ||
458  ((Operation != IoReadAccess) && (PteContents.u.Hard.Write == 0))) {
459 
460  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
461  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
462 
463  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
464  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (9);
465  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
466  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
467  }
468 
469  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
470 
471  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
472 
473  if (Pfn1->AweReferenceCount >= (LONG)MmReferenceCountCheck) {
474 
475  ASSERT (FALSE);
476  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
477  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
478 
479  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
480  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (17);
481  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
482  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
483  }
484 
485  InterlockedIncrement (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
486 
487  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
488 
489  Page += 1;
490  PointerPte += 1;
491  } while (PointerPte <= LastPte);
492 
493 
494  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
495  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
496 
497  return;
498  }
499 
500  if (PhysicalView->VadType == VadLargePages) {
501 
502  //
503  // The PTE cannot be referenced (it doesn't exist), but it
504  // serves the useful purpose of identifying when we cross
505  // PDEs and therefore must recompute the base PFN.
506  //
507 
508  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
509  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (StartVa);
510  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
511 
512  do {
513 
514  if (Pfn1->AweReferenceCount >= (LONG)MmReferenceCountCheck) {
515  ASSERT (FALSE);
516  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
517  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
518 
519  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
520  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (18);
521  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
522  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
523  }
524 
525  InterlockedIncrement (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
526 
527  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
528  Page += 1;
529 
530  NumberOfPagesToLock -= 1;
531 
532  if (NumberOfPagesToLock == 0) {
533  break;
534  }
535 
536  PointerPte += 1;
537 
538  if (!MiIsPteOnPdeBoundary (PointerPte)) {
539  PageFrameIndex += 1;
540  Pfn1 += 1;
541  }
542  else {
543  StartVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
544  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (StartVa);
545  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
546  }
547 
548  } while (TRUE);
549 
550  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
551  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
552 
553  return;
554  }
555  }
556  }
557  else {
558  CurrentProcess = NULL;
559  }
560 
561 DefaultProbeAndLock:
562 
563  NumberOfPagesSpanned = NumberOfPagesToLock;
564 
565  if (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (Va)) {
566 
567  ProbeStatus = STATUS_SUCCESS;
568 
569  MmSavePageFaultReadAhead (Thread, &SavedState);
570  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, (ULONG)(NumberOfPagesToLock - 1));
571 
572  try {
573 
574  do {
575 
576  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
577 
578  //
579  // Make sure the page is resident.
580  //
581 
582  *(volatile CHAR *)Va;
583 
584  if ((Operation != IoReadAccess) &&
585  (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS)) {
586 
587  //
588  // Probe for write access as well.
589  //
590 
591  ProbeForWriteChar ((PCHAR)Va);
592  }
593 
594  NumberOfPagesToLock -= 1;
595 
596  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, (ULONG)(NumberOfPagesToLock - 1));
597  Va = (PVOID) (((ULONG_PTR)Va + PAGE_SIZE) & ~(PAGE_SIZE - 1));
598  Page += 1;
599  } while (Va < EndVa);
600 
601  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock == 0);
602  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
603 
604  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
605  ProbeStatus = GetExceptionCode();
606  }
607 
608  //
609  // We may still fault again below but it's generally rare.
610  // Restore this thread's normal fault behavior now.
611  //
612 
613  MmResetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, SavedState);
614 
615  if (ProbeStatus != STATUS_SUCCESS) {
616  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (1);
617  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = NULL;
618  ExRaiseStatus (ProbeStatus);
619  }
620 
621  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
622  }
623  else {
624 
625  //
626  // Set PointerPte to NULL to indicate this is a physical address range.
627  //
628 
629  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
630  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (StartVa);
631  }
632  else {
633  PointerPte = NULL;
634  }
635 
636  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
637  }
638 
639  PointerPxe = MiGetPxeAddress (StartVa);
640  PointerPpe = MiGetPpeAddress (StartVa);
641  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (StartVa);
642 
643  Va = AlignedVa;
644  ASSERT (Page == (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1));
645  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (EntryCounter = 0);
646 
647  //
648  // Indicate whether this is a read or write operation.
649  //
650 
651  if (Operation != IoReadAccess) {
652  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_WRITE_OPERATION;
653  }
654  else {
655  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~(MDL_WRITE_OPERATION);
656  }
657 
658  //
659  // Initialize MdlFlags (assume the probe will succeed).
660  //
661 
662  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
663 
664  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
665 
666  //
667  // These are user space addresses, check them carefully.
668  //
669 
670  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesSpanned != 0);
671 
672  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == PsGetCurrentProcess ());
673 
674  //
675  // Initialize the MDL process field (assume the probe will succeed).
676  //
677 
678  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = CurrentProcess;
679 
680  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PCHAR)EndVa - 1);
681 
682  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&CurrentProcess->NumberOfLockedPages,
683  NumberOfPagesSpanned);
684  OldIrql = MM_NOIRQL;
685  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_WS;
686  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
687  }
688  else {
689 
690  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == NULL);
691 
692  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = NULL;
693 
694  Va = (PCHAR)Va + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset;
695 
696  NumberOfPagesToLock = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (Va,
697  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
698 
699  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
700 
701  //
702  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
703  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
704  //
705 
706  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (Va);
707  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
708 
709  LastPageFrameIndex = PageFrameIndex + NumberOfPagesToLock;
710 
711  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0);
712 
713  //
714  // Acquire the PFN database lock.
715  //
716 
717  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
718 
719  do {
720 
721  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
722 
723  //
724  // Check to make sure each page is not locked down an
725  // unusually high number of times.
726  //
727 
728  ASSERT (PageFrameIndex <= MmHighestPhysicalPage);
729 
730  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= MmReferenceCountCheck) {
731  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
732  ASSERT (FALSE);
733  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (19);
734  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
735  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
736  }
737 
738  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
739  MI_SNAP_DIRTY (Pfn1, 1, 0x99);
740  }
741 
742  MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE (Pfn1);
743  }
744  else {
745  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_IO_SPACE;
746  }
747 
748  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
749 
750  Page += 1;
751  PageFrameIndex += 1;
752  Pfn1 += 1;
753 
754  } while (PageFrameIndex < LastPageFrameIndex);
755 
756  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
757 
758  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
759 
760  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesSpanned != 0);
761 
762  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
763 
764  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
765  CallingAddress,
766  CallersCaller,
767  NumberOfPagesSpanned,
768  1);
769  }
770 
771  return;
772  }
773 
774  //
775  // Since this operation is to a system address, no need to check for
776  // PTE write access below so mark the access as a read so only the
777  // operation type (and not where the Va is) needs to be checked in the
778  // subsequent loop.
779  //
780 
781  Operation = IoReadAccess;
782 
783  LastPte = MiGetPteAddress ((PCHAR)EndVa - 1);
784 
785  //
786  // A driver may build an MDL for a user address and then get
787  // a system VA for it. The driver may then call MmProbeAndLockPages
788  // again, this time with the system VA (instead of the original
789  // user VA) for the same range.
790  //
791  // Thus the PFNs will really point at PFNs which generally
792  // require the relevant process' working set pushlock, but in
793  // this instance we would only be holding the system working set
794  // pushlock. Therefore the user can change PFN sharecounts and
795  // active states at any time. The only thing we'd know for sure
796  // is that the refcount must be nonzero on entry and will stay
797  // that way because it would be illegal for the driver to
798  // have called MmUnlockPages prior to this probe call.
799  //
800  // However, this is not enough state to ensure we charge locking
801  // properly (without leaking) so the code that used to acquire the
802  // system working set mutex here has been changed to instead always
803  // use the PFN lock to synchronize system space VA arguments.
804  //
805 
806  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_PFN;
807  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
808  }
809 
810  do {
811 
812  //
813  // Set the current MDL entry to empty so all error paths can
814  // call MmUnlockPages.
815  //
816 
817  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
818 
819  while (
820 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
821  (PointerPxe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
822 #endif
823 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
824  (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
825 #endif
826  ((PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
827  (((MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde)) == 0) &&
828  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0)))) {
829 
830  //
831  // The VA is not resident, release the PFN lock and access the page
832  // to make it appear.
833  //
834 
835  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
836  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
837  }
838  else {
839  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
840  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
841  }
842 
843  MmSavePageFaultReadAhead (Thread, &SavedState);
844  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, 0);
845 
846  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
847 
848  status = MmAccessFault (FALSE, Va, KernelMode, NULL);
849 
850  MmResetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, SavedState);
851 
852  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
853  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (20);
854  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
855  }
856 
857  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
858  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
859  }
860  else {
861  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
862  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
863  }
864  }
865 
866  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde)) {
867 
868  if ((Operation != IoReadAccess) &&
869  (PointerPde->u.Hard.Write == 0)) {
870 
871  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
872  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
873  }
874  else {
875  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
876  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
877  }
878 
879  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (4);
880  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
881  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
882  }
883 
884  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
885 
886  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde) + MiGetPteOffset (Va);
887  }
888  else {
889 
890 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
891 
892  //
893  // Pick up the PTE as an interlocked operation to prevent AWE
894  // updates from tearing our read on these platforms.
895  //
896 
897  PteContents.u.Long = InterlockedCompareExchangePte (PointerPte,
898  BogusPte.u.Long,
899  BogusPte.u.Long);
900  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Long != BogusPte.u.Long);
901 
902 #else
903  PteContents = *PointerPte;
904 #endif
905 
906  //
907  // There is a subtle race here where the PTE contents can get zeroed
908  // by a thread running on another processor. This can only happen
909  // for an AWE address space because these ranges (deliberately for
910  // performance reasons) do not acquire the PFN lock during remap
911  // operations. In this case, one of 2 scenarios is possible -
912  // either the old PTE is read or the new. The new may be a zero
913  // PTE if the map request was to invalidate *or* non-zero (and
914  // valid) if the map request was inserting a new entry. For the
915  // latter, we don't care if we lock the old or new frame here as
916  // it's an application bug to provoke this behavior - and
917  // regardless of which is used, no corruption can occur because
918  // the PFN lock is acquired during an NtFreeUserPhysicalPages.
919  // But the former must be checked for explicitly here. As a
920  // separate note, the PXE/PPE/PDE accesses above are always safe
921  // even for the AWE deletion race because these tables
922  // are never lazy-allocated for AWE ranges.
923  //
924 
925  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
926  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Long == 0);
927  ASSERT (PsGetCurrentProcess ()->AweInfo != NULL);
928 
929  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (5);
930  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
931  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
932  }
933 
934  if (Operation != IoReadAccess) {
935 
936  if ((PteContents.u.Long & MM_PTE_WRITE_MASK) == 0) {
937 
938  if (PteContents.u.Long & MM_PTE_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) {
939 
940  //
941  // The protection has changed from writable to copy on
942  // write. This can happen if a fork is in progress for
943  // example. Restart the operation at the top.
944  //
945 
946  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
947 
948  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
949 
950  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
951  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
952  }
953  else {
954  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
955  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
956  }
957 
958  MmSavePageFaultReadAhead (Thread, &SavedState);
959  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, 0);
960 
961  status = MmAccessFault (TRUE, Va, KernelMode, NULL);
962 
963  MmResetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, SavedState);
964 
965  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
966  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (23);
967  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
968  }
969 
970  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
971  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
972  }
973  else {
974  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
975  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
976  }
977 
978  continue;
979  }
980  }
981 
982  //
983  // The caller has made the page protection more
984  // restrictive, this should never be done once the
985  // request has been issued ! Rather than wading
986  // through the PFN database entry to see if it
987  // could possibly work out, give the caller an
988  // access violation.
989  //
990 
991 #if DBG
992  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
993  "MmProbeAndLockPages: PTE %p %p changed\n",
994  PointerPte,
995  PteContents.u.Long);
996 
997  if (MmStopOnBadProbe) {
998  DbgBreakPoint ();
999  }
1000 #endif
1001 
1002  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (16);
1003  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
1004  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1005  }
1006  }
1007 
1008  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
1009  }
1010 
1011  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
1012 
1013  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
1014 
1015  ASSERT ((CurrentProcess == NULL) || (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS));
1016 
1017  PfnHeldToo = FALSE;
1018 
1019  if ((CurrentProcess != NULL) && (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL)) {
1020 
1021  //
1022  // This process has a \Device\PhysicalMemory VAD so it must be
1023  // checked to see if the current address resides in it.
1024  //
1025 
1026  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot,
1027  MI_VA_TO_VPN (Va),
1028  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
1029  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
1030  (PhysicalView->VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory)) {
1031 
1032  ASSERT ((ULONG)PhysicalView->Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == (ULONG)PhysicalView->VadType);
1033 
1034  //
1035  // The VA lies within a device physical memory VAD.
1036  //
1037  // The PTE was already checked for read/write permissions
1038  // above, but the PFN must still be checked for ownership
1039  // and this must be done with the PFN lock since this
1040  // process is not necessarily the correct owner.
1041  //
1042 
1043  PfnHeldToo = TRUE;
1044 
1045  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1046 
1047  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation != ActiveAndValid) {
1048  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1049  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (32);
1050  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
1051  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1052  }
1053 
1054  //
1055  // Continue to hold the PFN lock until the reference count
1056  // on the desired PFN is incremented.
1057  //
1058  }
1059  }
1060 
1061  if (MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_FOR_PROBE (Pfn1, FALSE, PointerPte) == FALSE) {
1062 
1063  if (PfnHeldToo == TRUE) {
1064  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1065  }
1066 
1067  //
1068  // If this page is for privileged code/data,
1069  // then force it in regardless.
1070  //
1071 
1072  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
1073 
1074  if ((Va < MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) ||
1075  (MI_IS_SYSTEM_CACHE_ADDRESS(Va)) ||
1076  ((Va >= MmPagedPoolStart) && (Va <= MmPagedPoolEnd))) {
1077 
1078  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (10);
1079  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
1080  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1081  }
1082 
1083  if (MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_FOR_PROBE (Pfn1, TRUE, PointerPte) == FALSE) {
1084 
1085  //
1086  // The only reason we don't force for privileged code/data
1087  // is if it would have caused a reference count wrap.
1088  // Typically this indicates a driver is forgetting to call
1089  // MmUnlockPages as the page is locked down an unusually
1090  // high number of times.
1091  //
1092 
1093  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (3);
1094  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
1095  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1096  }
1097  }
1098  else if (PfnHeldToo == TRUE) {
1099  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
1100  }
1101 
1102 
1103  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
1104  MI_SNAP_DIRTY (Pfn1, 1, 0x98);
1105  }
1106  }
1107  else {
1108 
1109  //
1110  // This is an I/O space address - there is no PFN database entry
1111  // for it, so no reference counts may be modified for these pages.
1112  //
1113  // Don't charge page locking for this page, just add it to the MDL.
1114  //
1115 
1116  if (CurrentProcess != NULL) {
1117 
1118  //
1119  // The VA better be within a \Device\PhysicalMemory VAD.
1120  //
1121 
1122  if (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) {
1123  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (2);
1124  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
1125  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1126  }
1127 
1128  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
1129 
1130  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot,
1131  MI_VA_TO_VPN (Va),
1132  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
1133  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
1134  ((PhysicalView->VadType == VadRotatePhysical) ||
1135  (PhysicalView->VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory))) {
1136 
1137  ASSERT ((ULONG)PhysicalView->Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == (ULONG)PhysicalView->VadType);
1138 
1139  //
1140  // The range lies within a rotate physical VAD or a
1141  // device physical memory VAD.
1142  //
1143  // We already know the access is ok because the PTE was
1144  // already checked for read/write permissions above.
1145  //
1146 
1147  NOTHING;
1148  }
1149  else {
1150  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (11);
1151  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
1152  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
1153  }
1154  }
1155 
1156  if (((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0) &&
1157  (CurrentProcess != NULL)) {
1158 
1159  EntryCounter = *(volatile PLONG) &MiActiveIoCounter;
1160  }
1161 
1162  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_IO_SPACE;
1163  }
1164 
1165  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
1166 
1167  Page += 1;
1168 
1169  PointerPte += 1;
1170 
1171  if (MiIsPteOnPdeBoundary (PointerPte)) {
1172 
1173  PointerPde += 1;
1174 
1175  if (MiIsPteOnPpeBoundary (PointerPte)) {
1176  PointerPpe += 1;
1177  if (MiIsPteOnPxeBoundary (PointerPte)) {
1178  PointerPxe += 1;
1179  }
1180  }
1181  }
1182 
1183  } while (PointerPte <= LastPte);
1184 
1185  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
1186  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
1187  }
1188  else {
1189  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
1190  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
1191  }
1192 
1193  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) == 0);
1194 
1195  if (AlignedVa <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
1196 
1197  //
1198  // User space buffers that reside in I/O space need to be reference
1199  // counted because SANs will want to reuse the physical space but cannot
1200  // do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
1201  // going from/to it.
1202  //
1203 
1204  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) {
1205 
1206  if (MiReferenceIoSpace (MemoryDescriptorList, Page) == FALSE) {
1207  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
1208  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (24);
1209  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
1210  }
1211 
1212  if (EntryCounter != *(volatile PLONG) &MiActiveIoCounter) {
1213 
1214  //
1215  // The counter has changed since we captured the first PTE.
1216  // Just repeat everything.
1217  //
1218 
1219  MiDereferenceIoSpace (MemoryDescriptorList);
1220 
1221  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
1222 
1223  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesSpanned != 0);
1224 
1225  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
1226 
1227  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
1228  CallingAddress,
1229  CallersCaller,
1230  NumberOfPagesSpanned,
1231  2);
1232  }
1233 
1234  MmUnlockPages (MemoryDescriptorList);
1235  goto Top;
1236  }
1237  }
1238  }
1239 
1240  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
1241 
1242  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesSpanned != 0);
1243 
1244  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
1245 
1246  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
1247  CallingAddress,
1248  CallersCaller,
1249  NumberOfPagesSpanned,
1250  3);
1251  }
1252 
1253  return;
1254 
1255 FailureReleaseLocks:
1256 
1257  //
1258  // A violation was detected. Release the synchronization primitive
1259  // we used and unlock any pages locked so far.
1260  //
1261 
1262  ASSERT (!NT_SUCCESS (status));
1263 
1264  ASSERT (LockType > LOCK_TYPE_AWE);
1265 
1266  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN) {
1267  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
1268  }
1269  else {
1270  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS);
1271  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
1272  }
1273 
1274 FailureUnlockAnyPages:
1275 
1276  //
1277  // An exception occurred, unlock any pages locked so far. Note that
1278  // a tracker entry must be inserted for MmUnlockPages to find.
1279  //
1280 
1281  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED);
1282 
1283  if ((MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) &&
1284  ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) == 0)) {
1285 
1286  //
1287  // Compute NumberOfPagesToLock as MmUnlockPages will also when
1288  // freeing the MDL tracker.
1289  //
1290 
1291  NumberOfPagesToLock = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartVa,
1292  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
1293 
1294  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
1295 
1296  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
1297  CallingAddress,
1298  CallersCaller,
1299  NumberOfPagesToLock,
1300  5);
1301  }
1302 
1303  MmUnlockPages (MemoryDescriptorList);
1304 
1305  //
1306  // Raise an exception of access violation to the caller.
1307  //
1308 
1309  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (13);
1310  ExRaiseStatus (status);
1311 }
1312 
1313 NTKERNELAPI
1314 VOID
1315 MmProbeAndLockProcessPages (
1316  __inout PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1317  __in PEPROCESS Process,
1318  __in KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
1319  __in LOCK_OPERATION Operation
1320  )
1321 
1322 /*++
1323 
1324 Routine Description:
1325 
1326  This routine probes and locks the address range specified by
1327  the MemoryDescriptorList in the specified Process for the AccessMode
1328  and Operation.
1329 
1330 Arguments:
1331 
1332  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pre-initialized MDL that describes the
1333  address range to be probed and locked.
1334 
1335  Process - Specifies the address of the process whose address range is
1336  to be locked.
1337 
1338  AccessMode - The mode for which the probe should check access to the range.
1339 
1340  Operation - Supplies the type of access which for which to check the range.
1341 
1342 Return Value:
1343 
1344  None.
1345 
1346 --*/
1347 
1348 {
1349  KAPC_STATE ApcState;
1350  LOGICAL Attached;
1351  NTSTATUS Status;
1352 
1353  Attached = FALSE;
1354  Status = STATUS_SUCCESS;
1355 
1356  if (Process != PsGetCurrentProcess ()) {
1357  KeStackAttachProcess (&Process->Pcb, &ApcState);
1358  Attached = TRUE;
1359  }
1360 
1361  try {
1362 
1363  MmProbeAndLockPages (MemoryDescriptorList,
1364  AccessMode,
1365  Operation);
1366 
1367  } except (EXCEPTION_EXECUTE_HANDLER) {
1368  Status = GetExceptionCode();
1369  }
1370 
1371  if (Attached) {
1372  KeUnstackDetachProcess (&ApcState);
1373  }
1374 
1375  if (Status != STATUS_SUCCESS) {
1376 
1377  ExRaiseStatus (Status);
1378  }
1379  return;
1380 }
1381 
1382 VOID
1383 MiAddMdlTracker (
1384  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1385  IN PVOID CallingAddress,
1386  IN PVOID CallersCaller,
1387  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPagesToLock,
1388  IN ULONG Who
1389  )
1390 
1391 /*++
1392 
1393 Routine Description:
1394 
1395  This routine adds an MDL to the specified process' chain.
1396 
1397 Arguments:
1398 
1399  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List
1400  (MDL). The MDL must supply the length. The
1401  physical page portion of the MDL is updated when
1402  the pages are locked in memory.
1403 
1404  CallingAddress - Supplies the address of the caller of our caller.
1405 
1406  CallersCaller - Supplies the address of the caller of CallingAddress.
1407 
1408  NumberOfPagesToLock - Specifies the number of pages to lock.
1409 
1410  Who - Specifies which routine is adding the entry.
1411 
1412 Return Value:
1413 
1414  None - exceptions are raised.
1415 
1416 Environment:
1417 
1418  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL and below.
1419 
1420 --*/
1421 
1422 {
1423  PEPROCESS Process;
1424  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
1425  PLOCK_TRACKER Tracker;
1426  PLOCK_TRACKER P;
1427  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
1428  KLOCK_QUEUE_HANDLE LockHandle;
1429 
1430  ASSERT (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE);
1431 
1432  Process = MemoryDescriptorList->Process;
1433 
1434  if (Process == NULL) {
1435  Process = PsInitialSystemProcess;
1436  }
1437 
1438  LockedPagesHeader = Process->LockedPagesList;
1439 
1440  if (LockedPagesHeader == NULL) {
1441  return;
1442  }
1443 
1444  //
1445  // It's ok to check unsynchronized for aborted tracking as the worst case
1446  // is just that one more entry gets added which will be freed later anyway.
1447  // The main purpose behind aborted tracking is that frees and exits don't
1448  // mistakenly bugcheck when an entry cannot be found.
1449  //
1450 
1451  if (LockedPagesHeader->Valid == FALSE) {
1452  return;
1453  }
1454 
1455  Tracker = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1456  sizeof (LOCK_TRACKER),
1457  'kLmM');
1458 
1459  if (Tracker == NULL) {
1460 
1461  //
1462  // It's ok to set this without synchronization as the worst case
1463  // is just that a few more entries gets added which will be freed
1464  // later anyway. The main purpose behind aborted tracking is that
1465  // frees and exits don't mistakenly bugcheck when an entry cannot
1466  // be found.
1467  //
1468 
1469  LockedPagesHeader->Valid = FALSE;
1470 
1471  return;
1472  }
1473 
1474  Tracker->Mdl = MemoryDescriptorList;
1475  Tracker->Count = NumberOfPagesToLock;
1476  Tracker->StartVa = MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa;
1477  Tracker->Offset = MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset;
1478  Tracker->Length = MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount;
1479  Tracker->Page = *(PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
1480 
1481  Tracker->CallingAddress = CallingAddress;
1482  Tracker->CallersCaller = CallersCaller;
1483 
1484  Tracker->Who = Who;
1485  Tracker->Process = Process;
1486 
1487  //
1488  // Update the list for this process. First make sure it's not already
1489  // inserted.
1490  //
1491 
1492  KeAcquireInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock, &LockHandle);
1493 
1494  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Flink;
1495 
1496  while (NextEntry != &LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) {
1497 
1498  P = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
1499  LOCK_TRACKER,
1500  ListEntry);
1501 
1502  if (P->Mdl == MemoryDescriptorList) {
1503  KeBugCheckEx (LOCKED_PAGES_TRACKER_CORRUPTION,
1504  0x1,
1505  (ULONG_PTR) P,
1506  (ULONG_PTR) MemoryDescriptorList,
1507  (ULONG_PTR) LockedPagesHeader->Count);
1508  }
1509  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
1510  }
1511 
1512  InsertTailList (&LockedPagesHeader->ListHead, &Tracker->ListEntry);
1513 
1514  LockedPagesHeader->Count += NumberOfPagesToLock;
1515 
1516  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1517 }
1518 
1519 LOGICAL
1520 MiFreeMdlTracker (
1521  IN OUT PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1522  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages
1523  )
1524 
1525 /*++
1526 
1527 Routine Description:
1528 
1529  This deletes an MDL from the specified process' chain. Used specifically
1530  by MmProbeAndLockSelectedPages () because it builds an MDL in its local
1531  stack and then copies the requested pages into the real MDL. This lets
1532  us track these pages.
1533 
1534 Arguments:
1535 
1536  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List
1537  (MDL). The MDL must supply the length.
1538 
1539  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to be freed.
1540 
1541 Return Value:
1542 
1543  TRUE.
1544 
1545 Environment:
1546 
1547  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL and below.
1548 
1549 --*/
1550 {
1551  KLOCK_QUEUE_HANDLE LockHandle;
1552  PLOCK_TRACKER Tracker;
1553  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
1554  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
1555  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
1556  PVOID PoolToFree;
1557  PEPROCESS Process;
1558 
1559  Process = MemoryDescriptorList->Process;
1560 
1561  if (Process == NULL) {
1562  Process = PsInitialSystemProcess;
1563  }
1564 
1565  LockedPagesHeader = (PLOCK_HEADER) Process->LockedPagesList;
1566 
1567  if (LockedPagesHeader == NULL) {
1568  return TRUE;
1569  }
1570 
1571  PoolToFree = NULL;
1572 
1573  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER) (MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
1574 
1575  KeAcquireInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock, &LockHandle);
1576 
1577  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Flink;
1578  while (NextEntry != &LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) {
1579 
1580  Tracker = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
1581  LOCK_TRACKER,
1582  ListEntry);
1583 
1584  if (MemoryDescriptorList == Tracker->Mdl) {
1585 
1586  if (PoolToFree != NULL) {
1587  KeBugCheckEx (LOCKED_PAGES_TRACKER_CORRUPTION,
1588  0x3,
1589  (ULONG_PTR) PoolToFree,
1590  (ULONG_PTR) Tracker,
1591  (ULONG_PTR) MemoryDescriptorList);
1592  }
1593 
1594  ASSERT (Tracker->Page == *Page);
1595  ASSERT (Tracker->Count == NumberOfPages);
1596 
1597  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
1598  LockedPagesHeader->Count -= NumberOfPages;
1599 
1600  PoolToFree = (PVOID) Tracker;
1601  }
1602  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Flink;
1603  }
1604 
1605  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1606 
1607  if (PoolToFree == NULL) {
1608 
1609  //
1610  // A driver is trying to unlock pages that aren't locked.
1611  //
1612 
1613  if (LockedPagesHeader->Valid == FALSE) {
1614  return TRUE;
1615  }
1616 
1617  KeBugCheckEx (PROCESS_HAS_LOCKED_PAGES,
1618  1,
1619  (ULONG_PTR) MemoryDescriptorList,
1620  Process->NumberOfLockedPages,
1621  (ULONG_PTR) Process->LockedPagesList);
1622  }
1623 
1624  ExFreePool (PoolToFree);
1625 
1626  return TRUE;
1627 }
1628 
1629 
1630 LOGICAL
1631 MmUpdateMdlTracker (
1632  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1633  IN PVOID CallingAddress,
1634  IN PVOID CallersCaller
1635  )
1636 
1637 /*++
1638 
1639 Routine Description:
1640 
1641  This updates an MDL in the specified process' chain. Used by the I/O
1642  system so that proper driver identification can be done even when I/O
1643  is actually locking the pages on their behalf.
1644 
1645 Arguments:
1646 
1647  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List.
1648 
1649  CallingAddress - Supplies the address of the caller of our caller.
1650 
1651  CallersCaller - Supplies the address of the caller of CallingAddress.
1652 
1653 Return Value:
1654 
1655  TRUE if the MDL was found, FALSE if not.
1656 
1657 Environment:
1658 
1659  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL and below.
1660 
1661 --*/
1662 {
1663  KLOCK_QUEUE_HANDLE LockHandle;
1664  PLOCK_TRACKER Tracker;
1665  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
1666  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
1667  PEPROCESS Process;
1668 
1669  ASSERT (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE);
1670 
1671  Process = MemoryDescriptorList->Process;
1672 
1673  if (Process == NULL) {
1674  Process = PsInitialSystemProcess;
1675  }
1676 
1677  LockedPagesHeader = (PLOCK_HEADER) Process->LockedPagesList;
1678 
1679  if (LockedPagesHeader == NULL) {
1680  return FALSE;
1681  }
1682 
1683  KeAcquireInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock, &LockHandle);
1684 
1685  //
1686  // Walk the list backwards as it's likely the MDL was
1687  // just recently inserted.
1688  //
1689 
1690  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Blink;
1691  while (NextEntry != &LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) {
1692 
1693  Tracker = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
1694  LOCK_TRACKER,
1695  ListEntry);
1696 
1697  if (MemoryDescriptorList == Tracker->Mdl) {
1698  ASSERT (Tracker->Page == *(PPFN_NUMBER) (MemoryDescriptorList + 1));
1699  Tracker->CallingAddress = CallingAddress;
1700  Tracker->CallersCaller = CallersCaller;
1701  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1702  return TRUE;
1703  }
1704  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Blink;
1705  }
1706 
1707  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1708 
1709  //
1710  // The caller is trying to update an MDL that is no longer locked.
1711  //
1712 
1713  return FALSE;
1714 }
1715 
1716 
1717 LOGICAL
1718 MiUpdateMdlTracker (
1719  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1720  IN ULONG AdvancePages
1721  )
1722 
1723 /*++
1724 
1725 Routine Description:
1726 
1727  This updates an MDL in the specified process' chain.
1728 
1729 Arguments:
1730 
1731  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List.
1732 
1733  AdvancePages - Supplies the number of pages being advanced.
1734 
1735 Return Value:
1736 
1737  TRUE if the MDL was found, FALSE if not.
1738 
1739 Environment:
1740 
1741  Kernel mode. DISPATCH_LEVEL and below.
1742 
1743 --*/
1744 {
1745  KLOCK_QUEUE_HANDLE LockHandle;
1746  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
1747  PLOCK_TRACKER Tracker;
1748  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
1749  PLOCK_HEADER LockedPagesHeader;
1750  PEPROCESS Process;
1751 
1752  ASSERT (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE);
1753 
1754  Process = MemoryDescriptorList->Process;
1755 
1756  if (Process == NULL) {
1757  Process = PsInitialSystemProcess;
1758  }
1759 
1760  LockedPagesHeader = (PLOCK_HEADER) Process->LockedPagesList;
1761 
1762  if (LockedPagesHeader == NULL) {
1763  return FALSE;
1764  }
1765 
1766  KeAcquireInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockedPagesHeader->Lock, &LockHandle);
1767 
1768  //
1769  // Walk the list backwards as it's likely the MDL was
1770  // just recently inserted.
1771  //
1772 
1773  NextEntry = LockedPagesHeader->ListHead.Blink;
1774  while (NextEntry != &LockedPagesHeader->ListHead) {
1775 
1776  Tracker = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
1777  LOCK_TRACKER,
1778  ListEntry);
1779 
1780  if (MemoryDescriptorList == Tracker->Mdl) {
1781 
1782  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER) (MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
1783 
1784  ASSERT (Tracker->Page == *Page);
1785  ASSERT (Tracker->Count > AdvancePages);
1786 
1787  Tracker->Page = *(Page + AdvancePages);
1788  Tracker->Count -= AdvancePages;
1789 
1790  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1791  return TRUE;
1792  }
1793  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Blink;
1794  }
1795 
1796  KeReleaseInStackQueuedSpinLock (&LockHandle);
1797 
1798  //
1799  // The caller is trying to update an MDL that is no longer locked.
1800  //
1801 
1802  return FALSE;
1803 }
1804 
1805 
1806 #if defined(_AMD64_)
1807 #define COPY_STACK_SIZE 350 // so chkstk doesn't complain
1808 #else
1809 #define COPY_STACK_SIZE 512
1810 #endif
1811 
1812 
1813 NTKERNELAPI
1814 VOID
1815 MmProbeAndLockSelectedPages (
1816  __inout PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
1817  __in PFILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT PagedSegmentArray,
1818  __in KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode,
1819  __in LOCK_OPERATION Operation
1820  )
1821 
1822 /*++
1823 
1824 Routine Description:
1825 
1826  This routine probes the specified pages, makes the pages resident and
1827  locks the physical pages mapped by the virtual pages in memory. The
1828  Memory descriptor list is updated to describe the physical pages.
1829 
1830 Arguments:
1831 
1832  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List
1833  (MDL). The MDL must supply the length. The
1834  physical page portion of the MDL is updated when
1835  the pages are locked in memory.
1836 
1837  PagedSegmentArray - Supplies a pointer to a list of buffer segments to be
1838  probed and locked. Note that this array is in kernel
1839  space and contains a list of user mode addresses.
1840 
1841  AccessMode - Supplies the access mode in which to probe the arguments.
1842  One of KernelMode or UserMode.
1843 
1844  Operation - Supplies the operation type. One of IoReadAccess, IoWriteAccess
1845  or IoModifyAccess.
1846 
1847 Return Value:
1848 
1849  None - exceptions are raised.
1850 
1851 Environment:
1852 
1853  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL and below.
1854 
1855 --*/
1856 
1857 {
1858  LOGICAL AweOk;
1859  LOGICAL LockedPagesCharged;
1860  LOGICAL PfnHeldToo;
1861  ULONG Processor;
1862  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
1863  MMPTE PteContents;
1864  PMMPTE PointerPte;
1865  PMMPTE PointerPde;
1866  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
1867  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
1868  PVOID Va;
1869  PMMPFN Pfn1;
1870  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
1871  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
1872  KIRQL OldIrql;
1873  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPagesToLock;
1874  NTSTATUS status;
1875  PETHREAD Thread;
1876  ULONG SavedState;
1877  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
1878  PVOID CallingAddress;
1879  PVOID CallersCaller;
1880  PAWEINFO AweInfo;
1881  PEX_PUSH_LOCK PushLock;
1882  TABLE_SEARCH_RESULT SearchResult;
1883  LONG EntryCounter;
1884  MI_LOCK_USED_FOR_PROBE LockType;
1885  PFILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT SegmentArray;
1886  PFILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT EntrySegment;
1887  PFILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT LastSegment;
1888  FILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT StackArray[COPY_STACK_SIZE];
1889 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
1890  MMPTE BogusPte;
1891 
1892  BogusPte.u.Long = (ULONG64)-1;
1893 #endif
1894 
1895 
1896  PAGED_CODE ();
1897 
1898  AweOk = TRUE;
1899  LockedPagesCharged = FALSE;
1900  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
1901 
1902  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (OldIrql = MM_NOIRQL);
1903  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (EntryCounter = 0);
1904  SATISFY_OVERZEALOUS_COMPILER (PushLock = NULL);
1905 
1906  //
1907  // Calculate the end of the segment list.
1908  //
1909 
1910  NumberOfPagesToLock = BYTES_TO_PAGES (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
1911 
1912  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock != 0);
1913  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock <= (MAXULONG_PTR / sizeof (FILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT)));
1914 
1915  EntrySegment = (PVOID)&StackArray[0];
1916 
1917  if (NumberOfPagesToLock > COPY_STACK_SIZE) {
1918 
1919  EntrySegment = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
1920  NumberOfPagesToLock * sizeof (FILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT),
1921  'rPmM');
1922 
1923  if (EntrySegment == NULL) {
1924  ExRaiseStatus (STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES);
1925  }
1926  }
1927 
1928  SegmentArray = EntrySegment;
1929 
1930  LastSegment = SegmentArray + NumberOfPagesToLock;
1931 
1932  ASSERT (SegmentArray < LastSegment);
1933 
1934  //
1935  // Capture the specified segment elements so we can safely access them
1936  // while locks are held below. This is because the caller's segment
1937  // array can be in paged pool.
1938  //
1939 
1940  RtlCopyMemory (SegmentArray,
1941  PagedSegmentArray,
1942  NumberOfPagesToLock * sizeof (FILE_SEGMENT_ELEMENT));
1943 
1944  //
1945  // Indicate whether this is a read or write operation.
1946  //
1947 
1948  if (Operation != IoReadAccess) {
1949  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_WRITE_OPERATION;
1950  }
1951  else {
1952  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~(MDL_WRITE_OPERATION);
1953  }
1954 
1955  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = NULL;
1956 
1957  Va = (PVOID) Ptr64ToPtr (SegmentArray->Buffer);
1958 
1959  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
1960  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (Thread);
1961  }
1962  else {
1963  CurrentProcess = NULL;
1964  }
1965 
1966 Top:
1967 
1968  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
1969  ASSERT (((ULONG)MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset & ~(PAGE_SIZE - 1)) == 0);
1970  ASSERT (((ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa & (PAGE_SIZE - 1)) == 0);
1971 
1972  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
1973  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
1974 
1975  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (
1976  MDL_PAGES_LOCKED |
1977  MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA |
1978  MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL |
1979  MDL_PARTIAL |
1980  MDL_IO_SPACE)) == 0);
1981 
1982  //
1983  // Initialize MdlFlags (assume the probe will succeed).
1984  //
1985 
1986  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
1987 
1988  for (SegmentArray = EntrySegment; SegmentArray < LastSegment; SegmentArray += 1) {
1989 
1990  //
1991  // Even systems without 64 bit pointers are required to zero the
1992  // upper 32 bits of the segment address so use alignment rather
1993  // than the buffer pointer.
1994  //
1995 
1996  Va = Ptr64ToPtr (SegmentArray->Buffer);
1997 
1998 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
1999  *Page = MM_EMPTY_LIST;
2000 
2001  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
2002 
2003  ASSERT (LockType != LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2004  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == PsGetCurrentProcess ());
2005 
2006  if ((AweOk == TRUE) && (CurrentProcess->AweInfo != NULL)) {
2007 
2008  AweInfo = CurrentProcess->AweInfo;
2009 
2010  //
2011  // Block APCs to prevent recursive pushlock scenarios as
2012  // this is not supported.
2013  //
2014 
2015  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_NONE) {
2016  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_AWE;
2017  KeEnterGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2018 
2019  PushLock = ExAcquireCacheAwarePushLockShared (AweInfo->PushLock);
2020  }
2021 
2022  //
2023  // Provide a fast path for transfers that are within
2024  // a single AWE region.
2025  //
2026 
2027  Processor = KeGetCurrentProcessorNumber ();
2028  PhysicalView = AweInfo->PhysicalViewHint[Processor];
2029 
2030  if ((PhysicalView != NULL) &&
2031  ((PVOID)Va >= MI_VPN_TO_VA (PhysicalView->StartingVpn)) &&
2032  ((PVOID)Va <= MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (PhysicalView->EndingVpn))) {
2033  NOTHING;
2034  }
2035  else {
2036 
2037  //
2038  // Lookup the element and save the result.
2039  //
2040 
2041  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (&AweInfo->AweVadRoot,
2042  MI_VA_TO_VPN (Va),
2043  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
2044  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
2045  ((PVOID)Va >= MI_VPN_TO_VA (PhysicalView->StartingVpn)) &&
2046  ((PVOID)Va <= MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (PhysicalView->EndingVpn))) {
2047  AweInfo->PhysicalViewHint[Processor] = PhysicalView;
2048  }
2049  else {
2050  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2051  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2052  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
2053 
2054  AweOk = FALSE;
2055 
2056  if (Page == (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1)) {
2057 
2058  //
2059  // This is the first page of the transfer. This
2060  // process has AWE mappings, but this range is
2061  // not in it. That's ok, just use the working
2062  // set pushlock to process it normally.
2063  //
2064 
2065  goto DefaultProbeAndLock;
2066  }
2067 
2068  //
2069  // Release the existing MDL's pages as they will have
2070  // to be relocked without using the AWE mechanism.
2071  //
2072 
2073  MmUnlockPages (MemoryDescriptorList);
2074 
2075  goto Top;
2076  }
2077  }
2078 
2079  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = CurrentProcess;
2080 
2081  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= (MDL_PAGES_LOCKED | MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE);
2082 
2083  if (PhysicalView->VadType == VadAwe) {
2084 
2085  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (Va);
2086 
2087  PteContents = *PointerPte;
2088 
2089  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
2090 
2091  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2092  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2093  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
2094 
2095  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (17);
2096  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2097  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2098  }
2099 
2100  //
2101  // This is an AWE frame - it is either
2102  // noaccess, readonly or readwrite.
2103  //
2104 
2105  if ((PteContents.u.Hard.Owner == MI_PTE_OWNER_KERNEL) ||
2106  ((Operation != IoReadAccess) && (PteContents.u.Hard.Write == 0))) {
2107 
2108  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2109  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2110  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
2111 
2112  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (18);
2113  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2114  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2115  }
2116 
2117  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
2118 
2119  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2120 
2121  if (Pfn1->AweReferenceCount >= (LONG)MmReferenceCountCheck) {
2122 
2123  ASSERT (FALSE);
2124  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2125  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2126  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
2127 
2128  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (19);
2129  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
2130  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2131  }
2132 
2133  InterlockedIncrement (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
2134 
2135  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
2136  Page += 1;
2137 
2138  //
2139  // Captured this page, march on to the next one.
2140  //
2141 
2142  continue;
2143  }
2144 
2145  if (PhysicalView->VadType == VadLargePages) {
2146 
2147  //
2148  // The PTE cannot be referenced (it doesn't exist), but it
2149  // serves the useful purpose of identifying when we cross
2150  // PDEs and therefore must recompute the base PFN.
2151  //
2152 
2153  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (Va);
2154  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (Va);
2155  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2156 
2157  if (Pfn1->AweReferenceCount >= (LONG)MmReferenceCountCheck) {
2158  ASSERT (FALSE);
2159  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2160  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2161  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_NONE;
2162 
2163  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (20);
2164  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
2165  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2166  }
2167 
2168  InterlockedIncrement (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
2169 
2170  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
2171  Page += 1;
2172 
2173  //
2174  // Captured this page, march on to the next one.
2175  //
2176 
2177  continue;
2178  }
2179  }
2180 
2181  AweOk = FALSE;
2182  }
2183  else {
2184 
2185  //
2186  // The access mode must be kernel to reference kernel addresses.
2187  //
2188 
2189  if (AccessMode != KernelMode) {
2190 
2191  //
2192  // Order the checks from hot to cool (lockwise).
2193  //
2194 
2195  ASSERT (LockType != LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2196 
2197  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2198  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2199  }
2200  else if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_AWE) {
2201  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2202  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2203  }
2204 
2205  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (21);
2206  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2207  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2208  }
2209 
2210  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == NULL);
2211  }
2212 
2213 DefaultProbeAndLock:
2214 
2215  if (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (Va)) {
2216  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (Va);
2217  }
2218  else {
2219 
2220  //
2221  // Set PointerPte to NULL to indicate this is a
2222  // physical address range.
2223  //
2224 
2225  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
2226  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (Va);
2227  }
2228  else {
2229  PointerPte = NULL;
2230  }
2231  }
2232 
2233  PointerPxe = MiGetPxeAddress (Va);
2234  PointerPpe = MiGetPpeAddress (Va);
2235  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (Va);
2236 
2237  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
2238 
2239  //
2240  // These are user space addresses, check them carefully.
2241  //
2242 
2243  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock != 0);
2244 
2245  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == PsGetCurrentProcess ());
2246 
2247  //
2248  // Initialize the MDL process field (assume the probe will succeed).
2249  //
2250 
2251  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = CurrentProcess;
2252 
2253  if (LockedPagesCharged == FALSE) {
2254  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&CurrentProcess->NumberOfLockedPages,
2255  NumberOfPagesToLock);
2256  LockedPagesCharged = TRUE;
2257  }
2258 
2259  if (LockType != LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2260  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_NONE);
2261  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_WS;
2262  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2263  }
2264  }
2265  else {
2266 
2267  ASSERT (CurrentProcess == NULL);
2268 
2269  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = NULL;
2270 
2271  Va = (PCHAR)Va + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset;
2272 
2273  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
2274 
2275  //
2276  // On certain architectures, virtual addresses
2277  // may be physical and hence have no corresponding PTE.
2278  //
2279 
2280  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (Va);
2281  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2282 
2283  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0);
2284 
2285  //
2286  // Acquire the PFN database lock.
2287  //
2288 
2289  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_NONE) {
2290  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_PFN;
2291  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2292  }
2293  else {
2294  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2295  }
2296 
2297  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
2298 
2299  //
2300  // Check to make sure each page is not locked down an
2301  // unusually high number of times.
2302  //
2303 
2304  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= MmReferenceCountCheck) {
2305  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2306  ASSERT (FALSE);
2307  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
2308  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (22);
2309  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2310  }
2311 
2312  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
2313  MI_SNAP_DIRTY (Pfn1, 1, 0x99);
2314  }
2315 
2316  MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE (Pfn1);
2317  }
2318  else {
2319  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_IO_SPACE;
2320  }
2321 
2322  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
2323  Page += 1;
2324 
2325  //
2326  // Captured this page, march on to the next one.
2327  //
2328 
2329  continue;
2330  }
2331 
2332  //
2333  // Since this operation is to a system address, no need to check for
2334  // PTE write access below so mark the access as a read so only the
2335  // operation type (and not where the Va is) needs to be checked in
2336  // the subsequent loop.
2337  //
2338 
2339  Operation = IoReadAccess;
2340 
2341  //
2342  // A driver may build an MDL for a user address and then get
2343  // a system VA for it. The driver may then call MmProbeAndLockPages
2344  // again, this time with the system VA (instead of the original
2345  // user VA) for the same range.
2346  //
2347  // Thus the PFNs will really point at PFNs which generally
2348  // require the relevant process' working set pushlock, but in
2349  // this instance we would only be holding the system working set
2350  // pushlock. Therefore the user can change PFN sharecounts and
2351  // active states at any time. The only thing we'd know for sure
2352  // is that the refcount must be nonzero on entry and will stay
2353  // that way because it would be illegal for the driver to
2354  // have called MmUnlockPages prior to this probe call.
2355  //
2356  // However, this is not enough state to ensure we charge locking
2357  // properly (without leaking) so the code that used to acquire the
2358  // system working set mutex here has been changed to instead always
2359  // use the PFN lock to synchronize system space VA arguments.
2360  //
2361 
2362  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_NONE) {
2363  LockType = LOCK_TYPE_PFN;
2364  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2365  }
2366  else {
2367  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2368  }
2369  }
2370 
2371  while (
2372 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
2373  (PointerPxe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2374 #endif
2375 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
2376  (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2377 #endif
2378  ((PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) ||
2379  (((MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde)) == 0) &&
2380  (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0)))) {
2381 
2382  //
2383  // The VA is not resident, release the PFN lock and access the page
2384  // to make it appear.
2385  //
2386 
2387  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2388  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2389  }
2390  else {
2391  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2392  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2393  }
2394 
2395  MmSavePageFaultReadAhead (Thread, &SavedState);
2396  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, 0);
2397 
2398  status = MmAccessFault (FALSE, Va, KernelMode, NULL);
2399 
2400  MmResetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, SavedState);
2401 
2402  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
2403  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (23);
2404  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2405  }
2406 
2407  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2408  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2409  }
2410  else {
2411  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2412  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2413  }
2414  }
2415 
2416  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde)) {
2417 
2418  if ((Operation != IoReadAccess) &&
2419  (PointerPde->u.Hard.Write == 0)) {
2420 
2421  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (24);
2422  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2423  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2424  }
2425 
2426  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde) + MiGetPteOffset (Va);
2427  }
2428  else {
2429 
2430 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
2431 
2432  //
2433  // Pick up the PTE as an interlocked operation to prevent AWE
2434  // updates from tearing our read on these platforms.
2435  //
2436 
2437  PteContents.u.Long = InterlockedCompareExchangePte (PointerPte,
2438  BogusPte.u.Long,
2439  BogusPte.u.Long);
2440  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Long != BogusPte.u.Long);
2441 
2442 #else
2443  PteContents = *PointerPte;
2444 #endif
2445 
2446  //
2447  // There is a subtle race here where the PTE contents can get zeroed
2448  // by a thread running on another processor. This can only happen
2449  // for an AWE address space because these ranges (deliberately for
2450  // performance reasons) do not acquire the PFN lock during remap
2451  // operations. In this case, one of 2 scenarios is possible -
2452  // either the old PTE is read or the new. The new may be a zero
2453  // PTE if the map request was to invalidate *or* non-zero (and
2454  // valid) if the map request was inserting a new entry. For the
2455  // latter, we don't care if we lock the old or new frame here as
2456  // it's an application bug to provoke this behavior - and
2457  // regardless of which is used, no corruption can occur because
2458  // the PFN lock is acquired during an NtFreeUserPhysicalPages.
2459  // But the former must be checked for explicitly here. As a
2460  // separate note, the PXE/PPE/PDE accesses above are always safe
2461  // even for the AWE deletion race because these tables
2462  // are never lazy-allocated for AWE ranges.
2463  //
2464 
2465  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
2466  ASSERT (PteContents.u.Long == 0);
2467  ASSERT (PsGetCurrentProcess ()->AweInfo != NULL);
2468 
2469  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (25);
2470  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2471  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2472  }
2473 
2474  if (Operation != IoReadAccess) {
2475 
2476  if ((PteContents.u.Long & MM_PTE_WRITE_MASK) == 0) {
2477 
2478  if (PteContents.u.Long & MM_PTE_COPY_ON_WRITE_MASK) {
2479 
2480  //
2481  // The protection has changed from writable to copy on
2482  // write. This can happen if a fork is in progress for
2483  // example. Restart the operation at the top.
2484  //
2485 
2486  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
2487 
2488  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2489  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2490  }
2491  else {
2492  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2493  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2494  }
2495 
2496  MmSavePageFaultReadAhead (Thread, &SavedState);
2497  MmSetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, 0);
2498 
2499  status = MmAccessFault (TRUE, Va, KernelMode, NULL);
2500 
2501  MmResetPageFaultReadAhead (Thread, SavedState);
2502 
2503  if (!NT_SUCCESS(status)) {
2504  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (19);
2505  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2506  }
2507 
2508  //
2509  // Retry this VA again.
2510  //
2511 
2512  SegmentArray -= 1;
2513 
2514  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2515  LOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2516  }
2517  else {
2518  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN);
2519  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2520  }
2521 
2522  continue;
2523  }
2524  }
2525 
2526  //
2527  // The caller has made the page protection more
2528  // restrictive, this should never be done once the
2529  // request has been issued ! Rather than wading
2530  // through the PFN database entry to see if it
2531  // could possibly work out, give the caller an
2532  // access violation.
2533  //
2534 
2535 #if DBG
2536  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_WARNING_LEVEL,
2537  "MmProbeAndLockPages: PTE %p %p changed\n",
2538  PointerPte,
2539  PteContents.u.Long);
2540 
2541  if (MmStopOnBadProbe) {
2542  DbgBreakPoint ();
2543  }
2544 #endif
2545 
2546  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (26);
2547  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2548  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2549  }
2550  }
2551 
2552  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
2553  }
2554 
2555  //
2556  // We have a PFN that is mapped by the caller. If this is a user
2557  // space mapping, check to ensure the frame is owned by the caller.
2558  // The only way this isn't TRUE is if the caller has a
2559  // \Device\PhysicalMemory mapping for frames he doesn't own.
2560  //
2561 
2562  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
2563 
2564  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
2565 
2566  ASSERT ((CurrentProcess == NULL) || (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS));
2567 
2568  PfnHeldToo = FALSE;
2569 
2570  if ((CurrentProcess != NULL) && (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL)) {
2571 
2572  //
2573  // This process has a \Device\PhysicalMemory VAD so it must be
2574  // checked to see if the current address resides in it.
2575  //
2576 
2577  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot,
2578  MI_VA_TO_VPN (Va),
2579  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
2580  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
2581  (PhysicalView->VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory)) {
2582 
2583  ASSERT ((ULONG)PhysicalView->Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == (ULONG)PhysicalView->VadType);
2584 
2585  //
2586  // The VA lies within a device physical memory VAD.
2587  //
2588  // The PTE was already checked for read/write permissions
2589  // above, but the PFN must still be checked for ownership
2590  // and this must be done with the PFN lock since this
2591  // process is not necessarily the correct owner.
2592  //
2593 
2594  PfnHeldToo = TRUE;
2595 
2596  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2597 
2598  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation != ActiveAndValid) {
2599  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2600  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (33);
2601  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2602  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2603  }
2604 
2605  //
2606  // Continue to hold the PFN lock until the reference count
2607  // on the desired PFN is incremented.
2608  //
2609  }
2610  }
2611 
2612  if (MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_FOR_PROBE (Pfn1, FALSE, PointerPte) == FALSE) {
2613  if (PfnHeldToo == TRUE) {
2614  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2615  }
2616 
2617  //
2618  // If this page is for privileged code/data,
2619  // then force it in regardless.
2620  //
2621 
2622  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2623 
2624  if ((Va < MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) ||
2625  (MI_IS_SYSTEM_CACHE_ADDRESS(Va)) ||
2626  ((Va >= MmPagedPoolStart) && (Va <= MmPagedPoolEnd))) {
2627 
2628  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (27);
2629  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
2630  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2631  }
2632 
2633  if (MI_ADD_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_FOR_PROBE (Pfn1, TRUE, PointerPte) == FALSE) {
2634 
2635  //
2636  // The only reason we don't force for privileged code/data
2637  // is if it would have caused a reference count wrap.
2638  // Typically this indicates a driver is forgetting to call
2639  // MmUnlockPages as the page is locked down an unusually
2640  // high number of times.
2641  //
2642 
2643  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (28);
2644  status = STATUS_WORKING_SET_QUOTA;
2645  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2646  }
2647  }
2648  else if (PfnHeldToo == TRUE) {
2649  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
2650  }
2651 
2652  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
2653  MI_SNAP_DIRTY (Pfn1, 1, 0x98);
2654  }
2655  }
2656  else {
2657 
2658  //
2659  // This is an I/O space address - there is no PFN database entry
2660  // for it, so no reference counts may be modified for these pages.
2661  //
2662  // Don't charge page locking for this page, just add it to the MDL.
2663  //
2664 
2665  if (CurrentProcess != NULL) {
2666 
2667  //
2668  // The VA better be within a \Device\PhysicalMemory VAD.
2669  //
2670 
2671  if (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) {
2672  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (29);
2673  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2674  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2675  }
2676 
2677  Va = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
2678 
2679  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (CurrentProcess->PhysicalVadRoot,
2680  MI_VA_TO_VPN (Va),
2681  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
2682  if ((SearchResult == TableFoundNode) &&
2683  ((PhysicalView->VadType == VadRotatePhysical) ||
2684  (PhysicalView->VadType == VadDevicePhysicalMemory))) {
2685 
2686  ASSERT ((ULONG)PhysicalView->Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == (ULONG)PhysicalView->VadType);
2687 
2688  //
2689  // The range lies within a rotate physical VAD or a
2690  // device physical memory VAD.
2691  //
2692  // We already know the access is ok because the PTE was
2693  // already checked for read/write permissions above.
2694  //
2695 
2696  NOTHING;
2697  }
2698  else {
2699  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (30);
2700  status = STATUS_ACCESS_VIOLATION;
2701  goto FailureReleaseLocks;
2702  }
2703  }
2704 
2705  if (((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0) &&
2706  (CurrentProcess != NULL)) {
2707 
2708  EntryCounter = *(volatile PLONG) &MiActiveIoCounter;
2709  }
2710 
2711  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_IO_SPACE;
2712  }
2713 
2714  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
2715  Page += 1;
2716  }
2717 
2718  //
2719  // Order the checks from hot to cool (lockwise).
2720  //
2721 
2722  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN) {
2723  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2724  }
2725  else if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS) {
2726  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2727  }
2728  else if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_AWE) {
2729  ExReleaseCacheAwarePushLockShared (PushLock);
2730  KeLeaveGuardedRegionThread (&Thread->Tcb);
2731  }
2732 
2733  if (Va <= MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS) {
2734 
2735  //
2736  // User space buffers that reside in I/O space need to be reference
2737  // counted because SANs will want to reuse the physical space but cannot
2738  // do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
2739  // going from/to it.
2740  //
2741 
2742  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) {
2743 
2744  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) == 0);
2745 
2746  if (MiReferenceIoSpace (MemoryDescriptorList, Page) == FALSE) {
2747  MI_INSTRUMENT_PROBE_RAISES (31);
2748  status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
2749  goto FailureUnlockAnyPages;
2750  }
2751 
2752  if (EntryCounter != *(volatile PLONG) &MiActiveIoCounter) {
2753 
2754  //
2755  // The counter has changed since we captured the first PTE.
2756  // Just repeat everything.
2757  //
2758 
2759  ASSERT (LockedPagesCharged == TRUE);
2760  MiDereferenceIoSpace (MemoryDescriptorList);
2761 
2762  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
2763 
2764  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
2765 
2766  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
2767  CallingAddress,
2768  CallersCaller,
2769  NumberOfPagesToLock,
2770  6);
2771  }
2772 
2773  MmUnlockPages (MemoryDescriptorList);
2774  LockedPagesCharged = FALSE;
2775  goto Top;
2776  }
2777  }
2778  }
2779 
2780  if (EntrySegment != (PVOID)&StackArray[0]) {
2781  ExFreePool (EntrySegment);
2782  }
2783 
2784  if ((MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) &&
2785  ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) == 0)) {
2786 
2787  ASSERT (NumberOfPagesToLock != 0);
2788 
2789  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
2790 
2791  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
2792  CallingAddress,
2793  CallersCaller,
2794  NumberOfPagesToLock,
2795  7);
2796  }
2797 
2798  return;
2799 
2800 FailureReleaseLocks:
2801 
2802  //
2803  // A violation was detected. Release the synchronization primitive
2804  // we used and unlock any pages locked so far.
2805  //
2806 
2807  ASSERT (!NT_SUCCESS (status));
2808 
2809  ASSERT (LockType > LOCK_TYPE_AWE);
2810 
2811  if (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_PFN) {
2812  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2813  }
2814  else {
2815  ASSERT (LockType == LOCK_TYPE_WS);
2816  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (Thread, CurrentProcess);
2817  }
2818 
2819 FailureUnlockAnyPages:
2820 
2821  //
2822  // An exception occurred, unlock any pages locked so far. Note that
2823  // a tracker entry must be inserted for MmUnlockPages to find.
2824  //
2825 
2826  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED);
2827 
2828  if ((MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) &&
2829  ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) == 0)) {
2830 
2831  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
2832 
2833  MiAddMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
2834  CallingAddress,
2835  CallersCaller,
2836  NumberOfPagesToLock,
2837  8);
2838  }
2839 
2840  MmUnlockPages (MemoryDescriptorList);
2841 
2842  if (EntrySegment != (PVOID)&StackArray[0]) {
2843  ExFreePool (EntrySegment);
2844  }
2845 
2846  //
2847  // Raise an exception of access violation to the caller.
2848  //
2849 
2850  ExRaiseStatus (status);
2851 }
2852 
2853 VOID
2854 MiDecrementReferenceCountForAwePage (
2855  IN PMMPFN Pfn1,
2856  IN LOGICAL PfnHeld
2857  )
2858 
2859 /*++
2860 
2861 Routine Description:
2862 
2863  This routine decrements the reference count for an AWE-allocated page.
2864  Descriptor List. If this decrements the count to zero, the page is
2865  put on the freelist and various resident available and commitment
2866  counters are updated.
2867 
2868 Arguments:
2869 
2870  Pfn - Supplies a pointer to the PFN database element for the physical
2871  page to decrement the reference count for.
2872 
2873  PfnHeld - Supplies TRUE if the caller holds the PFN lock.
2874 
2875 Return Value:
2876 
2877  None.
2878 
2879 Environment:
2880 
2881  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
2882 
2883 --*/
2884 
2885 {
2886  KIRQL OldIrql;
2887 
2888  if (PfnHeld == FALSE) {
2889  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2890  }
2891  else {
2892  OldIrql = PASSIVE_LEVEL;
2893  }
2894 
2895  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
2896  ASSERT (Pfn1->AweReferenceCount == 0);
2897  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.AweAllocation == 1);
2898 
2899  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= 2) {
2900  InterlockedDecrement16 ((PSHORT)&Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount);
2901  if (PfnHeld == FALSE) {
2902  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2903  }
2904  }
2905  else {
2906 
2907  //
2908  // This is the final dereference - the page was sitting in
2909  // limbo (not on any list) waiting for this last I/O to complete.
2910  //
2911 
2912  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation != ActiveAndValid);
2913  ASSERT (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount == 0);
2914  MiDecrementReferenceCount (Pfn1, MI_PFN_ELEMENT_TO_INDEX (Pfn1));
2915 
2916  if (PfnHeld == FALSE) {
2917  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
2918  }
2919  }
2920 
2921  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (1, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_AWE);
2922 
2923  MiReturnCommitment (1);
2924  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_RETURN_MDL_PAGES, 1);
2925 
2926  InterlockedDecrementSizeT (&MmMdlPagesAllocated);
2927 
2928  return;
2929 }
2930 
2931 SINGLE_LIST_ENTRY MmLockedIoPagesHead;
2932 
2933 LOGICAL
2934 MiReferenceIoSpace (
2935  IN OUT PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
2936  IN PPFN_NUMBER Page
2937  )
2938 
2939 /*++
2940 
2941 Routine Description:
2942 
2943  This routine reference counts physical pages which reside in I/O space
2944  when they are probed on behalf of a user-initiated transfer. These counts
2945  cannot be kept inside PFN database entries because there are no PFN entries
2946  for I/O space.
2947 
2948  These counts are kept because SANs will want to reuse the physical space
2949  but cannot do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
2950  going from/to it. If the process has not exited, but the SAN driver has
2951  unmapped the views to its I/O space, it still needs this as a way to know
2952  that the application does not have a transfer in progress to the previously
2953  mapped space.
2954 
2955 Arguments:
2956 
2957  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to the memory descriptor list.
2958 
2959  Page - Supplies a pointer to the PFN just after the end of the MDL.
2960 
2961 Return Value:
2962 
2963  TRUE if the reference counts were updated, FALSE if not.
2964 
2965 Environment:
2966 
2967  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
2968 
2969 --*/
2970 
2971 {
2972  PMDL Tracker;
2973  KIRQL OldIrql;
2974  SIZE_T MdlSize;
2975 
2976  MdlSize = (PCHAR)Page - (PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList;
2977 
2978  Tracker = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool, MdlSize, 'tImM');
2979 
2980  if (Tracker == NULL) {
2981  return FALSE;
2982  }
2983 
2984  RtlCopyMemory ((PVOID) Tracker,
2985  (PVOID) MemoryDescriptorList,
2986  MdlSize);
2987 
2988  Tracker->MappedSystemVa = (PVOID) MemoryDescriptorList;
2989 
2990  //
2991  // Add this transfer to the list.
2992  //
2993 
2994  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, &OldIrql);
2995 
2996  PushEntryList (&MmLockedIoPagesHead, (PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY) Tracker);
2997 
2998  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
2999 
3000  return TRUE;
3001 }
3002 
3003 NTKERNELAPI
3004 LOGICAL
3005 MiDereferenceIoSpace (
3006  IN OUT PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
3007  )
3008 
3009 /*++
3010 
3011 Routine Description:
3012 
3013  This routine decrements the reference counts on physical pages which
3014  reside in I/O space that were previously probed on behalf of a
3015  user-initiated transfer. These counts cannot be kept inside PFN
3016  database entries because there are no PFN entries for I/O space.
3017 
3018  These counts are kept because SANs will want to reuse the physical space
3019  but cannot do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
3020  going from/to it. If the process has not exited, but the SAN driver has
3021  unmapped the views to its I/O space, it still needs this as a way to know
3022  that the application does not have a transfer in progress to the previously
3023  mapped space.
3024 
3025 Arguments:
3026 
3027  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to the memory descriptor list.
3028 
3029 Return Value:
3030 
3031  TRUE if the reference counts were updated, FALSE if not.
3032 
3033 Environment:
3034 
3035  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
3036 
3037 --*/
3038 
3039 {
3040  KIRQL OldIrql;
3041  PMDL PrevEntry;
3042  PMDL NextEntry;
3043 
3044  PrevEntry = NULL;
3045 
3046  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, &OldIrql);
3047 
3048  NextEntry = (PMDL) MmLockedIoPagesHead.Next;
3049 
3050  while (NextEntry != NULL) {
3051 
3052  if (NextEntry->MappedSystemVa == (PVOID) MemoryDescriptorList) {
3053 
3054  if (PrevEntry != NULL) {
3055  PrevEntry->Next = NextEntry->Next;
3056  }
3057  else {
3058  MmLockedIoPagesHead.Next = (PSINGLE_LIST_ENTRY) NextEntry->Next;
3059  }
3060 
3061  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3062 
3063  ExFreePool (NextEntry);
3064 
3065  return TRUE;
3066  }
3067 
3068  PrevEntry = NextEntry;
3069  NextEntry = NextEntry->Next;
3070  }
3071 
3072  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3073 
3074  return FALSE;
3075 }
3076 
3077 LOGICAL
3078 MmIsIoSpaceActive (
3079  __in PHYSICAL_ADDRESS StartAddress,
3080  __in SIZE_T NumberOfBytes
3081  )
3082 
3083 /*++
3084 
3085 Routine Description:
3086 
3087  This routine returns TRUE if any portion of the requested range still has
3088  an outstanding pending I/O. It is the calling driver's responsibility to
3089  unmap all usermode mappings to the specified range (so another transfer
3090  cannot be initiated) prior to calling this API.
3091 
3092  These counts are kept because SANs will want to reuse the physical space
3093  but cannot do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
3094  going from/to it. If the process has not exited, but the SAN driver has
3095  unmapped the views to its I/O space, it still needs this as a way to know
3096  that the application does not have a transfer in progress to the previously
3097  mapped space.
3098 
3099 Arguments:
3100 
3101  StartAddress - Supplies the physical address of the start of the I/O range.
3102  This MUST NOT be within system DRAM as those pages are not
3103  tracked by this structure.
3104 
3105  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes in the range.
3106 
3107 Return Value:
3108 
3109  TRUE if any page in the range is currently locked for I/O, FALSE if not.
3110 
3111 Environment:
3112 
3113  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
3114 
3115 --*/
3116 
3117 {
3118  KIRQL OldIrql;
3119  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3120  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
