3121  PPFN_NUMBER LastPage;
3122  PVOID StartingVa;
3123  PMDL MemoryDescriptorList;
3124  PFN_NUMBER StartPage;
3125  PFN_NUMBER EndPage;
3126  PHYSICAL_ADDRESS EndAddress;
3127 
3128  ASSERT (NumberOfBytes != 0);
3129  StartPage = (PFN_NUMBER) (StartAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
3130  EndAddress.QuadPart = StartAddress.QuadPart + NumberOfBytes - 1;
3131  EndPage = (PFN_NUMBER) (EndAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
3132 
3133 #if DBG
3134  do {
3135  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PFN (StartPage));
3136  StartPage += 1;
3137  } while (StartPage <= EndPage);
3138  StartPage = (PFN_NUMBER) (StartAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
3139 #endif
3140 
3141  InterlockedIncrement (&MiActiveIoCounter);
3142 
3143  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, &OldIrql);
3144 
3145  MemoryDescriptorList = (PMDL) MmLockedIoPagesHead.Next;
3146 
3147  while (MemoryDescriptorList != NULL) {
3148 
3149  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
3150  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
3151 
3152  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(StartingVa,
3153  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
3154 
3155  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
3156 
3157  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
3158 
3159  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
3160 
3161  do {
3162 
3163  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3164 
3165  //
3166  // There are no more locked pages.
3167  //
3168 
3169  break;
3170  }
3171 
3172  if ((*Page >= StartPage) && (*Page <= EndPage)) {
3173  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3174  return TRUE;
3175  }
3176 
3177  Page += 1;
3178 
3179  } while (Page < LastPage);
3180 
3181  MemoryDescriptorList = MemoryDescriptorList->Next;
3182  }
3183 
3184  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3185 
3186  return FALSE;
3187 }

3189 LOGICAL
3190 MiIsProbeActive (
3191  IN PMMPTE InputPte,
3192  IN PFN_NUMBER InputPages
3193  )
3194 
3195 /*++
3196 
3197 Routine Description:
3198 
3199  This routine returns TRUE if any portion of the requested range still has
3200  an outstanding pending I/O.
3201 
3202  These counts are kept because drivers will want to remap the physical space
3203  but cannot do this unless it is guaranteed there are no more pending I/Os
3204  going from/to it.
3205 
3206 Arguments:
3207 
3208  InputPte - Supplies the starting PTE of the range to check.
3209 
3210  InputPages - Supplies the number of pages to check.
3211 
3212 Return Value:
3213 
3214  TRUE if any page in the range is currently locked for I/O, FALSE if not.
3215 
3216 Environment:
3217 
3218  Kernel mode, working set pushlock held, APC_LEVEL.
3219 
3220 --*/

3222 {
3223  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3224  KIRQL OldIrql;
3225  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3226  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
3227  PPFN_NUMBER LastPage;
3228  PVOID StartingVa;
3229  PMDL MemoryDescriptorList;
3230  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3231 
3232  InterlockedIncrement (&MiActiveIoCounter);
3233 
3234  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, &OldIrql);
3235 
3236  MemoryDescriptorList = (PMDL) MmLockedIoPagesHead.Next;
3237 
3238  while (MemoryDescriptorList != NULL) {
3239 
3240  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
3241  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
3242

3244  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
3245 
3246  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
3247 
3248  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
3249 
3250  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
3251 
3252  do {
3253 
3254  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3255 
3256  //
3257  // There are no more locked pages.
3258  //
3259 
3260  break;
3261  }
3262

3264  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
3265  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
3266 
3267  if (*Page == PageFrameIndex) {
3268  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3269  return TRUE;
3270  }
3271  }
3272 
3273  Page += 1;
3274 
3275  } while (Page < LastPage);
3276 
3277  MemoryDescriptorList = MemoryDescriptorList->Next;
3278  }
3279 
3280  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock, OldIrql);
3281

3284 
3285 
3286 VOID
3287 MmUnlockPages (
3288  __inout PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
3289  )
3290 
3291 /*++
3292 
3293 Routine Description:
3294 
3295  This routine unlocks physical pages which are described by a Memory
3296  Descriptor List.
3297 
3298 Arguments:
3299 
3300  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a memory descriptor list
3301  (MDL). The supplied MDL must have been supplied
3302  to MmLockPages to lock the pages down. As the
3303  pages are unlocked, the MDL is updated.
3304 
3305 Return Value:
3306 
3307  None.
3308 
3309 Environment:
3310 
3311  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
3312 
3313 --*/
3314 
3315 {
3316  LONG EntryCount;
3317  LONG OriginalCount;
3318  PVOID OldValue;
3319  PETHREAD CurrentThread;
3320  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
3321  PEPROCESS MdlProcess;
3322  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3323  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
3324  PPFN_NUMBER LastPage;
3325  PVOID StartingVa;
3326  KIRQL OldIrql;
3327  PMMPFN Pfn1;
3328  CSHORT MdlFlags;
3329  PSLIST_ENTRY SingleListEntry;
3330  PMI_PFN_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK DerefMdl;
3331  PSLIST_HEADER PfnDereferenceSListHead;
3332  PSLIST_ENTRY *PfnDeferredList;
3333 
3334  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED) != 0);
3335  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL) == 0);
3336  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL) == 0);
3337  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
3338 
3339  MdlProcess = MemoryDescriptorList->Process;
3340 
3341  //
3342  // Carefully snap a copy of the MDL flags - realize that bits in it may
3343  // change due to some of the subroutines called below. Only bits that
3344  // we know can't change are examined in this local copy. This is done
3345  // to reduce the amount of processing while the PFN lock is held.
3346  //
3347 
3348  MdlFlags = MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags;
3349 
3350  if (MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
3351 
3352  //
3353  // This MDL has been mapped into system space, unmap now.
3354  //
3355 
3356  MmUnmapLockedPages (MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa,
3357  MemoryDescriptorList);
3358  }
3359 
3360  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
3361  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
3362  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
3363 
3364  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(StartingVa,
3365  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
3366 
3367  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
3368 
3369  if (MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) {
3370 
3371  ASSERT (MdlProcess != NULL);
3372  ASSERT (MdlProcess->AweInfo != NULL);
3373 
3374  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
3375 
3376  //
3377  // Note neither AWE nor PFN locks are needed for unlocking these MDLs
3378  // in all but the very rare cases (see below).
3379  //
3380 
3381  do {
3382 
3383 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
3384  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3385 
3386  //
3387  // There are no more locked pages - if there were none at all
3388  // then we're done.
3389  //
3390 
3391  break;
3392  }
3393 
3394  ASSERT (MI_IS_PFN (*Page));
3395  ASSERT (*Page <= MmHighestPhysicalPage);
3396  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
3397 
3398  do {
3399  EntryCount = ReadForWriteAccess (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
3400 
3401  ASSERT ((LONG)EntryCount > 0);
3402  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.AweAllocation == 1);
3403  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
3404 
3405  OriginalCount = InterlockedCompareExchange (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount,
3406  EntryCount - 1,
3407  EntryCount);
3408 
3409  if (OriginalCount == EntryCount) {
3410 
3411  //
3412  // This thread can be racing against other threads also
3413  // calling MmUnlockPages and also a thread calling
3414  // NtFreeUserPhysicalPages. All threads can safely do
3415  // interlocked decrements on the "AWE reference count".
3416  // Whichever thread drives it to zero is responsible for
3417  // decrementing the actual PFN reference count (which may
3418  // be greater than 1 due to other non-AWE API calls being
3419  // used on the same page). The thread that drives this
3420  // reference count to zero must put the page on the actual
3421  // freelist at that time and decrement various resident
3422  // available and commitment counters also.
3423  //
3424 
3425  if (OriginalCount == 1) {
3426 
3427  //
3428  // This thread has driven the AWE reference count to
3429  // zero so it must initiate a decrement of the PFN
3430  // reference count (while holding the PFN lock), etc.
3431  //
3432  // This path should be rare since typically I/Os
3433  // complete before these types of pages are freed by
3434  // the app.
3435  //
3436 
3437  MiDecrementReferenceCountForAwePage (Pfn1, FALSE);
3438  }
3439 
3440  break;
3441  }
3442  } while (TRUE);
3443 
3444  Page += 1;
3445  } while (Page < LastPage);
3446 
3447  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~(MDL_PAGES_LOCKED | MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE);
3448 
3449  return;
3450  }
3451 
3452  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
3453  MiFreeMdlTracker (MemoryDescriptorList, NumberOfPages);
3454  }
3455 
3456  //
3457  // Try for the fast path if not I/O space.
3458  //
3459 
3460  if ((MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0) {
3461 
3462  CurrentThread = NULL;
3463  CurrentProcess = NULL;
3464 
3465  if (MdlProcess != NULL) {
3466  ASSERT ((SPFN_NUMBER)MdlProcess->NumberOfLockedPages >= 0);
3467  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MdlProcess->NumberOfLockedPages,
3468  0 - NumberOfPages);
3469 
3470  //
3471  // See if this was a transfer from user space and we are in the
3472  // initiating process context. If so, set Thread to indicate
3473  // the fastpath (using the working set pushlock instead of the PFN
3474  // lock) should be used.
3475  //
3476 
3477  if (((MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) == 0) &&
3478  (KeGetCurrentIrql () == PASSIVE_LEVEL)) {
3479 
3480  CurrentThread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
3481  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (CurrentThread);
3482  }
3483  }
3484 
3485  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
3486 
3487  //
3488  // Calculate PFN addresses and termination without the PFN lock
3489  // (it's not needed for this) to reduce PFN lock contention.
3490  //
3491 
3492  ASSERT (sizeof(PFN_NUMBER) == sizeof(PMMPFN));
3493 
3494  do {
3495 
3496  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3497 
3498  //
3499  // There are no more locked pages - if there were none at all
3500  // then we're done.
3501  //
3502 
3503  if (Page == (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1)) {
3504  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
3505  return;
3506  }
3507 
3508  LastPage = Page;
3509  break;
3510  }
3511  ASSERT (MI_IS_PFN (*Page));
3512  ASSERT (*Page <= MmHighestPhysicalPage);
3513 
3514  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
3515  *Page = (PFN_NUMBER) Pfn1;
3516  Page += 1;
3517  } while (Page < LastPage);
3518 
3519  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
3520 
3521  //
3522  // If this was a transfer from user space and we are in the
3523  // initiating process context then take advantage of this fact
3524  // and unlock the pages using the process' working set pushlock
3525  // instead of the PFN lock.
3526  //
3527 
3528  if (CurrentThread != NULL) {
3529 
3530  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3531  LOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3532  }
3533  else {
3534  LOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3535  }
3536 
3537  //
3538  // If all the pages are still valid in the process' address space
3539  // then process the pages directly here without the PFN lock.
3540  // Note if any of the pages are no longer valid in this process'
3541  // address space then the entire MDL must be processed under the
3542  // PFN lock.
3543  //
3544 
3545  do {
3546  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
3547 
3548  if (Pfn1->u2.ShareCount >= 1) {
3549 
3550  if (Pfn1->u3.e1.PrototypePte == 0) {
3551 
3552  //
3553  // This page is still mapped and it's private so it
3554  // must be mapped in this process.
3555  //
3556 
3557  NOTHING;
3558  }
3559  else if (CurrentProcess != MdlProcess) {
3560 
3561  //
3562  // This is a shared page so the working set pushlock
3563  // is not sufficient - the PXE/PPE/PDE/PTE mappings
3564  // must be checked.
3565  //
3566  // Since we are not in the address space of the MDL's
3567  // initiating process, it's not worth the cost of
3568  // attaching to interrogate. Just go the expensive
3569  // (PFN) way instead.
3570  //
3571 
3572  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3573  CurrentThread = NULL;
3574  break;
3575  }
3576  else {
3577 
3578  //
3579  // This is a sharable page so the current process'
3580  // working set pushlock is not enough to check
3581  // the PFN contents. The PXE/PPE/PDE/PTE hierarchy
3582  // must be checked to ensure the user has not deleted
3583  // (and replaced) the original virtual address space.
3584  //
3585 
3586  PVOID TempVa;
3587  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
3588 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
3589  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
3590 #endif
3591 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
3592  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
3593 #endif
3594  PMMPTE PointerPde;
3595  PMMPTE PointerPte;
3596 
3597  TempVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa + ((Page -
3598  (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1)) << PAGE_SHIFT));
3599 
3600 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
3601  PointerPxe = MiGetPxeAddress (TempVa);
3602  if (PointerPxe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3603  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3604  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3605  }
3606  else {
3607  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3608  }
3609  CurrentThread = NULL;
3610  break;
3611  }
3612 #endif
3613 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
3614  PointerPpe = MiGetPpeAddress (TempVa);
3615  if (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3616  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3617  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3618  }
3619  else {
3620  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3621  }
3622  CurrentThread = NULL;
3623  break;
3624  }
3625 #endif
3626  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (TempVa);
3627 
3628  if (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3629  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3630  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3631  }
3632  else {
3633  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3634  }
3635  CurrentThread = NULL;
3636  break;
3637  }
3638 
3639  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde)) {
3640  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde) + MiGetPteOffset (TempVa);
3641  }
3642  else {
3643  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (TempVa);
3644 
3645  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
3646  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3647  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3648  }
3649  else {
3650  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3651  }
3652  CurrentThread = NULL;
3653  break;
3654  }
3655 
3656  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
3657  }
3658  if (MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex) != (PMMPFN) *Page) {
3659  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3660  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3661  }
3662  else {
3663  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3664  }
3665  CurrentThread = NULL;
3666  break;
3667  }
3668  }
3669  }
3670  else {
3671  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3672  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3673  }
3674  else {
3675  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3676  }
3677  CurrentThread = NULL;
3678  break;
3679  }
3680 
3681  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= 2);
3682 
3683  Page += 1;
3684  } while (Page < LastPage);
3685 
3686  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
3687 
3688  if (CurrentThread != NULL) {
3689  do {
3690  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
3691  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount >= 2);
3692 
3693  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
3694 
3695  Page += 1;
3696  } while (Page < LastPage);
3697 
3698  if (CurrentProcess == MdlProcess) {
3699  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3700  }
3701  else {
3702  UNLOCK_WS_SHARED_CROSS_PROCESS (CurrentThread, MdlProcess);
3703  }
3704 
3705  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
3706 
3707  return;
3708  }
3709  }
3710 
3711  //
3712  // If the MDL can be queued so the PFN acquisition/release can be
3713  // amortized then do so.
3714  //
3715 
3716  if (NumberOfPages <= MI_MAX_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK) {
3717 
3718 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3719 
3720  PKNODE Node = KeGetCurrentNode ();
3721 
3722  //
3723  // The node may change beneath us but that should be fairly
3724  // infrequent and not worth checking for. Just make sure the
3725  // same node that gives us a free entry gets the deferred entry
3726  // back.
3727  //
3728 
3729  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &Node->PfnDereferenceSListHead;
3730 #else
3731  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &MmPfnDereferenceSListHead;
3732 #endif
3733 
3734  //
3735  // Pop an entry from the freelist.
3736  //
3737 
3738  SingleListEntry = InterlockedPopEntrySList (PfnDereferenceSListHead);
3739 
3740  if (SingleListEntry != NULL) {
3741  DerefMdl = CONTAINING_RECORD (SingleListEntry,
3742  MI_PFN_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK,
3743  ListEntry);
3744 
3745  DerefMdl->Flags = MdlFlags;
3746  DerefMdl->NumberOfPages = (USHORT) (LastPage - Page);
3747 
3748 #if defined (_WIN64)
3749 
3750  //
3751  // Avoid the majority of the high cost of RtlCopyMemory on
3752  // 64 bit platforms.
3753  //
3754 
3755  if (DerefMdl->NumberOfPages == 1) {
3756  DerefMdl->Pfns[0] = *Page;
3757  }
3758  else if (DerefMdl->NumberOfPages == 2) {
3759  DerefMdl->Pfns[0] = *Page;
3760  DerefMdl->Pfns[1] = *(Page + 1);
3761  }
3762  else
3763 #endif
3764  RtlCopyMemory ((PVOID)(&DerefMdl->Pfns[0]),
3765  (PVOID)Page,
3766  (LastPage - Page) * sizeof (PFN_NUMBER));
3767 
3768  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
3769 
3770  //
3771  // Push this entry on the deferred list.
3772  //
3773 
3774 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3775  PfnDeferredList = &Node->PfnDeferredList;
3776 #else
3777  PfnDeferredList = &MmPfnDeferredList;
3778 #endif
3779 
3780  do {
3781 
3782  OldValue = *PfnDeferredList;
3783  SingleListEntry->Next = OldValue;
3784 
3785  } while (InterlockedCompareExchangePointer (
3786  PfnDeferredList,
3787  SingleListEntry,
3788  OldValue) != OldValue);
3789  return;
3790  }
3791  }
3792 
3793  SingleListEntry = NULL;
3794 
3795  if (MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
3796 
3797  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3798 
3799  do {
3800 
3801  //
3802  // If this was a write operation set the modified bit in the
3803  // PFN database.
3804  //
3805 
3806  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
3807 
3808  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x3);
3809 
3810  if ((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
3811  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0)) {
3812 
3813  ULONG FreeBit;
3814  FreeBit = GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
3815 
3816  if ((FreeBit != 0) && (FreeBit != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
3817  MiReleaseConfirmedPageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
3818  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.PageFileHigh = 0;
3819  }
3820  }
3821 
3822  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
3823 
3824  Page += 1;
3825  } while (Page < LastPage);
3826  }
3827  else {
3828 
3829  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3830 
3831  do {
3832 
3833  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
3834 
3835  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
3836 
3837  Page += 1;
3838  } while (Page < LastPage);
3839  }
3840 
3841  if (NumberOfPages <= MI_MAX_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK) {
3842 
3843  //
3844  // The only reason this code path is being reached is because
3845  // a deferred entry was not available so clear the list now.
3846  //
3847 
3848  MiDeferredUnlockPages (MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD | MI_DEFER_DRAIN_LOCAL_ONLY);
3849  }
3850 
3851  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3852  }
3853  else {
3854 
3855  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
3856 
3857  if (MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
3858 
3859  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3860 
3861  do {
3862 
3863  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3864  break;
3865  }
3866 
3867  if (MI_IS_PFN (*Page)) {
3868 
3869  //
3870  // If this was a write operation set the modified bit in the
3871  // PFN database.
3872  //
3873 
3874  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
3875 
3876  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x3);
3877 
3878  if ((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
3879  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0)) {
3880 
3881  ULONG FreeBit;
3882  FreeBit = GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
3883 
3884  if ((FreeBit != 0) && (FreeBit != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
3885  MiReleaseConfirmedPageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
3886  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.PageFileHigh = 0;
3887  }
3888  }
3889 
3890  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
3891  }
3892 
3893  Page += 1;
3894  } while (Page < LastPage);
3895  }
3896  else {
3897 
3898  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3899 
3900  do {
3901 
3902  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
3903  break;
3904  }
3905 
3906  if (MI_IS_PFN (*Page)) {
3907  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
3908  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
3909  }
3910 
3911  Page += 1;
3912  } while (Page < LastPage);
3913  }
3914 
3915  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3916 
3917  if (MdlProcess != NULL) {
3918  ASSERT ((SPFN_NUMBER)MdlProcess->NumberOfLockedPages >= 0);
3919  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MdlProcess->NumberOfLockedPages,
3920  0 - NumberOfPages);
3921  }
3922 
3923  MiDereferenceIoSpace (MemoryDescriptorList);
3924 
3925  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~MDL_IO_SPACE;
3926  }
3927 
3928  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~MDL_PAGES_LOCKED;
3929 
3930  return;
3931 }
3932 
3933 
3934 VOID
3935 MiDeferredUnlockPages (
3936  ULONG Flags
3937  )
3938 
3939 /*++
3940 
3941 Routine Description:
3942 
3943  This routine unlocks physical pages which were previously described by
3944  a Memory Descriptor List.
3945 
3946 Arguments:
3947 
3948  Flags - Supplies a bitfield of the caller's needs :
3949 
3950  MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD - Indicates the caller holds the PFN lock on entry.
3951 
3952  MI_DEFER_DRAIN_LOCAL_ONLY - Indicates the caller only wishes to drain
3953  the current processor's queue. This only
3954  has meaning in NUMA systems.
3955 
3956 Return Value:
3957 
3958  None.
3959 
3960 Environment:
3961 
3962  Kernel mode, PFN database lock *MAY* be held on entry (see Flags).
3963 
3964 --*/
3965 
3966 {
3967  KIRQL OldIrql = 0;
3968  ULONG FreeBit;
3969  ULONG i;
3970  ULONG ListCount;
3971  ULONG TotalNodes;
3972  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
3973  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
3974  PPFN_NUMBER LastPage;
3975  PMMPFN Pfn1;
3976  CSHORT MdlFlags;
3977  PSLIST_ENTRY SingleListEntry;
3978  PSLIST_ENTRY LastEntry;
3979  PSLIST_ENTRY FirstEntry;
3980  PSLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
3981  PSLIST_ENTRY VeryLastEntry;
3982  PMI_PFN_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK DerefMdl;
3983  PSLIST_HEADER PfnDereferenceSListHead;
3984  PSLIST_ENTRY *PfnDeferredList;
3985 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
3986  PKNODE Node;
3987 #endif
3988 
3989  i = 0;
3990  ListCount = 0;
3991  TotalNodes = 1;
3992 
3993  if ((Flags & MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD) == 0) {
3994  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
3995  }
3996 
3997  MM_PFN_LOCK_ASSERT();
3998 
3999 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
4000  if (Flags & MI_DEFER_DRAIN_LOCAL_ONLY) {
4001  Node = KeGetCurrentNode();
4002  PfnDeferredList = &Node->PfnDeferredList;
4003  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &Node->PfnDereferenceSListHead;
4004  }
4005  else {
4006  TotalNodes = KeNumberNodes;
4007  Node = KeNodeBlock[0];
4008  PfnDeferredList = &Node->PfnDeferredList;
4009  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &Node->PfnDereferenceSListHead;
4010  }
4011 #else
4012  PfnDeferredList = &MmPfnDeferredList;
4013  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &MmPfnDereferenceSListHead;
4014 #endif
4015 
4016  do {
4017 
4018  if (*PfnDeferredList == NULL) {
4019 
4020 #if !defined(MI_MULTINODE)
4021  if ((Flags & MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD) == 0) {
4022  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
4023  }
4024  return;
4025 #else
4026  i += 1;
4027  if (i < TotalNodes) {
4028  Node = KeNodeBlock[i];
4029  PfnDeferredList = &Node->PfnDeferredList;
4030  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &Node->PfnDereferenceSListHead;
4031  continue;
4032  }
4033  break;
4034 #endif
4035  }
4036 
4037  //
4038  // Process each deferred unlock entry until they're all done.
4039  //
4040 
4041  LastEntry = NULL;
4042  VeryLastEntry = NULL;
4043 
4044  do {
4045 
4046  SingleListEntry = *PfnDeferredList;
4047 
4048  FirstEntry = SingleListEntry;
4049 
4050  do {
4051 
4052  NextEntry = SingleListEntry->Next;
4053 
4054  //
4055  // Process the deferred entry.
4056  //
4057 
4058  DerefMdl = CONTAINING_RECORD (SingleListEntry,
4059  MI_PFN_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK,
4060  ListEntry);
4061 
4062  MdlFlags = DerefMdl->Flags;
4063  NumberOfPages = (PFN_NUMBER) DerefMdl->NumberOfPages;
4064  ASSERT (NumberOfPages <= MI_MAX_DEREFERENCE_CHUNK);
4065  Page = &DerefMdl->Pfns[0];
4066  LastPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
4067 
4068 #if DBG
4069  //
4070  // Mark the entry as processed so if it mistakenly gets
4071  // reprocessed, we will assert above.
4072  //
4073 
4074  DerefMdl->NumberOfPages |= 0x80;
4075 #endif
4076  if (MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
4077 
4078  do {
4079 
4080  //
4081  // If this was a write operation set the modified bit
4082  // in the PFN database.
4083  //
4084 
4085  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
4086 
4087  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x4);
4088 
4089  if ((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
4090  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0)) {
4091 
4092  FreeBit = GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
4093 
4094  if ((FreeBit != 0) && (FreeBit != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
4095  MiReleaseConfirmedPageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
4096  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.PageFileHigh = 0;
4097  }
4098  }
4099 
4100  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
4101 
4102  Page += 1;
4103  } while (Page < LastPage);
4104  }
4105  else {
4106 
4107  do {
4108 
4109  Pfn1 = (PMMPFN) (*Page);
4110 
4111  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
4112 
4113  Page += 1;
4114  } while (Page < LastPage);
4115  }
4116 
4117  ListCount += 1;
4118 
4119  //
4120  // March on to the next entry if there is one.
4121  //
4122 
4123  if (NextEntry == LastEntry) {
4124  break;
4125  }
4126 
4127  SingleListEntry = NextEntry;
4128 
4129  } while (TRUE);
4130 
4131  if (VeryLastEntry == NULL) {
4132  VeryLastEntry = SingleListEntry;
4133  }
4134 
4135  if (InterlockedCompareExchangePointer (PfnDeferredList,
4136  NULL,
4137  FirstEntry) == FirstEntry) {
4138  ASSERT (*PfnDeferredList != FirstEntry);
4139  break;
4140  }
4141  ASSERT (*PfnDeferredList != FirstEntry);
4142  LastEntry = FirstEntry;
4143 
4144  } while (TRUE);
4145 
4146  //
4147  // Push the processed list chain on the freelist.
4148  //
4149 
4150  ASSERT (ListCount != 0);
4151  ASSERT (FirstEntry != NULL);
4152  ASSERT (VeryLastEntry != NULL);
4153 
4154 #if defined(MI_MULTINODE)
4155  InterlockedPushListSList (PfnDereferenceSListHead,
4156  FirstEntry,
4157  VeryLastEntry,
4158  ListCount);
4159 
4160  i += 1;
4161  if (i < TotalNodes) {
4162  Node = KeNodeBlock[i];
4163  PfnDeferredList = &Node->PfnDeferredList;
4164  PfnDereferenceSListHead = &Node->PfnDereferenceSListHead;
4165  ListCount = 0;
4166  }
4167  else {
4168  break;
4169  }
4170  } while (TRUE);
4171 #else
4172  } while (FALSE);
4173 #endif
4174 
4175  if ((Flags & MI_DEFER_PFN_HELD) == 0) {
4176  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
4177  }
4178 
4179 #if !defined(MI_MULTINODE)
4180 
4181  //
4182  // If possible, push the processed chain after releasing the PFN lock.
4183  //
4184 
4185  InterlockedPushListSList (PfnDereferenceSListHead,
4186  FirstEntry,
4187  VeryLastEntry,
4188  ListCount);
4189 #endif
4190 }
4191 
4192 VOID
4193 MmBuildMdlForNonPagedPool (
4194  __inout PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
4195  )
4196 
4197 /*++
4198 
4199 Routine Description:
4200 
4201  This routine fills in the "pages" portion of the MDL using the PFN
4202  numbers corresponding to the buffers which reside in non-paged pool.
4203 
4204  Unlike MmProbeAndLockPages, there is no corresponding unlock as no
4205  reference counts are incremented as the buffers being in nonpaged
4206  pool are always resident.
4207 
4208 Arguments:
4209 
4210  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a pointer to a Memory Descriptor List
4211  (MDL). The supplied MDL must supply a virtual
4212  address, byte offset and length field. The
4213  physical page portion of the MDL is updated when
4214  the pages are locked in memory. The virtual
4215  address must be within the non-paged portion
4216  of the system space.
4217 
4218 Return Value:
4219 
4220  None.
4221 
4222 Environment:
4223 
4224  Kernel mode, IRQL of DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
4225 
4226 --*/
4227 
4228 {
4229  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
4230  PPFN_NUMBER EndPage;
4231  PMMPTE PointerPte;
4232  PVOID VirtualAddress;
4233  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
4234  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
4235 
4236  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
4237 
4238  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
4239  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (
4240  MDL_PAGES_LOCKED |
4241  MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA |
4242  MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL |
4243  MDL_PARTIAL)) == 0);
4244 
4245  MemoryDescriptorList->Process = NULL;
4246 
4247  //
4248  // Endva is last byte of the buffer.
4249  //
4250 
4251  VirtualAddress = MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa;
4252 
4253  MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa =
4254  (PVOID)((PCHAR)VirtualAddress + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
4255 
4256  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa,
4257  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
4258 
4259  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
4260 
4261  EndPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
4262 
4263  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS(VirtualAddress)) {
4264 
4265  PageFrameIndex = MI_CONVERT_PHYSICAL_TO_PFN (VirtualAddress);
4266 
4267  do {
4268 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
4269  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
4270  Page += 1;
4271  PageFrameIndex += 1;
4272  } while (Page < EndPage);
4273 
4274  PageFrameIndex -= 1;
4275  }
4276  else {
4277 
4278  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
4279 
4280  do {
4281  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
4282  *Page = PageFrameIndex;
4283  Page += 1;
4284  PointerPte += 1;
4285  } while (Page < EndPage);
4286  }
4287 
4288  ASSERT ((MmIsNonPagedSystemAddressValid (MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa)) ||
4289  (MmAreMdlPagesLocked (MemoryDescriptorList)));
4290 
4291  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL;
4292 
4293  //
4294  // Assume either all the frames are in the PFN database (ie: the MDL maps
4295  // pool) or none of them (the MDL maps dualport RAM) are.
4296  //
4297 
4298  if (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
4299  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_IO_SPACE;
4300  }
4301 
4302  return;
4303 }
4304 
4305 VOID
4306 MiInitializeIoTrackers (
4307  VOID
4308  )
4309 {
4310  InitializeSListHead (&MiDeadPteTrackerSListHead);
4311  KeInitializeSpinLock (&MiPteTrackerLock);
4312  InitializeListHead (&MiPteHeader.ListHead);
4313 
4314  KeInitializeSpinLock (&MmIoTrackerLock);
4315  InitializeListHead (&MmIoHeader);
4316 
4317  KeInitializeSpinLock (&MiTrackIoLock);
4318 }
4319 
4320 VOID
4321 MiInsertPteTracker (
4322  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
4323  IN ULONG Flags,
4324  IN LOGICAL IoMapping,
4325  IN MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute,
4326  IN PVOID MyCaller,
4327  IN PVOID MyCallersCaller
4328  )
4329 
4330 /*++
4331 
4332 Routine Description:
4333 
4334  This function inserts a PTE tracking block as the caller has just
4335  consumed system PTEs.
4336 
4337 Arguments:
4338 
4339  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List.
4340 
4341  Flags - Supplies the following values:
4342 
4343  0 - Indicates all the fields of the MDL are legitimate and can
4344  be snapped.
4345 
4346  1 - Indicates the caller is mapping physically contiguous memory.
4347  The only valid MDL fields are Page[0] & ByteCount.
4348  Page[0] contains the PFN start, ByteCount the byte count.
4349 
4350  2 - Indicates the caller is just reserving mapping PTEs.
4351  The only valid MDL fields are Page[0] & ByteCount.
4352  Page[0] contains the pool tag, ByteCount the byte count.
4353 
4354  MyCaller - Supplies the return address of the caller who consumed the
4355  system PTEs to map this MDL.
4356 
4357  MyCallersCaller - Supplies the return address of the caller of the caller
4358  who consumed the system PTEs to map this MDL.
4359 
4360 Return Value:
4361 
4362  None.
4363 
4364 Environment:
4365 
4366  Kernel mode, DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
4367 
4368 --*/
4369 
4370 {
4371  KIRQL OldIrql;
4372  PVOID StartingVa;
4373  PPTE_TRACKER Tracker;
4374  PSLIST_ENTRY SingleListEntry;
4375  PSLIST_ENTRY NextSingleListEntry;
4376  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes;
4377 
4378  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
4379 
4380  if (ExQueryDepthSList (&MiDeadPteTrackerSListHead) < 10) {
4381  Tracker = (PPTE_TRACKER) InterlockedPopEntrySList (&MiDeadPteTrackerSListHead);
4382  }
4383  else {
4384  SingleListEntry = ExInterlockedFlushSList (&MiDeadPteTrackerSListHead);
4385 
4386  Tracker = (PPTE_TRACKER) SingleListEntry;
4387 
4388  if (SingleListEntry != NULL) {
4389 
4390  SingleListEntry = SingleListEntry->Next;
4391 
4392  while (SingleListEntry != NULL) {
4393 
4394  NextSingleListEntry = SingleListEntry->Next;
4395 
4396  ExFreePool (SingleListEntry);
4397 
4398  SingleListEntry = NextSingleListEntry;
4399  }
4400  }
4401  }
4402 
4403  if (Tracker == NULL) {
4404 
4405  Tracker = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
4406  sizeof (PTE_TRACKER),
4407  'ySmM');
4408 
4409  if (Tracker == NULL) {
4410  MiTrackPtesAborted = TRUE;
4411  return;
4412  }
4413  }
4414 
4415  switch (Flags) {
4416 
4417  case 0:
4418 
4419  //
4420  // Regular MDL mapping.
4421  //
4422 
4423  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
4424  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
4425 
4426  NumberOfPtes = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
4427  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
4428  Tracker->Mdl = MemoryDescriptorList;
4429 
4430  Tracker->StartVa = MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa;
4431  Tracker->Offset = MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset;
4432  Tracker->Length = MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount;
4433 
4434  break;
4435 
4436  case 1:
4437 
4438  //
4439  // MmMapIoSpace call (ie: physically contiguous mapping).
4440  //
4441 
4442  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
4443  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
4444 
4445  NumberOfPtes = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
4446  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
4447  Tracker->Mdl = (PVOID)1;
4448  break;
4449 
4450  default:
4451  ASSERT (FALSE);
4452  // Fall through
4453 
4454  case 2:
4455 
4456  //
4457  // MmAllocateReservedMapping call (ie: currently maps nothing).
4458  //
4459 
4460  NumberOfPtes = (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount >> PAGE_SHIFT);
4461  Tracker->Mdl = NULL;
4462  break;
4463  }
4464 
4465  Tracker->Count = NumberOfPtes;
4466 
4467  Tracker->CallingAddress = MyCaller;
4468  Tracker->CallersCaller = MyCallersCaller;
4469 
4470  Tracker->SystemVa = MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa;
4471  Tracker->Page = *(PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
4472 
4473  Tracker->CacheAttribute = CacheAttribute;
4474  Tracker->IoMapping = IoMapping;
4475  Tracker->Matched = 0;
4476 
4477  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiPteTrackerLock, &OldIrql);
4478 
4479  InsertHeadList (&MiPteHeader.ListHead, &Tracker->ListEntry);
4480 
4481  MiPteHeader.Count += NumberOfPtes;
4482  MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntries += 1;
4483 
4484  if (MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntries > MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntriesPeak) {
4485  MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntriesPeak = MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntries;
4486  }
4487 
4488  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiPteTrackerLock, OldIrql);
4489 }
4490 
4491 VOID
4492 MiRemovePteTracker (
4493  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList OPTIONAL,
4494  IN PVOID VirtualAddress,
4495  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes
4496  )
4497 
4498 /*++
4499 
4500 Routine Description:
4501 
4502  This function removes a PTE tracking block from the lists as the PTEs
4503  are being freed.
4504 
4505 Arguments:
4506 
4507  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List.
4508 
4509  PteAddress - Supplies the address the system PTEs were mapped to.
4510 
4511  NumberOfPtes - Supplies the number of system PTEs allocated.
4512 
4513 Return Value:
4514 
4515  None.
4516 
4517 Environment:
4518 
4519  Kernel mode, DISPATCH_LEVEL or below. Locks (including the PFN) may be held.
4520 
4521 --*/
4522 
4523 {
4524  KIRQL OldIrql;
4525  PPTE_TRACKER Tracker;
4526  PLIST_ENTRY LastFound;
4527  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4528 
4529  LastFound = NULL;
4530 
4531  VirtualAddress = PAGE_ALIGN (VirtualAddress);
4532 
4533  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiPteTrackerLock, &OldIrql);
4534 
4535  NextEntry = MiPteHeader.ListHead.Flink;
4536  while (NextEntry != &MiPteHeader.ListHead) {
4537 
4538  Tracker = (PPTE_TRACKER) CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
4539  PTE_TRACKER,
4540  ListEntry.Flink);
4541 
4542  if (VirtualAddress == PAGE_ALIGN (Tracker->SystemVa)) {
4543 
4544  if (LastFound != NULL) {
4545 
4546  //
4547  // Duplicate map entry.
4548  //
4549 
4550  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4551  0x1,
4552  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker,
4553  (ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList,
4554  (ULONG_PTR)LastFound);
4555  }
4556 
4557  if (Tracker->Count != NumberOfPtes) {
4558 
4559  //
4560  // Not unmapping the same of number of PTEs that were mapped.
4561  //
4562 
4563  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4564  0x2,
4565  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker,
4566  Tracker->Count,
4567  NumberOfPtes);
4568  }
4569 
4570  if ((ARGUMENT_PRESENT (MemoryDescriptorList)) &&
4571  ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_FREE_EXTRA_PTES) == 0) &&
4572  (MiMdlsAdjusted == FALSE)) {
4573 
4574  if (Tracker->SystemVa != MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa) {
4575 
4576  //
4577  // Not unmapping the same address that was mapped.
4578  //
4579 
4580  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4581  0x3,
4582  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker,
4583  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->SystemVa,
4584  (ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa);
4585  }
4586 
4587  if (Tracker->Page != *(PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1)) {
4588 
4589  //
4590  // The first page in the MDL has changed since it was mapped.
4591  //
4592 
4593  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4594  0x4,
4595  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker,
4596  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->Page,
4597  (ULONG_PTR) *(PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1));
4598  }
4599 
4600  if (Tracker->StartVa != MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa) {
4601 
4602  //
4603  // Map and unmap don't match up.
4604  //
4605 
4606  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4607  0x5,
4608  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker,
4609  (ULONG_PTR)Tracker->StartVa,
4610  (ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa);
4611  }
4612  }
4613 
4614  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
4615  LastFound = NextEntry;
4616  }
4617  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Flink;
4618  }
4619 
4620  if ((LastFound == NULL) && (MiTrackPtesAborted == FALSE)) {
4621 
4622  //
4623  // Can't unmap something that was never (or isn't currently) mapped.
4624  //
4625 
4626  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
4627  0x6,
4628  (ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList,
4629  (ULONG_PTR)VirtualAddress,
4630  (ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPtes);
4631  }
4632 
4633  MiPteHeader.Count -= NumberOfPtes;
4634  MiPteHeader.NumberOfEntries -= 1;
4635 
4636  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiPteTrackerLock, OldIrql);
4637 
4638  //
4639  // Insert the tracking block into the dead PTE list for later
4640  // release. Locks (including the PFN lock) may be held on entry, thus the
4641  // block cannot be directly freed to pool at this time.
4642  //
4643 
4644  if (LastFound != NULL) {
4645  InterlockedPushEntrySList (&MiDeadPteTrackerSListHead,
4646  (PSLIST_ENTRY)LastFound);
4647  }
4648 
4649  return;
4650 }
4651 
4652 PVOID
4653 MiGetHighestPteConsumer (
4654  OUT PULONG_PTR NumberOfPtes
4655  )
4656 
4657 /*++
4658 
4659 Routine Description:
4660 
4661  This function examines the PTE tracking blocks and returns the biggest
4662  consumer.
4663 
4664 Arguments:
4665 
4666  None.
4667 
4668 Return Value:
4669 
4670  The loaded module entry of the biggest consumer.
4671 
4672 Environment:
4673 
4674  Kernel mode, called during bugcheck only. Many locks may be held.
4675 
4676 --*/
4677 
4678 {
4679  PPTE_TRACKER Tracker;
4680  PVOID BaseAddress;
4681  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
4682  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4683  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry2;
4684  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY DataTableEntry;
4685  ULONG_PTR Highest;
4686  ULONG_PTR PagesByThisModule;
4687  PKLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY HighDataTableEntry;
4688 
4689  *NumberOfPtes = 0;
4690 
4691  //
4692  // No locks are acquired as this is only called during a bugcheck.
4693  //
4694 
4695  if ((MmTrackPtes & 0x1) == 0) {
4696  return NULL;
4697  }
4698 
4699  if (MiTrackPtesAborted == TRUE) {
4700  return NULL;
4701  }
4702 
4703  if (IsListEmpty (&MiPteHeader.ListHead)) {
4704  return NULL;
4705  }
4706 
4707  if (PsLoadedModuleList.Flink == NULL) {
4708  return NULL;
4709  }
4710 
4711  Highest = 0;
4712  HighDataTableEntry = NULL;
4713 
4714  //
4715  // Walk the loaded module list backwards so we do the kernel last as the
4716  // bit bucket for everyone else.
4717  //
4718 
4719  NextEntry = PsLoadedModuleList.Blink;
4720  while (NextEntry != &PsLoadedModuleList) {
4721 
4722  DataTableEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
4723  KLDR_DATA_TABLE_ENTRY,
4724  InLoadOrderLinks);
4725 
4726  PagesByThisModule = 0;
4727 
4728  //
4729  // Walk the PTE mapping list and update each driver's counts.
4730  //
4731 
4732  NextEntry2 = MiPteHeader.ListHead.Flink;
4733  while (NextEntry2 != &MiPteHeader.ListHead) {
4734 
4735  Tracker = (PPTE_TRACKER) CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry2,
4736  PTE_TRACKER,
4737  ListEntry.Flink);
4738 
4739  BaseAddress = Tracker->CallingAddress;
4740  NumberOfPages = Tracker->Count;
4741 
4742  if (Tracker->Matched == 1) {
4743 
4744  //
4745  // We already processed this one in an earlier loop.
4746  //
4747 
4748  NOTHING;
4749  }
4750  else if ((BaseAddress >= DataTableEntry->DllBase) &&
4751  (BaseAddress < (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)(DataTableEntry->DllBase) + DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage))) {
4752 
4753  PagesByThisModule += NumberOfPages;
4754  Tracker->Matched = 1;
4755  }
4756  else {
4757 
4758  //
4759  // See if the caller's caller can be charged instead. This way
4760  // drivers that call MmMapLockedPages (which in turn calls
4761  // MmMapLockedPagesSpecifyCache where the charging is done)
4762  // don't get their allocations incorrectly logged against the
4763  // kernel.
4764  //
4765 
4766  BaseAddress = Tracker->CallersCaller;
4767 
4768  if ((BaseAddress >= DataTableEntry->DllBase) &&
4769  (BaseAddress < (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)(DataTableEntry->DllBase) + DataTableEntry->SizeOfImage))) {
4770 
4771  PagesByThisModule += NumberOfPages;
4772  Tracker->Matched = 1;
4773  }
4774  }
4775 
4776  NextEntry2 = NextEntry2->Flink;
4777  }
4778 
4779  if (PagesByThisModule > Highest) {
4780  Highest = PagesByThisModule;
4781  HighDataTableEntry = DataTableEntry;
4782  }
4783 
4784  NextEntry = NextEntry->Blink;
4785  }
4786 
4787  *NumberOfPtes = Highest;
4788 
4789  return (PVOID)HighDataTableEntry;
4790 }
4791 
4792 MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE
4793 MiInsertIoSpaceMap (
4794  IN PVOID BaseVa,
4795  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
4796  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages,
4797  IN MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute
4798  )
4799 
4800 /*++
4801 
4802 Routine Description:
4803 
4804  This function inserts an I/O space tracking block, returning the cache
4805  type the caller should use. The cache type is different from the input
4806  cache type if an overlap collision is detected.
4807 
4808 Arguments:
4809 
4810  BaseVa - Supplies the virtual address that will be used for the mapping.
4811 
4812  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the starting physical page number that will be
4813  mapped.
4814 
4815  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to map.
4816 
4817  CacheAttribute - Supplies the caller's desired cache attribute.
4818 
4819 Return Value:
4820 
4821  The cache attribute that is safe to use.
4822 
4823 Environment:
4824 
4825  Kernel mode, DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
4826 
4827 --*/
4828 
4829 {
4830  KIRQL OldIrql;
4831  PMMIO_TRACKER Tracker;
4832  PMMIO_TRACKER Tracker2;
4833  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4834 
4835 #if DBG
4836 
4837  ULONG Hash;
4838 
4839 #endif
4840 
4841  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql() <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
4842 
4843  Tracker = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
4844  sizeof (MMIO_TRACKER),
4845  'ySmM');
4846 
4847  if (Tracker == NULL) {
4848  return MiNotMapped;
4849  }
4850 
4851  Tracker->BaseVa = BaseVa;
4852  Tracker->PageFrameIndex = PageFrameIndex;
4853  Tracker->NumberOfPages = NumberOfPages;
4854  Tracker->CacheAttribute = CacheAttribute;
4855 
4856  RtlZeroMemory (&Tracker->StackTrace[0], MI_IO_BACKTRACE_LENGTH * sizeof(PVOID));
4857 
4858 #if DBG
4859 
4860  RtlCaptureStackBackTrace (2, MI_IO_BACKTRACE_LENGTH, Tracker->StackTrace, &Hash);
4861 
4862 #endif
4863 
4864  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex));
4865 
4866  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmIoTrackerLock, &OldIrql);
4867 
4868  //
4869  // Scan I/O space mappings for duplicate or overlapping entries.
4870  //
4871 
4872  NextEntry = MmIoHeader.Flink;
4873  while (NextEntry != &MmIoHeader) {
4874 
4875  Tracker2 = (PMMIO_TRACKER) CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
4876  MMIO_TRACKER,
4877  ListEntry.Flink);
4878 
4879  if ((Tracker->PageFrameIndex < Tracker2->PageFrameIndex + Tracker2->NumberOfPages) &&
4880  (Tracker->PageFrameIndex + Tracker->NumberOfPages > Tracker2->PageFrameIndex)) {
4881 
4882 #if DBG
4883  if ((MmShowMapOverlaps & 0x1) ||
4884 
4885  ((Tracker->CacheAttribute != Tracker2->CacheAttribute) &&
4886  (MmShowMapOverlaps & 0x2))) {
4887 
4888  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4889  "MM: Iospace mapping overlap %p %p\n",
4890  Tracker,
4891  Tracker2);
4892 
4893  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4894  "Physical range 0x%p->%p first mapped %s at VA %p\n",
4895  Tracker2->PageFrameIndex << PAGE_SHIFT,
4896  (Tracker2->PageFrameIndex + Tracker2->NumberOfPages) << PAGE_SHIFT,
4897  MiCacheStrings[Tracker2->CacheAttribute],
4898  Tracker2->BaseVa);
4899 
4900  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4901  "\tCall stack: %p %p %p %p %p %p\n",
4902  Tracker2->StackTrace[0],
4903  Tracker2->StackTrace[1],
4904  Tracker2->StackTrace[2],
4905  Tracker2->StackTrace[3],
4906  Tracker2->StackTrace[4],
4907  Tracker2->StackTrace[5]);
4908 
4909  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4910  "Physical range 0x%p->%p now being mapped %s at VA %p\n",
4911  Tracker->PageFrameIndex << PAGE_SHIFT,
4912  (Tracker->PageFrameIndex + Tracker->NumberOfPages) << PAGE_SHIFT,
4913  MiCacheStrings[Tracker->CacheAttribute],
4914  Tracker->BaseVa);
4915 
4916  DbgPrintEx (DPFLTR_MM_ID, DPFLTR_ERROR_LEVEL,
4917  "\tCall stack: %p %p %p %p %p %p\n",
4918  Tracker->StackTrace[0],
4919  Tracker->StackTrace[1],
4920  Tracker->StackTrace[2],
4921  Tracker->StackTrace[3],
4922  Tracker->StackTrace[4],
4923  Tracker->StackTrace[5]);
4924 
4925  if (MmShowMapOverlaps & 0x80000000) {
4926  DbgBreakPoint ();
4927  }
4928  }
4929 #endif
4930 
4931  if (Tracker->CacheAttribute != Tracker2->CacheAttribute) {
4932  MiCacheOverride[3] += 1;
4933 
4934  Tracker->CacheAttribute = Tracker2->CacheAttribute;
4935  }
4936 
4937  //
4938  // Don't bother checking for overlapping multiple entries.
4939  // This would be a very strange driver bug and is already
4940  // caught by the verifier anyway.
4941  //
4942  }
4943 
4944  NextEntry = Tracker2->ListEntry.Flink;
4945  }
4946 
4947  InsertHeadList (&MmIoHeader, &Tracker->ListEntry);
4948 
4949 #if DBG
4950  MmIoHeaderCount += NumberOfPages;
4951  MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntries += 1;
4952 
4953  if (MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntries > MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntriesPeak) {
4954  MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntriesPeak = MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntries;
4955  }
4956 #endif
4957 
4958  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmIoTrackerLock, OldIrql);
4959 
4960  return Tracker->CacheAttribute;
4961 }
4962 
4963 VOID
4964 MiRemoveIoSpaceMap (
4965  IN PVOID BaseVa,
4966  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages
4967  )
4968 
4969 /*++
4970 
4971 Routine Description:
4972 
4973  This function removes an I/O space tracking block from the lists.
4974 
4975 Arguments:
4976 
4977  BaseVa - Supplies the virtual address that will be used for the unmapping.
4978 
4979  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to unmap.
4980 
4981 Return Value:
4982 
4983  None.
4984 
4985 Environment:
4986 
4987  Kernel mode, DISPATCH_LEVEL or below.
4988 
4989 --*/
4990 
4991 {
4992  KIRQL OldIrql;
4993  PMMIO_TRACKER Tracker;
4994  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
4995  PVOID AlignedVa;
4996 
4997  AlignedVa = PAGE_ALIGN (BaseVa);
4998 
4999  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MmIoTrackerLock, &OldIrql);
5000 
5001  NextEntry = MmIoHeader.Flink;
5002  while (NextEntry != &MmIoHeader) {
5003 
5004  Tracker = (PMMIO_TRACKER) CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
5005  MMIO_TRACKER,
5006  ListEntry.Flink);
5007 
5008  if ((PAGE_ALIGN (Tracker->BaseVa) == AlignedVa) &&
5009  (Tracker->NumberOfPages == NumberOfPages)) {
5010 
5011  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
5012 
5013 #if DBG
5014  MmIoHeaderCount -= NumberOfPages;
5015  MmIoHeaderNumberOfEntries -= 1;
5016 #endif
5017 
5018  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MmIoTrackerLock, OldIrql);
5019 
5020  ExFreePool (Tracker);
5021 
5022  return;
5023  }
5024  NextEntry = Tracker->ListEntry.Flink;
5025  }
5026 
5027  //
5028  // Can't unmap something that was never (or isn't currently) mapped.
5029  //
5030 
5031  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5032  0x400,
5033  (ULONG_PTR)BaseVa,
5034  (ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPages,
5035  0);
5036 }
5037 
5038 PVOID
5039 MiMapSinglePage (
5040  IN PVOID VirtualAddress OPTIONAL,
5041  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
5042  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType,
5043  IN MM_PAGE_PRIORITY Priority
5044  )
5045 
5046 /*++
5047 
5048 Routine Description:
5049 
5050  This function (re)maps a single system PTE to the specified physical page.
5051 
5052 Arguments:
5053 
5054  VirtualAddress - Supplies the virtual address to map the page frame at.
5055  NULL indicates a system PTE is needed. Non-NULL supplies
5056  the virtual address returned by an earlier
5057  MiMapSinglePage call.
5058 
5059  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the page frame index to map.
5060 
5061  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping to use for the MDL.
5062  MmCached indicates "normal" kernel or user mappings.
5063 
5064  Priority - Supplies an indication as to how important it is that this
5065  request succeed under low available PTE conditions.
5066 
5067 Return Value:
5068 
5069  Returns the base address where the page is mapped, or NULL if the
5070  mapping failed.
5071 
5072 Environment:
5073 
5074  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL or below. Since the process working set pushlock
5075  may be held by callers, this routine is nonpaged.
5076 
5077 --*/
5078 
5079 {
5080  KIRQL OldIrql;
5081  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5082  MMPTE TempPte;
5083  PMMPFN Pfn1;
5084  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
5085 
5086  PAGED_CODE ();
5087 
5088  UNREFERENCED_PARAMETER (Priority);
5089 
5090  ASSERT (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex));
5091 
5092  if (VirtualAddress == NULL) {
5093 
5094  PointerPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
5095 
5096  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
5097 
5098  //
5099  // Not enough system PTES are available.
5100  //
5101 
5102  return NULL;
5103  }
5104 
5105  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
5106  VirtualAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
5107  }
5108  else {
5109  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress) == 0);
5110  ASSERT (VirtualAddress >= MM_SYSTEM_RANGE_START);
5111 
5112  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
5113  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
5114 
5115  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
5116 
5117  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VirtualAddress, TRUE);
5118  }
5119 
5120  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
5121 
5122  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
5123 
5124  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, 0);
5125 
5126  if (MI_PAGE_FRAME_INDEX_MUST_BE_CACHED (PageFrameIndex)) {
5127  CacheAttribute = MiCached;
5128  }
5129 
5130  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
5131 
5132  switch (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute) {
5133 
5134  case MiCached:
5135  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
5136 
5137  //
5138  // The caller asked for a noncached or writecombined
5139  // mapping, but the page is already mapped cached by
5140  // someone else. Override the caller's request in
5141  // order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
5142  //
5143 
5144  MiCacheOverride[0] += 1;
5145  CacheAttribute = MiCached;
5146  }
5147  break;
5148 
5149  case MiNonCached:
5150  if (CacheAttribute != MiNonCached) {
5151 
5152  //
5153  // The caller asked for a cached or writecombined
5154  // mapping, but the page is already mapped noncached
5155  // by someone else. Override the caller's request
5156  // in order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
5157  //
5158 
5159  MiCacheOverride[1] += 1;
5160  CacheAttribute = MiNonCached;
5161  }
5162  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5163  break;
5164 
5165  case MiWriteCombined:
5166  if (CacheAttribute != MiWriteCombined) {
5167 
5168  //
5169  // The caller asked for a cached or noncached
5170  // mapping, but the page is already mapped
5171  // writecombined by someone else. Override the
5172  // caller's request in order to keep the TB page
5173  // attribute coherent.
5174  //
5175 
5176  MiCacheOverride[2] += 1;
5177  CacheAttribute = MiWriteCombined;
5178  }
5179  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5180  break;
5181 
5182  case MiNotMapped:
5183 
5184  //
5185  // This better be for a page allocated with
5186  // MmAllocatePagesForMdl. Otherwise it might be a
5187  // page on the freelist which could subsequently be
5188  // given out with a different attribute !
5189  //
5190 
5191  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME) ||
5192  (Pfn1->PteAddress == (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR)(X64K | 0x1)));
5193 
5194  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5195 
5196  switch (CacheAttribute) {
5197 
5198  case MiCached:
5199  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
5200  break;
5201 
5202  case MiNonCached:
5203  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiNonCached;
5204  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5205  break;
5206 
5207  case MiWriteCombined:
5208  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiWriteCombined;
5209  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5210  break;
5211 
5212  default:
5213  ASSERT (FALSE);
5214  break;
5215  }
5216 
5217  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5218  break;
5219 
5220  default:
5221  ASSERT (FALSE);
5222  break;
5223  }
5224 
5225  switch (CacheAttribute) {
5226 
5227  case MiCached:
5228  break;
5229 
5230  case MiNonCached:
5231  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5232  break;
5233 
5234  case MiWriteCombined:
5235  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5236  break;
5237 
5238  default:
5239  ASSERT (FALSE);
5240  break;
5241  }
5242 
5243  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
5244 
5245  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
5246 
5247  return VirtualAddress;
5248 }
5249 
5250 PVOID
5251 MmMapLockedPages (
5252  __in PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
5253  __in KPROCESSOR_MODE AccessMode
5254  )
5255 
5256 /*++
5257 
5258 Routine Description:
5259 
5260  This function maps physical pages described by a memory descriptor
5261  list into the system virtual address space or the user portion of
5262  the virtual address space.
5263 
5264 Arguments:
5265 
5266  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
5267  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
5268 
5269 
5270  AccessMode - Supplies an indicator of where to map the pages;
5271  KernelMode indicates that the pages should be mapped in the
5272  system part of the address space, UserMode indicates the
5273  pages should be mapped in the user part of the address space.
5274 
5275 Return Value:
5276 
5277  Returns the base address where the pages are mapped. The base address
5278  has the same offset as the virtual address in the MDL.
5279 
5280  This routine will raise an exception if the processor mode is USER_MODE
5281  and quota limits or VM limits are exceeded.
5282 
5283 Environment:
5284 
5285  Kernel mode. DISPATCH_LEVEL or below if access mode is KernelMode,
5286  APC_LEVEL or below if access mode is UserMode.
5287 
5288 --*/
5289 
5290 {
5291  return MmMapLockedPagesSpecifyCache (MemoryDescriptorList,
5292  AccessMode,
5293  MmCached,
5294  NULL,
5295  TRUE,
5296  HighPagePriority);
5297 }
5298 
5299 VOID
5300 MiUnmapSinglePage (
5301  IN PVOID VirtualAddress
5302  )
5303 
5304 /*++
5305 
5306 Routine Description:
5307 
5308  This routine unmaps a single locked page which was previously mapped via
5309  an MiMapSinglePage call.
5310 
5311 Arguments:
5312 
5313  VirtualAddress - Supplies the virtual address used to map the page.
5314 
5315 Return Value:
5316 
5317  None.
5318 
5319 Environment:
5320 
5321  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL or below, base address is within system space.
5322  Since the process working set pushlock may be held by callers, this
5323  routine is nonpaged.
5324 
5325 --*/
5326 
5327 {
5328  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5329 
5330  PAGED_CODE ();
5331 
5332  ASSERT (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress) == 0);
5333  ASSERT (VirtualAddress >= MM_SYSTEM_RANGE_START);
5334 
5335  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
5336 
5337  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte, 1, SystemPteSpace);
5338  return;
5339 }
5340 
5341 __bcount(NumberOfBytes) PVOID
5342 MmAllocateMappingAddress (
5343  __in SIZE_T NumberOfBytes,
5344  __in ULONG PoolTag
5345  )
5346 
5347 /*++
5348 
5349 Routine Description:
5350 
5351  This function allocates a system PTE mapping of the requested length
5352  that can be used later to map arbitrary addresses.
5353 
5354 Arguments:
5355 
5356  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the maximum number of bytes the mapping can span.
5357 
5358  PoolTag - Supplies a pool tag to associate this mapping to the caller.
5359 
5360 Return Value:
5361 
5362  Returns a virtual address where to use for later mappings.
5363 
5364 Environment:
5365 
5366  Kernel mode. PASSIVE_LEVEL.
5367 
5368 --*/
5369 
5370 {
5371  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
5372  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5373  PVOID BaseVa;
5374  PVOID CallingAddress;
5375  PVOID CallersCaller;
5376  PFN_NUMBER MdlHack[(sizeof(MDL)/sizeof(PFN_NUMBER)) + 1];
5377  PMDL MemoryDescriptorList;
5378  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
5379 
5380  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () == PASSIVE_LEVEL);
5381 
5382  //
5383  // Make sure there are enough PTEs of the requested size.
5384  // Try to ensure available PTEs inline when we're rich.
5385  // Otherwise go the long way.
5386  //
5387 
5388  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (0, NumberOfBytes);
5389 
5390  if (NumberOfPages == 0) {
5391 
5392  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
5393 
5394  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5395  0x100,
5396  NumberOfPages,
5397  PoolTag,
5398  (ULONG_PTR) CallingAddress);
5399  }
5400 
5401  //
5402  // Callers must identify themselves.
5403  //
5404 
5405  if (PoolTag == 0) {
5406  return NULL;
5407  }
5408 
5409  //
5410  // Leave space to stash the length and tag.
5411  //
5412 
5413  NumberOfPages += 2;
5414 
5415  PointerPte = MiReserveSystemPtes ((ULONG)NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
5416 
5417  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
5418 
5419  //
5420  // Not enough system PTES are available.
5421  //
5422 
5423  return NULL;
5424  }
5425 
5426  //
5427  // Make sure the valid bit is always zero in the stash PTEs.
5428  //
5429 
5430  *(PULONG_PTR)PointerPte = (NumberOfPages << 1);
5431  PointerPte += 1;
5432 
5433  *(PULONG_PTR)PointerPte = (PoolTag & ~0x1);
5434  PointerPte += 1;
5435 
5436  //
5437  // Zero out the PTEs as they may have pointers and timestamps in them,
5438  // and we want to be able to assert they are all NULL on release.
5439  //
5440 
5441  MiZeroMemoryPte (PointerPte, NumberOfPages - 2);
5442 
5443  BaseVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
5444 
5445  if (MmTrackPtes & 0x1) {
5446 
5447  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
5448 
5449  MemoryDescriptorList = (PMDL) MdlHack;
5450 
5451  MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa = BaseVa;
5452  MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa = (PVOID)(ULONG_PTR)PoolTag;
5453  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset = 0;
5454  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount = (ULONG)((NumberOfPages - 2) * PAGE_SIZE);
5455 
5456  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
5457  *Page = 0;
5458 
5459  MiInsertPteTracker (MemoryDescriptorList,
5460  2,
5461  FALSE,
5462  MiCached,
5463  CallingAddress,
5464  CallersCaller);
5465  }
5466 
5467  return BaseVa;
5468 }
5469 
5470 VOID
5471 MmFreeMappingAddress (
5472  __in PVOID BaseAddress,
5473  __in ULONG PoolTag
5474  )
5475 
5476 /*++
5477 
5478 Routine Description:
5479 
5480  This routine unmaps a virtual address range previously reserved with
5481  MmAllocateMappingAddress.
5482 
5483 Arguments:
5484 
5485  BaseAddress - Supplies the base address previously reserved.
5486 
5487  PoolTag - Supplies the caller's identifying tag.
5488 
5489 Return Value:
5490 
5491  None.
5492 
5493 Environment:
5494 
5495  Kernel mode. PASSIVE_LEVEL.
5496 
5497 --*/
5498 
5499 {
5500  ULONG OriginalPoolTag;
5501  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
5502  PMMPTE PointerBase;
5503  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5504  PMMPTE LastPte;
5505 
5506  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () == PASSIVE_LEVEL);
5507  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (BaseAddress));
5508  ASSERT (BaseAddress > MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS);
5509 
5510  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
5511  PointerBase = PointerPte - 2;
5512 
5513  OriginalPoolTag = *(PULONG) (PointerPte - 1);
5514  ASSERT ((OriginalPoolTag & 0x1) == 0);
5515 
5516  if (OriginalPoolTag != (PoolTag & ~0x1)) {
5517  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5518  0x101,
5519  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
5520  PoolTag,
5521  OriginalPoolTag);
5522  }
5523 
5524  NumberOfPages = *(PULONG_PTR)PointerBase;
5525  ASSERT ((NumberOfPages & 0x1) == 0);
5526  NumberOfPages >>= 1;
5527 
5528  if (NumberOfPages <= 2) {
5529  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5530  0x102,
5531  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
5532  PoolTag,
5533  NumberOfPages);
5534  }
5535 
5536  NumberOfPages -= 2;
5537  LastPte = PointerPte + NumberOfPages;
5538 
5539  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
5540  if (PointerPte->u.Long != 0) {
5541  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5542  0x103,
5543  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
5544  PoolTag,
5545  NumberOfPages);
5546  }
5547  PointerPte += 1;
5548  }
5549 
5550  if (MmTrackPtes & 0x1) {
5551  MiRemovePteTracker (NULL, BaseAddress, NumberOfPages);
5552  }
5553 
5554  //
5555  // Note the tag and size are nulled out when the PTEs are released below
5556  // so any drivers that try to use their mapping after freeing it get
5557  // caught immediately.
5558  //
5559 
5560  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerBase, (ULONG)NumberOfPages + 2, SystemPteSpace);
5561  return;
5562 }
5563 
5564 PVOID
5565 MmMapLockedPagesWithReservedMapping (
5566  __in PVOID MappingAddress,
5567  __in ULONG PoolTag,
5568  __in PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
5569  __in MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType
5570  )
5571 
5572 /*++
5573 
5574 Routine Description:
5575 
5576  This function maps physical pages described by a memory descriptor
5577  list into the system virtual address space.
5578 
5579 Arguments:
5580 
5581  MappingAddress - Supplies a valid mapping address obtained earlier via
5582  MmAllocateMappingAddress.
5583 
5584  PoolTag - Supplies the caller's identifying tag.
5585 
5586  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
5587  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
5588 
5589  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping to use for the MDL.
5590  MmCached indicates "normal" kernel or user mappings.
5591 
5592 Return Value:
5593 
5594  Returns the base address where the pages are mapped. The base address
5595  has the same offset as the virtual address in the MDL.
5596 
5597  This routine will return NULL if the cache type requested is incompatible
5598  with the pages being mapped or if the caller tries to map an MDL that is
5599  larger than the virtual address range originally reserved.
5600 
5601 Environment:
5602 
5603  Kernel mode. DISPATCH_LEVEL or below. The caller must synchronize usage
5604  of the argument virtual address space.
5605 
5606 --*/
5607 
5608 {
5609  KIRQL OldIrql;
5610  CSHORT IoMapping;
5611  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
5612  PFN_NUMBER VaPageSpan;
5613  PFN_NUMBER SavedPageCount;
5614  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
5615  PMMPTE PointerBase;
5616  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5617  PMMPTE LastPte;
5618  MMPTE TempPte;
5619  PVOID StartingVa;
5620  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPtes;
5621  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
5622  ULONG OriginalPoolTag;
5623  PMMPFN Pfn2;
5624  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
5625 
5626  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
5627 
5628  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
5629  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
5630 
5631  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
5632  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) == 0);
5633 
5634  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
5635  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
5636  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
5637 
5638  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (MappingAddress);
5639  PointerBase = PointerPte - 2;
5640 
5641  OriginalPoolTag = *(PULONG) (PointerPte - 1);
5642  ASSERT ((OriginalPoolTag & 0x1) == 0);
5643 
5644  if (OriginalPoolTag != (PoolTag & ~0x1)) {
5645  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5646  0x104,
5647  (ULONG_PTR)MappingAddress,
5648  PoolTag,
5649  OriginalPoolTag);
5650  }
5651 
5652  VaPageSpan = *(PULONG_PTR)PointerBase;
5653  ASSERT ((VaPageSpan & 0x1) == 0);
5654  VaPageSpan >>= 1;
5655 
5656  if (VaPageSpan <= 2) {
5657  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5658  0x105,
5659  (ULONG_PTR)MappingAddress,
5660  PoolTag,
5661  VaPageSpan);
5662  }
5663 
5664  if (NumberOfPages > VaPageSpan - 2) {
5665 
5666  //
5667  // The caller is trying to map an MDL that spans a range larger than
5668  // the reserving mapping ! This is a driver bug.
5669  //
5670 
5671  ASSERT (FALSE);
5672  return NULL;
5673  }
5674 
5675  //
5676  // All the mapping PTEs must be zero.
5677  //
5678 
5679  LastPte = PointerPte + VaPageSpan - 2;
5680 
5681  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
5682 
5683  if (PointerPte->u.Long != 0) {
5684  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5685  0x107,
5686  (ULONG_PTR)MappingAddress,
5687  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
5688  (ULONG_PTR)LastPte);
5689  }
5690 
5691  PointerPte += 1;
5692  }
5693 
5694  PointerPte = PointerBase + 2;
5695  SavedPageCount = NumberOfPages;
5696 
5697  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (
5698  MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA |
5699  MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL |
5700  MDL_PARTIAL_HAS_BEEN_MAPPED)) == 0);
5701 
5702  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (
5703  MDL_PAGES_LOCKED |
5704  MDL_PARTIAL)) != 0);
5705 
5706  //
5707  // If a noncachable mapping is requested, none of the pages in the
5708  // requested MDL can reside in a large page. Otherwise we would be
5709  // creating an incoherent overlapping TB entry as the same physical
5710  // page would be mapped by 2 different TB entries with different
5711  // cache attributes.
5712  //
5713 
5714  IoMapping = MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE;
5715 
5716  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, IoMapping);
5717 
5718  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
5719 
5720  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5721 
5722  do {
5723 
5724 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
5725  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
5726  break;
5727  }
5728 
5729  PageFrameIndex = *Page;
5730 
5731  if (MI_PAGE_FRAME_INDEX_MUST_BE_CACHED (PageFrameIndex)) {
5732  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5733  MiNonCachedCollisions += 1;
5734  return NULL;
5735  }
5736 
5737  Page += 1;
5738  NumberOfPages -= 1;
5739  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
5740 
5741  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5742 
5743  NumberOfPages = SavedPageCount;
5744  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
5745 
5746  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
5747  }
5748 
5749  NumberOfPtes = NumberOfPages;
5750 
5751  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
5752 
5753  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
5754 
5755  switch (CacheAttribute) {
5756 
5757  case MiNonCached:
5758  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5759  break;
5760 
5761  case MiCached:
5762  break;
5763 
5764  case MiWriteCombined:
5765  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5766  break;
5767 
5768  default:
5769  ASSERT (FALSE);
5770  break;
5771  }
5772 
5773  OldIrql = HIGH_LEVEL;
5774 
5775  do {
5776 
5777  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
5778  break;
5779  }
5780 
5781  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
5782 
5783  if ((IoMapping == 0) || (MI_IS_PFN (*Page))) {
5784 
5785  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
5786  ASSERT (Pfn2->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
5787  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
5788 
5789  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
5790 
5791  switch (Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute) {
5792 
5793  case MiCached:
5794  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
5795 
5796  //
5797  // The caller asked for a noncached or writecombined
5798  // mapping, but the page is already mapped cached by
5799  // someone else. Override the caller's request in
5800  // order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
5801  //
5802 
5803  MiCacheOverride[0] += 1;
5804  }
5805  break;
5806 
5807  case MiNonCached:
5808  if (CacheAttribute != MiNonCached) {
5809 
5810  //
5811  // The caller asked for a cached or writecombined
5812  // mapping, but the page is already mapped noncached
5813  // by someone else. Override the caller's request
5814  // in order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
5815  //
5816 
5817  MiCacheOverride[1] += 1;
5818  }
5819  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5820  break;
5821 
5822  case MiWriteCombined:
5823  if (CacheAttribute != MiWriteCombined) {
5824 
5825  //
5826  // The caller asked for a cached or noncached
5827  // mapping, but the page is already mapped
5828  // writecombined by someone else. Override the
5829  // caller's request in order to keep the TB page
5830  // attribute coherent.
5831  //
5832 
5833  MiCacheOverride[2] += 1;
5834  }
5835  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5836  break;
5837 
5838  case MiNotMapped:
5839 
5840  //
5841  // This better be for a page allocated with
5842  // MmAllocatePagesForMdl. Otherwise it might be a
5843  // page on the freelist which could subsequently be
5844  // given out with a different attribute !
5845  //
5846 
5847  ASSERT ((Pfn2->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME) ||
5848  (Pfn2->PteAddress == (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR)(X64K | 0x1)));
5849  if (OldIrql == HIGH_LEVEL) {
5850  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5851  }
5852 
5853  switch (CacheAttribute) {
5854 
5855  case MiCached:
5856  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
5857  break;
5858 
5859  case MiNonCached:
5860  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiNonCached;
5861  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
5862  break;
5863 
5864  case MiWriteCombined:
5865  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiWriteCombined;
5866  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
5867  break;
5868 
5869  default:
5870  ASSERT (FALSE);
5871  break;
5872  }
5873  break;
5874 
5875  default:
5876  ASSERT (FALSE);
5877  break;
5878  }
5879  }
5880 
5881  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = *Page;
5882  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
5883  Page += 1;
5884  PointerPte += 1;
5885  NumberOfPages -= 1;
5886  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
5887 
5888  if (OldIrql != HIGH_LEVEL) {
5889  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
5890  }
5891 
5892  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) == 0);
5893  MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa = MappingAddress;
5894 
5895  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA;
5896 
5897  if ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL) != 0) {
5898  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags |= MDL_PARTIAL_HAS_BEEN_MAPPED;
5899  }
5900 
5901  MappingAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MappingAddress + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
5902 
5903  return MappingAddress;
5904 }
5905 
5906 VOID
5907 MmUnmapReservedMapping (
5908  IN PVOID BaseAddress,
5909  IN ULONG PoolTag,
5910  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
5911  )
5912 
5913 /*++
5914 
5915 Routine Description:
5916 
5917  This routine unmaps locked pages which were previously mapped via
5918  a MmMapLockedPagesWithReservedMapping call.
5919 
5920 Arguments:
5921 
5922  BaseAddress - Supplies the base address where the pages were previously
5923  mapped.
5924 
5925  PoolTag - Supplies the caller's identifying tag.
5926 
5927  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
5928  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
5929 
5930 Return Value:
5931 
5932  None.
5933 
5934 Environment:
5935 
5936  Kernel mode. DISPATCH_LEVEL or below. The caller must synchronize usage
5937  of the argument virtual address space.
5938 
5939 --*/
5940 
5941 {
5942  ULONG OriginalPoolTag;
5943  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
5944  PFN_NUMBER ExtraPages;
5945  PFN_NUMBER VaPageSpan;
5946  PMMPTE PointerBase;
5947  PMMPTE LastPte;
5948  PMMPTE LastMdlPte;
5949  PVOID StartingVa;
5950  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
5951  PMMPTE PointerPte;
5952  PFN_NUMBER i;
5953  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
5954  PPFN_NUMBER LastCurrentPage;
5955 
5956  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
5957  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
5958  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) != 0);
5959 
5960  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PARENT_MAPPED_SYSTEM_VA) == 0);
5961  ASSERT (!MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (BaseAddress));
5962  ASSERT (BaseAddress > MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS);
5963 
5964  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
5965  PointerBase = PointerPte - 2;
5966 
5967  OriginalPoolTag = *(PULONG) (PointerPte - 1);
5968  ASSERT ((OriginalPoolTag & 0x1) == 0);
5969 
5970  if (OriginalPoolTag != (PoolTag & ~0x1)) {
5971  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5972  0x108,
5973  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
5974  PoolTag,
5975  OriginalPoolTag);
5976  }
5977 
5978  VaPageSpan = *(PULONG_PTR)PointerBase;
5979  ASSERT ((VaPageSpan & 0x1) == 0);
5980  VaPageSpan >>= 1;
5981 
5982  if (VaPageSpan <= 2) {
5983  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5984  0x109,
5985  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
5986  PoolTag,
5987  VaPageSpan);
5988  }
5989 
5990  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
5991  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
5992 
5993  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
5994  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
5995 
5996  if (NumberOfPages > VaPageSpan - 2) {
5997  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
5998  0x10A,
5999  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
6000  VaPageSpan,
6001  NumberOfPages);
6002  }
6003 
6004  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
6005  LastCurrentPage = Page + NumberOfPages;
6006 
6007  if (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_FREE_EXTRA_PTES) {
6008 
6009  ExtraPages = *(Page + NumberOfPages);
6010  ASSERT (ExtraPages <= MiCurrentAdvancedPages);
6011  ASSERT (NumberOfPages + ExtraPages <= VaPageSpan - 2);
6012  NumberOfPages += ExtraPages;
6013 #if DBG
6014  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MiCurrentAdvancedPages, 0 - ExtraPages);
6015  MiAdvancesFreed += ExtraPages;
6016 #endif
6017  }
6018 
6019  LastMdlPte = PointerPte + NumberOfPages;
6020  LastPte = PointerPte + VaPageSpan - 2;
6021 
6022  //
6023  // The range described by the argument MDL must be mapped.
6024  //
6025 
6026  while (PointerPte < LastMdlPte) {
6027  if (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0) {
6028  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
6029  0x10B,
6030  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
6031  PoolTag,
6032  NumberOfPages);
6033  }
6034 
6035 #if DBG
6036  ASSERT ((*Page == MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte)) ||
6037  (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_FREE_EXTRA_PTES));
6038 
6039  if ((MI_IS_PFN (*Page)) && (Page < LastCurrentPage)) {
6040  PMMPFN Pfn3;
6041  Pfn3 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
6042  ASSERT (Pfn3->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
6043  }
6044 
6045  Page += 1;
6046 #endif
6047 
6048  PointerPte += 1;
6049  }
6050 
6051  //
6052  // The range past the argument MDL must be unmapped.
6053  //
6054 
6055  while (PointerPte < LastPte) {
6056  if (PointerPte->u.Long != 0) {
6057  KeBugCheckEx (SYSTEM_PTE_MISUSE,
6058  0x10C,
6059  (ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress,
6060  PoolTag,
6061  NumberOfPages);
6062  }
6063  PointerPte += 1;
6064  }
6065 
6066  MiZeroMemoryPte (PointerBase + 2, NumberOfPages);
6067 
6068  if (NumberOfPages == 1) {
6069  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (BaseAddress, TRUE);
6070  }
6071  else if (NumberOfPages < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6072 
6073  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
6074  VaFlushList[i] = BaseAddress;
6075  BaseAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseAddress + PAGE_SIZE);
6076  }
6077 
6078  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB ((ULONG)NumberOfPages, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6079  }
6080  else {
6081  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (2);
6082  }
6083 
6084  MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags &= ~(MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA |
6085  MDL_PARTIAL_HAS_BEEN_MAPPED);
6086 
6087  return;
6088 }
6089 
6090 NTKERNELAPI
6091 NTSTATUS
6092 MmAdvanceMdl (
6093  __inout PMDL Mdl,
6094  __in ULONG NumberOfBytes
6095  )
6096 
6097 /*++
6098 
6099 Routine Description:
6100 
6101  This routine takes the specified MDL and "advances" it forward
6102  by the specified number of bytes. If this causes the MDL to advance
6103  past the initial page, the pages that are advanced over are immediately
6104  unlocked and the system VA that maps the MDL is also adjusted (along
6105  with the user address).
6106 
6107  WARNING ! WARNING ! WARNING !
6108 
6109  This means the caller MUST BE AWARE that the "advanced" pages are
6110  immediately reused and therefore MUST NOT BE REFERENCED by the caller
6111  once this routine has been called. Likewise the virtual address as
6112  that is also being adjusted here.
6113 
6114  Even if the caller has statically allocated this MDL on his local stack,
6115  he cannot use more than the space currently described by the MDL on return
6116  from this routine unless he first unmaps the MDL (if it was mapped).
6117  Otherwise the system PTE lists will be corrupted.
6118 
6119 Arguments:
6120 
6121  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
6122  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
6123 
6124  NumberOfBytes - The number of bytes to advance the MDL by.
6125 
6126 Return Value:
6127 
6128  NTSTATUS.
6129 
6130 --*/
6131 
6132 {
6133  ULONG i;
6134  ULONG PageCount;
6135  LONG EntryCount;
6136  LONG OriginalCount;
6137  ULONG FreeBit;
6138  ULONG Slush;
6139  KIRQL OldIrql;
6140  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
6141  PPFN_NUMBER NewPage;
6142  ULONG OffsetPages;
6143  PEPROCESS Process;
6144  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6145  CSHORT MdlFlags;
6146  PVOID StartingVa;
6147  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
6148  PPFN_NUMBER LastPage;
6149 
6150  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
6151  ASSERT (Mdl->MdlFlags & (MDL_PAGES_LOCKED | MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL));
6152  ASSERT (BYTE_OFFSET (Mdl->StartVa) == 0);
6153 
6154  //
6155  // Disallow advancement past the end of the MDL.
6156  //
6157 
6158  if (NumberOfBytes >= Mdl->ByteCount) {
6159  return STATUS_INVALID_PARAMETER_2;
6160  }
6161 
6162  PageCount = 0;
6163 
6164  MiMdlsAdjusted = TRUE;
6165 
6166  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)Mdl->StartVa + Mdl->ByteOffset);
6167 
6168  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES(StartingVa, Mdl->ByteCount);
6169 
6170  if (Mdl->ByteOffset != 0) {
6171  Slush = PAGE_SIZE - Mdl->ByteOffset;
6172 
6173  if (NumberOfBytes < Slush) {
6174 
6175  Mdl->ByteCount -= NumberOfBytes;
6176  Mdl->ByteOffset += NumberOfBytes;
6177 
6178  //
6179  // StartVa never includes the byte offset (it's always page-aligned)
6180  // so don't adjust it here. MappedSystemVa does include byte
6181  // offsets so do adjust that.
6182  //
6183 
6184  if (Mdl->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
6185  Mdl->MappedSystemVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)Mdl->MappedSystemVa + NumberOfBytes);
6186  }
6187 
6188  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
6189  }
6190 
6191  NumberOfBytes -= Slush;
6192 
6193  Mdl->StartVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)Mdl->StartVa + PAGE_SIZE);
6194  Mdl->ByteOffset = 0;
6195  Mdl->ByteCount -= Slush;
6196
