6197  if (Mdl->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
6198  Mdl->MappedSystemVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)Mdl->MappedSystemVa + Slush);
6199  }
6200 
6201  //
6202  // Up the number of pages (and addresses) that need to slide.
6203  //
6204 
6205  PageCount += 1;
6206  }
6207 
6208  //
6209  // The MDL start is now nicely page aligned. Make sure there's still
6210  // data left in it (we may have finished it off above), then operate on it.
6211  //
6212 
6213  if (NumberOfBytes != 0) {
6214 
6215  Mdl->ByteCount -= NumberOfBytes;
6216 
6217  Mdl->ByteOffset = BYTE_OFFSET (NumberOfBytes);
6218 
6219  OffsetPages = NumberOfBytes >> PAGE_SHIFT;
6220 
6221  Mdl->StartVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)Mdl->StartVa + (OffsetPages << PAGE_SHIFT));
6222  PageCount += OffsetPages;
6223 
6224  if (Mdl->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
6225 
6226  Mdl->MappedSystemVa = (PVOID) ((PCHAR)Mdl->MappedSystemVa +
6227  (OffsetPages << PAGE_SHIFT) +
6228  Mdl->ByteOffset);
6229  }
6230  }
6231 
6232  ASSERT (PageCount <= NumberOfPages);
6233 
6234  if (PageCount != 0) {
6235 
6236  //
6237  // Slide the page frame numbers forward decrementing reference counts
6238  // on the ones that are released. Then adjust the mapped system VA
6239  // (if there is one) to reflect the current frame. Note that the TB
6240  // does not need to be flushed due to the careful sliding and when
6241  // the MDL is finally completely unmapped, the extra information
6242  // added to the MDL here is used to free the entire original PTE
6243  // mapping range in one chunk so as not to fragment the PTE space.
6244  //
6245 
6246  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(Mdl + 1);
6247  NewPage = Page;
6248 
6249  Process = Mdl->Process;
6250 
6251  MdlFlags = Mdl->MdlFlags;
6252 
6253  if (MdlFlags & MDL_DESCRIBES_AWE) {
6254 
6255  ASSERT (Process != NULL);
6256  ASSERT (Process->AweInfo != NULL);
6257 
6258  LastPage = Page + PageCount;
6259 
6260  //
6261  // Note neither AWE nor PFN locks are needed for unlocking these
6262  // MDLs in all but the very rare cases (see below).
6263  //
6264 
6265  do {
6266 
6267 #pragma prefast(suppress: 2000, "SAL 1.2 needed for accurate MDL struct annotation.")
6268  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
6269 
6270  //
6271  // There are no more locked pages - if there were none
6272  // at all then we're done.
6273  //
6274 
6275  break;
6276  }
6277 
6278  ASSERT (MI_IS_PFN (*Page));
6279  ASSERT (*Page <= MmHighestPhysicalPage);
6280  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
6281 
6282  do {
6283  EntryCount = ReadForWriteAccess (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount);
6284 
6285  ASSERT ((LONG)EntryCount > 0);
6286  ASSERT (Pfn1->u4.AweAllocation == 1);
6287  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
6288 
6289  OriginalCount = InterlockedCompareExchange (&Pfn1->AweReferenceCount,
6290  EntryCount - 1,
6291  EntryCount);
6292 
6293  if (OriginalCount == EntryCount) {
6294 
6295  //
6296  // This thread can be racing against other threads also
6297  // calling MmUnlockPages and also a thread calling
6298  // NtFreeUserPhysicalPages. All threads can safely do
6299  // interlocked decrements on the "AWE reference count".
6300  // Whichever thread drives it to zero is responsible for
6301  // decrementing the actual PFN reference count (which
6302  // may be greater than 1 due to other non-AWE API calls
6303  // being used on the same page). The thread that
6304  // drives this reference count to zero must put the
6305  // page on the actual freelist at that time and
6306  // decrement various resident available and commitment
6307  // counters also.
6308  //
6309 
6310  if (OriginalCount == 1) {
6311 
6312  //
6313  // This thread has driven the AWE reference count to
6314  // zero so it must initiate a decrement of the PFN
6315  // reference count (while holding the PFN lock),
6316  // etc.
6317  //
6318  // This path should be rare since typically I/Os
6319  // complete before these types of pages are freed by
6320  // the app.
6321  //
6322 
6323  MiDecrementReferenceCountForAwePage (Pfn1, FALSE);
6324  }
6325 
6326  break;
6327  }
6328  } while (TRUE);
6329 
6330  Page += 1;
6331  } while (Page < LastPage);
6332 
6333  i = (ULONG) (Page - (PPFN_NUMBER)(Mdl + 1));
6334  }
6335  else {
6336 
6337  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
6338 
6339  for (i = 0; i < PageCount; i += 1) {
6340 
6341  //
6342  // Decrement the stale page frames now, this will unlock them
6343  // resulting in them being immediately reused if necessary.
6344  //
6345 
6346  if ((MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED) &&
6347  ((MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0)) {
6348 
6349  ASSERT ((MdlFlags & MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL) == 0);
6350 
6351  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
6352 
6353  if (MdlFlags & MDL_WRITE_OPERATION) {
6354 
6355  //
6356  // If this was a write operation set the modified bit
6357  // in the PFN database.
6358  //
6359 
6360  MI_SET_MODIFIED (Pfn1, 1, 0x3);
6361 
6362  if ((Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.Prototype == 0) &&
6363  (Pfn1->u3.e1.WriteInProgress == 0)) {
6364 
6365  FreeBit = GET_PAGING_FILE_OFFSET (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6366 
6367  if ((FreeBit != 0) && (FreeBit != MI_PTE_LOOKUP_NEEDED)) {
6368  MiReleaseConfirmedPageFileSpace (Pfn1->OriginalPte);
6369  Pfn1->OriginalPte.u.Soft.PageFileHigh = 0;
6370  }
6371  }
6372  }
6373  MI_REMOVE_LOCKED_PAGE_CHARGE_AND_DECREF (Pfn1);
6374  }
6375  Page += 1;
6376  }
6377 
6378  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
6379 
6380  if (Process != NULL) {
6381 
6382  if ((MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED) &&
6383  ((MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE) == 0)) {
6384 
6385  ASSERT ((MdlFlags & MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL) == 0);
6386  ASSERT ((SPFN_NUMBER)Process->NumberOfLockedPages >= 0);
6387 
6388  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&Process->NumberOfLockedPages,
6389  0 - (PFN_NUMBER) PageCount);
6390  }
6391 
6392  if (MmTrackLockedPages == TRUE) {
6393  MiUpdateMdlTracker (Mdl, PageCount);
6394  }
6395  }
6396  }
6397 
6398  //
6399  // Now ripple the remaining pages to the front of the MDL, effectively
6400  // purging the old ones which have just been released.
6401  //
6402 
6403  ASSERT (i < NumberOfPages);
6404 
6405  for ( ; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
6406 
6407  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
6408  break;
6409  }
6410 
6411  *NewPage = *Page;
6412  NewPage += 1;
6413  Page += 1;
6414  }
6415 
6416  //
6417  // If the MDL has been mapped, stash the number of pages advanced
6418  // at the end of the frame list inside the MDL and mark the MDL as
6419  // containing extra PTEs to free. Thus when the MDL is finally
6420  // completely unmapped, this can be used so the entire original PTE
6421  // mapping range can be freed in one chunk so as not to fragment the
6422  // PTE space.
6423  //
6424 
6425  if (MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) {
6426 
6427 #if DBG
6428  InterlockedExchangeAddSizeT (&MiCurrentAdvancedPages, PageCount);
6429  MiAdvancesGiven += PageCount;
6430 #endif
6431 
6432  if (MdlFlags & MDL_FREE_EXTRA_PTES) {
6433 
6434  //
6435  // This MDL has already been advanced at least once. Any
6436  // PTEs from those advancements need to be preserved now.
6437  //
6438 
6439  ASSERT (*Page <= MiCurrentAdvancedPages - PageCount);
6440  PageCount += *(PULONG)Page;
6441  }
6442  else {
6443  Mdl->MdlFlags |= MDL_FREE_EXTRA_PTES;
6444  }
6445 
6446  *NewPage = PageCount;
6447  }
6448  }
6449 
6450  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
6451 }
6452 
6453 NTKERNELAPI
6454 NTSTATUS
6455 MmProtectMdlSystemAddress (
6456  __in PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
6457  __in ULONG NewProtect
6458  )
6459 
6460 /*++
6461 
6462 Routine Description:
6463 
6464  This function protects the system address range specified
6465  by the argument Memory Descriptor List.
6466 
6467  Note the caller must make this MDL mapping readwrite before finally
6468  freeing (or reusing) it.
6469 
6470 Arguments:
6471 
6472  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies the MDL describing the virtual range.
6473 
6474  NewProtect - Supplies the protection to set the pages to (PAGE_XX).
6475 
6476 Return Value:
6477 
6478  NTSTATUS.
6479 
6480 Environment:
6481 
6482  Kernel mode, IRQL DISPATCH_LEVEL or below. The caller is responsible for
6483  synchronizing access to this routine.
6484 
6485 --*/
6486 
6487 {
6488  KIRQL OldIrql;
6489  PVOID BaseAddress;
6490  PVOID SystemVa;
6491  MMPTE PteContents;
6492  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6493  ULONG ProtectionMask;
6494 #if DBG
6495  PMMPFN Pfn1;
6496  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
6497 #endif
6498  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
6499  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
6500  ULONG FlushCount;
6501  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
6502  MMPTE OriginalPte;
6503  LOGICAL WasValid;
6504  PMM_PTE_MAPPING Map;
6505  PMM_PTE_MAPPING MapEntry;
6506  PMM_PTE_MAPPING FoundMap;
6507  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
6508 
6509  ASSERT (KeGetCurrentIrql () <= DISPATCH_LEVEL);
6510  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PAGES_LOCKED) != 0);
6511  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL) == 0);
6512  ASSERT ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_PARTIAL) == 0);
6513  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount != 0);
6514 
6515  if ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA) == 0) {
6516  return STATUS_NOT_MAPPED_VIEW;
6517  }
6518 
6519  BaseAddress = MemoryDescriptorList->MappedSystemVa;
6520 
6521  ASSERT (BaseAddress > MM_HIGHEST_USER_ADDRESS);
6522 
6523  //
6524  // On some architectures, we may use a large or KSEG-based MDL mapping
6525  // which must always be READWRITE, so disallow any changes to these.
6526  //
6527 
6528  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (BaseAddress)) {
6529  return STATUS_NOT_SUPPORTED;
6530  }
6531 
6532  ProtectionMask = MiMakeProtectionMask (NewProtect);
6533 
6534  //
6535  // No bogus or copy-on-write protections allowed for these.
6536  //
6537 
6538  if ((ProtectionMask == MM_INVALID_PROTECTION) ||
6539  (MI_IS_GUARD (ProtectionMask)) ||
6540  (MI_IS_NOCACHE (ProtectionMask)) ||
6541  (MI_IS_WRITECOMBINE (ProtectionMask)) ||
6542  (ProtectionMask == MM_WRITECOPY) ||
6543  (ProtectionMask == MM_EXECUTE_WRITECOPY)) {
6544 
6545  return STATUS_INVALID_PAGE_PROTECTION;
6546  }
6547 
6548  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
6549 
6550  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (BaseAddress,
6551  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
6552 
6553  SystemVa = PAGE_ALIGN (BaseAddress);
6554 
6555  //
6556  // Initializing Map is not needed for correctness
6557  // but without it the compiler cannot compile this code
6558  // W4 to check for use of uninitialized variables.
6559  //
6560 
6561  Map = NULL;
6562 
6563  if (ProtectionMask != MM_READWRITE) {
6564 
6565  Map = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
6566  sizeof(MM_PTE_MAPPING),
6567  'mPmM');
6568 
6569  if (Map == NULL) {
6570  return STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
6571  }
6572 
6573  Map->SystemVa = SystemVa;
6574  Map->SystemEndVa = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)SystemVa + (NumberOfPages << PAGE_SHIFT));
6575  Map->Protection = ProtectionMask;
6576  }
6577 
6578 #if DBG
6579  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
6580 #endif
6581 
6582  FlushCount = 0;
6583 
6584  while (NumberOfPages != 0) {
6585 
6586  PteContents = *PointerPte;
6587 
6588  if (PteContents.u.Hard.Valid == 1) {
6589  WasValid = TRUE;
6590  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (&PteContents);
6591  OriginalPte = PteContents;
6592  }
6593  else if ((PteContents.u.Soft.Transition == 1) &&
6594  (PteContents.u.Soft.Protection == MM_NOACCESS)) {
6595  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_TRANSITION_PTE (&PteContents);
6596  WasValid = FALSE;
6597 
6598  OriginalPte.u.Hard.WriteThrough = PteContents.u.Soft.PageFileLow;
6599  OriginalPte.u.Hard.CacheDisable = (PteContents.u.Soft.PageFileLow >> 1);
6600 
6601  }
6602  else {
6603  KeBugCheckEx (MEMORY_MANAGEMENT,
6604  0x1235,
6605  (ULONG_PTR)MemoryDescriptorList,
6606  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte,
6607  (ULONG_PTR)PteContents.u.Long);
6608  }
6609 
6610 #if DBG
6611  ASSERT (*Page == PageFrameIndex);
6612 
6613  if (MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
6614  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
6615  ASSERT (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
6616  }
6617 
6618  Page += 1;
6619 #endif
6620 
6621  if (ProtectionMask == MM_NOACCESS) {
6622 
6623  //
6624  // To generate a bugcheck on bogus access: Prototype must stay
6625  // clear, transition must stay set, protection must stay NO_ACCESS.
6626  //
6627 
6628  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE_TRANSITION (PteContents, MM_NOACCESS);
6629 
6630  //
6631  // Stash the cache attributes into the software PTE so they can
6632  // be restored later.
6633  //
6634 
6635  PteContents.u.Soft.PageFileLow = OriginalPte.u.Hard.WriteThrough;
6636  PteContents.u.Soft.PageFileLow |= (OriginalPte.u.Hard.CacheDisable << 1);
6637 
6638  MI_WRITE_INVALID_PTE (PointerPte, PteContents);
6639  }
6640  else {
6641  MI_MAKE_VALID_KERNEL_PTE (PteContents,
6642  PageFrameIndex,
6643  ProtectionMask,
6644  PointerPte);
6645 
6646  if (ProtectionMask & MM_READWRITE) {
6647  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (PteContents);
6648  }
6649 
6650  //
6651  // Extract cache type from the original PTE so it can be preserved.
6652  // Note that since we only allow protection changes (not caching
6653  // attribute changes), there is no need to flush or sweep TBs on
6654  // insertion below.
6655  //
6656 
6657  PteContents.u.Hard.WriteThrough = OriginalPte.u.Hard.WriteThrough;
6658  PteContents.u.Hard.CacheDisable = OriginalPte.u.Hard.CacheDisable;
6659 
6660  if (WasValid == TRUE) {
6661  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE_NEW_PROTECTION (PointerPte, PteContents);
6662  }
6663  else {
6664  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, PteContents);
6665  }
6666  }
6667 
6668  if ((WasValid == TRUE) && (FlushCount != MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT)) {
6669  VaFlushList[FlushCount] = BaseAddress;
6670  FlushCount += 1;
6671  }
6672 
6673  BaseAddress = (PVOID)((ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress + PAGE_SIZE);
6674  PointerPte += 1;
6675  NumberOfPages -= 1;
6676  }
6677 
6678  //
6679  // Flush the TB entries for any relevant pages.
6680  //
6681 
6682  if (FlushCount == 0) {
6683  NOTHING;
6684  }
6685  else if (FlushCount == 1) {
6686  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6687  }
6688  else if (FlushCount < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
6689  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB (FlushCount, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
6690  }
6691  else {
6692  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (0x12);
6693  }
6694 
6695  if (ProtectionMask != MM_READWRITE) {
6696 
6697  //
6698  // Insert (or update) the list entry describing this range.
6699  // Don't bother sorting the list as there will never be many entries.
6700  //
6701 
6702  FoundMap = NULL;
6703 
6704  OldIrql = KeAcquireSpinLockRaiseToSynch (&MmProtectedPteLock);
6705 
6706  NextEntry = MmProtectedPteList.Flink;
6707 
6708  while (NextEntry != &MmProtectedPteList) {
6709 
6710  MapEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
6711  MM_PTE_MAPPING,
6712  ListEntry);
6713 
6714  if (MapEntry->SystemVa == SystemVa) {
6715  ASSERT (MapEntry->SystemEndVa == Map->SystemEndVa);
6716  MapEntry->Protection = Map->Protection;
6717  FoundMap = MapEntry;
6718  break;
6719  }
6720  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
6721  }
6722 
6723  if (FoundMap == NULL) {
6724  InsertHeadList (&MmProtectedPteList, &Map->ListEntry);
6725  }
6726 
6727  KeReleaseSpinLock (&MmProtectedPteLock, OldIrql);
6728 
6729  if (FoundMap != NULL) {
6730  ExFreePool (Map);
6731  }
6732  }
6733  else {
6734 
6735  //
6736  // If there is an existing list entry describing this range, remove it.
6737  //
6738 
6739  if (!IsListEmpty (&MmProtectedPteList)) {
6740 
6741  FoundMap = NULL;
6742 
6743  OldIrql = KeAcquireSpinLockRaiseToSynch (&MmProtectedPteLock);
6744 
6745  NextEntry = MmProtectedPteList.Flink;
6746 
6747  while (NextEntry != &MmProtectedPteList) {
6748 
6749  MapEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
6750  MM_PTE_MAPPING,
6751  ListEntry);
6752 
6753  if (MapEntry->SystemVa == SystemVa) {
6754  RemoveEntryList (NextEntry);
6755  FoundMap = MapEntry;
6756  break;
6757  }
6758  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
6759  }
6760 
6761  KeReleaseSpinLock (&MmProtectedPteLock, OldIrql);
6762 
6763  if (FoundMap != NULL) {
6764  ExFreePool (FoundMap);
6765  }
6766  }
6767  }
6768 
6769  ASSERT (MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_MAPPED_TO_SYSTEM_VA);
6770 
6771  return STATUS_SUCCESS;
6772 }
6773 
6774 LOGICAL
6775 MiCheckSystemPteProtection (
6776  IN ULONG_PTR StoreInstruction,
6777  IN PVOID VirtualAddress
6778  )
6779 
6780 /*++
6781 
6782 Routine Description:
6783 
6784  This function determines whether the faulting virtual address lies
6785  within the non-writable alternate system PTE mappings.
6786 
6787 Arguments:
6788 
6789  StoreInstruction - Supplies nonzero if the operation causes a write into
6790  memory, zero if not.
6791 
6792  VirtualAddress - Supplies the virtual address which caused the fault.
6793 
6794 Return Value:
6795 
6796  TRUE if the fault was handled by this code (and PTE updated), FALSE if not.
6797 
6798 Environment:
6799 
6800  Kernel mode. Called from the fault handler at any IRQL.
6801 
6802 --*/
6803 
6804 {
6805  KIRQL OldIrql;
6806  PMMPTE PointerPte;
6807  ULONG ProtectionCode;
6808  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
6809  PMM_PTE_MAPPING MapEntry;
6810 
6811  //
6812  // If PTE mappings with various protections are active and the faulting
6813  // address lies within these mappings, resolve the fault with
6814  // the appropriate protections.
6815  //
6816 
6817  if (IsListEmpty (&MmProtectedPteList)) {
6818  return FALSE;
6819  }
6820 
6821  OldIrql = KeAcquireSpinLockRaiseToSynch (&MmProtectedPteLock);
6822 
6823  NextEntry = MmProtectedPteList.Flink;
6824 
6825  while (NextEntry != &MmProtectedPteList) {
6826 
6827  MapEntry = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry,
6828  MM_PTE_MAPPING,
6829  ListEntry);
6830 
6831  if ((VirtualAddress >= MapEntry->SystemVa) &&
6832  (VirtualAddress < MapEntry->SystemEndVa)) {
6833 
6834  ProtectionCode = MapEntry->Protection;
6835  KeReleaseSpinLock (&MmProtectedPteLock, OldIrql);
6836 
6837  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
6838 
6839  if (StoreInstruction != 0) {
6840  if ((ProtectionCode & MM_READWRITE) == 0) {
6841 
6842  KeBugCheckEx (ATTEMPTED_WRITE_TO_READONLY_MEMORY,
6843  (ULONG_PTR)VirtualAddress,
6844  (ULONG_PTR)PointerPte->u.Long,
6845  0,
6846  16);
6847  }
6848  }
6849 
6850  MI_NO_FAULT_FOUND (StoreInstruction,
6851  PointerPte,
6852  VirtualAddress,
6853  FALSE);
6854 
6855  //
6856  // Fault was handled directly here, no need for the caller to
6857  // do anything.
6858  //
6859 
6860  return TRUE;
6861  }
6862  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
6863  }
6864 
6865  KeReleaseSpinLock (&MmProtectedPteLock, OldIrql);
6866 
6867  return FALSE;
6868 }
6869 
6870 PVOID
6871 MiCreatePhysicalVadRoot (
6872  IN PEPROCESS Process,
6873  IN LOGICAL WsHeld
6874  )
6875 
6876 /*++
6877 
6878 Routine Description:
6879 
6880  This function creates a physical VAD AVL root table for the specified
6881  process.
6882 
6883 Arguments:
6884 
6885  Process - Supplies the process to add the physical VAD root to.
6886 
6887  WsHeld - Supplies TRUE if the caller holds the WS mutex, FALSE if not.
6888 
6889 Return Value:
6890 
6891  The PhysicalVadRoot or NULL.
6892 
6893 Environment:
6894 
6895  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL or below.
6896 
6897 --*/
6898 {
6899  PETHREAD Thread;
6900  PMM_AVL_TABLE PhysicalVadRoot;
6901 
6902  //
6903  // The address space mutex synchronizes the allocation of the
6904  // EPROCESS PhysicalVadRoot. This table root is not deleted until
6905  // the process exits.
6906  //
6907 
6908  if (Process->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) {
6909 
6910  PhysicalVadRoot = (PMM_AVL_TABLE) ExAllocatePoolWithTag (
6911  NonPagedPool,
6912  sizeof (MM_AVL_TABLE),
6913  MI_PHYSICAL_VIEW_ROOT_KEY);
6914 
6915  if (PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) {
6916  return NULL;
6917  }
6918 
6919  RtlZeroMemory (PhysicalVadRoot, sizeof (MM_AVL_TABLE));
6920  ASSERT (PhysicalVadRoot->NumberGenericTableElements == 0);
6921  PhysicalVadRoot->BalancedRoot.u1.Parent = &PhysicalVadRoot->BalancedRoot;
6922 
6923  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
6924 
6925  //
6926  // Synchronize with concurrent MmProbeAndLockPages callers by
6927  // acquiring the working set mutex.
6928  //
6929 
6930  if (WsHeld == FALSE) {
6931  LOCK_WS (Thread, Process);
6932  }
6933 
6934  if (Process->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) {
6935 
6936  Process->PhysicalVadRoot = PhysicalVadRoot;
6937 
6938  if (WsHeld == FALSE) {
6939  UNLOCK_WS (Thread, Process);
6940  }
6941  }
6942  else {
6943  if (WsHeld == FALSE) {
6944  UNLOCK_WS (Thread, Process);
6945  }
6946  ExFreePool (PhysicalVadRoot);
6947  }
6948  }
6949 
6950  return Process->PhysicalVadRoot;
6951 }
6952 
6953 VOID
6954 MiPhysicalViewRemover (
6955  IN PEPROCESS Process,
6956  IN PMMVAD Vad
6957  )
6958 
6959 /*++
6960 
6961 Routine Description:
6962 
6963  This function removes a physical VAD from the process chain.
6964 
6965 Arguments:
6966 
6967  Process - Supplies the process to remove the physical VAD from.
6968 
6969  Vad - Supplies the Vad to remove.
6970 
6971 Return Value:
6972 
6973  None.
6974 
6975 Environment:
6976 
6977  Kernel mode, APC_LEVEL, working set and address space mutexes held.
6978 
6979 --*/
6980 
6981 {
6982  PETHREAD Thread;
6983  PRTL_BITMAP BitMap;
6984  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
6985  ULONG BitMapSize;
6986  TABLE_SEARCH_RESULT SearchResult;
6987  PFN_NUMBER PagesRequired;
6988 
6989  //
6990  // Lookup the element and save the result.
6991  //
6992 
6993  ASSERT (Process->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL);
6994 
6995  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (Process->PhysicalVadRoot,
6996  Vad->StartingVpn,
6997  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
6998 
6999  ASSERT (SearchResult == TableFoundNode);
7000  ASSERT (PhysicalView->Vad == Vad);
7001 
7002  MiRemoveNode ((PMMADDRESS_NODE)PhysicalView, Process->PhysicalVadRoot);
7003 
7004  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadWriteWatch) {
7005  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
7006  UNLOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
7007  BitMap = PhysicalView->u.BitMap;
7008  BitMapSize = sizeof(RTL_BITMAP) + (ULONG)(((BitMap->SizeOfBitMap + 31) / 32) * 4);
7009  PsReturnProcessNonPagedPoolQuota (Process, BitMapSize);
7010  ExFreePool (BitMap);
7011  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
7012  }
7013 
7014  if (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType == VadRotatePhysical) {
7015  MiFreeInPageSupportBlock (PhysicalView->InPageSupport);
7016  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PhysicalView->u.MappingPte, 2, SystemPteSpace);
7017 
7018  PagesRequired = MiResidentPagesForSpan (MI_VPN_TO_VA (Vad->StartingVpn),
7019  MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn));
7020  MI_INCREMENT_RESIDENT_AVAILABLE (PagesRequired, MM_RESAVAIL_FREE_ROTATE_VAD);
7021  }
7022 
7023  ExFreePool (PhysicalView);
7024 
7025  return;
7026 }
7027 
7028 VOID
7029 MiPhysicalViewAdjuster (
7030  IN PEPROCESS Process,
7031  IN PMMVAD OldVad,
7032  IN PMMVAD NewVad
7033  )
7034 
7035 /*++
7036 
7037 Routine Description:
7038 
7039  This function re-points a physical VAD in the process chain.
7040 
7041 Arguments:
7042 
7043  Process - Supplies the process in which to adjust the physical VAD.
7044 
7045  Vad - Supplies the old Vad to replace.
7046 
7047  NewVad - Supplies the newVad to substitute.
7048 
7049 Return Value:
7050 
7051  None.
7052 
7053 Environment:
7054 
7055  Kernel mode, called with APCs disabled, working set mutex held.
7056 
7057 --*/
7058 {
7059  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
7060  TABLE_SEARCH_RESULT SearchResult;
7061 
7062  //
7063  // Lookup the element and save the result.
7064  //
7065 
7066  ASSERT (Process->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL);
7067 
7068  SearchResult = MiFindNodeOrParent (Process->PhysicalVadRoot,
7069  OldVad->StartingVpn,
7070  (PMMADDRESS_NODE *) &PhysicalView);
7071 
7072  ASSERT (SearchResult == TableFoundNode);
7073  ASSERT (PhysicalView->Vad == OldVad);
7074 
7075  PhysicalView->Vad = NewVad;
7076 
7077  return;
7078 }
7079 
7080 PVOID
7081 MiMapLockedPagesInUserSpace (
7082  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList,
7083  IN PVOID StartingVa,
7084  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType,
7085  IN PVOID BaseVa
7086  )
7087 
7088 /*++
7089 
7090 Routine Description:
7091 
7092  This function maps physical pages described by a memory descriptor
7093  list into the user portion of the virtual address space.
7094 
7095 Arguments:
7096 
7097  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
7098  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
7099 
7100 
7101  StartingVa - Supplies the starting address.
7102 
7103  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping to use for the MDL.
7104  MmCached indicates "normal" user mappings.
7105 
7106  BaseVa - Supplies the base address of the view. If the initial
7107  value of this argument is not null, then the view will
7108  be allocated starting at the specified virtual
7109  address rounded down to the next 64kb address
7110  boundary. If the initial value of this argument is
7111  null, then the operating system will determine
7112  where to allocate the view.
7113 
7114 Return Value:
7115 
7116  Returns the base address where the pages are mapped. The base address
7117  has the same offset as the virtual address in the MDL.
7118 
7119  This routine will raise an exception if quota limits or VM limits are
7120  exceeded.
7121 
7122 Environment:
7123 
7124  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL or below.
7125 
7126 --*/
7127 
7128 {
7129  KIRQL OldIrql;
7130  CSHORT IoMapping;
7131  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
7132  PFN_NUMBER SavedPageCount;
7133  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
7134  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
7135  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7136  PMMPTE PointerPde;
7137  PCHAR Va;
7138  MMPTE TempPte;
7139  PVOID EndingAddress;
7140  PMMVAD_LONG Vad;
7141  PETHREAD Thread;
7142  PEPROCESS Process;
7143  PMMPFN Pfn2;
7144  PVOID UsedPageTableHandle;
7145  PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW PhysicalView;
7146  NTSTATUS Status;
7147  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
7148 
7149  PAGED_CODE ();
7150  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
7151  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
7152  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
7153 
7154  //
7155  // If a noncachable mapping is requested, none of the pages in the
7156  // requested MDL can reside in a large page. Otherwise we would be
7157  // creating an incoherent overlapping TB entry as the same physical
7158  // page would be mapped by 2 different TB entries with different
7159  // cache attributes.
7160  //
7161 
7162  IoMapping = MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & MDL_IO_SPACE;
7163 
7164  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, IoMapping);
7165 
7166  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
7167 
7168  SavedPageCount = NumberOfPages;
7169 
7170  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7171 
7172  do {
7173 
7174  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
7175  break;
7176  }
7177  PageFrameIndex = *Page;
7178  if (MI_PAGE_FRAME_INDEX_MUST_BE_CACHED (PageFrameIndex)) {
7179  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7180  MiNonCachedCollisions += 1;
7181 
7182  ExRaiseStatus (STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS);
7183  }
7184 
7185  Page += 1;
7186  NumberOfPages -= 1;
7187  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
7188  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7189 
7190  NumberOfPages = SavedPageCount;
7191  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
7192  }
7193 
7194  //
7195  // Map the pages into the user part of the address as user
7196  // read/write no-delete.
7197  //
7198 
7199  Vad = ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool, sizeof(MMVAD_LONG), 'ldaV');
7200 
7201  if (Vad == NULL) {
7202 
7203  ExRaiseStatus (STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES);
7204  }
7205 
7206  PhysicalView = (PMI_PHYSICAL_VIEW)ExAllocatePoolWithTag (NonPagedPool,
7207  sizeof(MI_PHYSICAL_VIEW),
7208  MI_PHYSICAL_VIEW_KEY);
7209  if (PhysicalView == NULL) {
7210  ExFreePool (Vad);
7211 
7212  ExRaiseStatus (STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES);
7213  }
7214 
7215  RtlZeroMemory (Vad, sizeof (MMVAD_LONG));
7216 
7217  ASSERT (Vad->ControlArea == NULL);
7218  ASSERT (Vad->FirstPrototypePte == NULL);
7219  ASSERT (Vad->u.LongFlags == 0);
7220  Vad->u.VadFlags.Protection = MM_READWRITE;
7221  Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType = VadDevicePhysicalMemory;
7222  Vad->u.VadFlags.PrivateMemory = 1;
7223 
7224  Vad->u2.VadFlags2.LongVad = 1;
7225 
7226  PhysicalView->Vad = (PMMVAD) Vad;
7227  PhysicalView->VadType = VadDevicePhysicalMemory;
7228 
7229  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
7230  Process = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (Thread);
7231 
7232  //
7233  // Make sure the specified starting and ending addresses are
7234  // within the user part of the virtual address space.
7235  //
7236 
7237  if (BaseVa != NULL) {
7238 
7239  if (BYTE_OFFSET (BaseVa) != 0) {
7240 
7241  //
7242  // Invalid base address.
7243  //
7244 
7245  Status = STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS;
7246  goto ErrorReturn;
7247  }
7248 
7249  EndingAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseVa + ((ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPages * PAGE_SIZE) - 1);
7250 
7251  if ((EndingAddress <= BaseVa) || (EndingAddress > MM_HIGHEST_VAD_ADDRESS)) {
7252  //
7253  // Invalid region size.
7254  //
7255 
7256  Status = STATUS_INVALID_ADDRESS;
7257  goto ErrorReturn;
7258  }
7259 
7260  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7261 
7262  //
7263  // Make sure the address space was not deleted, if so, return an error.
7264  //
7265 
7266  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) {
7267  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7268  Status = STATUS_PROCESS_IS_TERMINATING;
7269  goto ErrorReturn;
7270  }
7271 
7272  //
7273  // Make sure the address space is not already in use.
7274  //
7275 
7276  if (MiCheckForConflictingVadExistence (Process, BaseVa, EndingAddress) == TRUE) {
7277  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7278  Status = STATUS_CONFLICTING_ADDRESSES;
7279  goto ErrorReturn;
7280  }
7281  }
7282  else {
7283 
7284  //
7285  // Get the address creation mutex.
7286  //
7287 
7288  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7289 
7290  //
7291  // Make sure the address space was not deleted, if so, return an error.
7292  //
7293 
7294  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_VM_DELETED) {
7295  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7296  Status = STATUS_PROCESS_IS_TERMINATING;
7297  goto ErrorReturn;
7298  }
7299 
7300  Status = MiFindEmptyAddressRange ((ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPages * PAGE_SIZE,
7301  X64K,
7302  0,
7303  &BaseVa);
7304 
7305  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
7306  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7307  goto ErrorReturn;
7308  }
7309 
7310  EndingAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseVa + ((ULONG_PTR)NumberOfPages * PAGE_SIZE) - 1);
7311  }
7312 
7313  Vad->StartingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (BaseVa);
7314  Vad->EndingVpn = MI_VA_TO_VPN (EndingAddress);
7315 
7316  PhysicalView->StartingVpn = Vad->StartingVpn;
7317  PhysicalView->EndingVpn = Vad->EndingVpn;
7318 
7319  //
7320  // The PhysicalVadRoot table root is not deleted until
7321  // the process exits.
7322  //
7323 
7324  if ((Process->PhysicalVadRoot == NULL) &&
7325  (MiCreatePhysicalVadRoot (Process, FALSE) == NULL)) {
7326 
7327  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7328  Status = STATUS_INSUFFICIENT_RESOURCES;
7329  goto ErrorReturn;
7330  }
7331 
7332  Status = MiInsertVadCharges ((PMMVAD) Vad, Process);
7333 
7334  if (!NT_SUCCESS (Status)) {
7335  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7336  goto ErrorReturn;
7337  }
7338 
7339  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
7340 
7341  MiInsertVad ((PMMVAD) Vad, Process);
7342 
7343  //
7344  // The VAD has been inserted, but the physical view descriptor cannot
7345  // be until the page table page hierarchy is in place. This is to
7346  // prevent races with probes.
7347  //
7348 
7349  //
7350  // Create a page table and fill in the mappings for the Vad.
7351  //
7352 
7353  Va = BaseVa;
7354  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseVa);
7355 
7356  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
7357 
7358  do {
7359 
7360  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
7361  break;
7362  }
7363 
7364  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPte);
7365 
7366  MiMakePdeExistAndMakeValid (PointerPde, Process, MM_NOIRQL);
7367 
7368  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
7369 
7370  //
7371  // Another zeroed PTE is being made non-zero.
7372  //
7373 
7374  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (Va);
7375 
7376  MI_INCREMENT_USED_PTES_BY_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle);
7377 
7378  TempPte = ValidUserPte;
7379  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = *Page;
7380 
7381  if ((IoMapping == 0) || (MI_IS_PFN (*Page))) {
7382 
7383  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
7384  ASSERT (Pfn2->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0);
7385 
7386  switch (Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute) {
7387 
7388  case MiCached:
7389  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
7390  //
7391  // The caller asked for a noncached or writecombined
7392  // mapping, but the page is already mapped cached by
7393  // someone else. Override the caller's request in
7394  // order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
7395  //
7396 
7397  MiCacheOverride[0] += 1;
7398  }
7399  break;
7400 
7401  case MiNonCached:
7402  if (CacheAttribute != MiNonCached) {
7403 
7404  //
7405  // The caller asked for a cached or writecombined
7406  // mapping, but the page is already mapped noncached
7407  // by someone else. Override the caller's request
7408  // in order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
7409  //
7410 
7411  MiCacheOverride[1] += 1;
7412  }
7413  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
7414  break;
7415 
7416  case MiWriteCombined:
7417  if (CacheAttribute != MiWriteCombined) {
7418 
7419  //
7420  // The caller asked for a cached or noncached
7421  // mapping, but the page is already mapped
7422  // writecombined by someone else. Override the
7423  // caller's request in order to keep the TB page
7424  // attribute coherent.
7425  //
7426 
7427  MiCacheOverride[2] += 1;
7428  }
7429  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
7430  break;
7431 
7432  case MiNotMapped:
7433 
7434  //
7435  // This better be for a page allocated with
7436  // MmAllocatePagesForMdl. Otherwise it might be a
7437  // page on the freelist which could subsequently be
7438  // given out with a different attribute !
7439  //
7440 
7441  ASSERT ((Pfn2->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME) ||
7442  (Pfn2->PteAddress == (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR)(X64K | 0x1)));
7443  switch (CacheAttribute) {
7444 
7445  case MiCached:
7446  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
7447  break;
7448 
7449  case MiNonCached:
7450  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiNonCached;
7451  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
7452  break;
7453 
7454  case MiWriteCombined:
7455  Pfn2->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiWriteCombined;
7456  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
7457  break;
7458 
7459  default:
7460  ASSERT (FALSE);
7461  break;
7462  }
7463  break;
7464 
7465  default:
7466  ASSERT (FALSE);
7467  break;
7468  }
7469  }
7470  else {
7471  switch (CacheAttribute) {
7472 
7473  case MiCached:
7474  break;
7475 
7476  case MiNonCached:
7477  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
7478  break;
7479 
7480  case MiWriteCombined:
7481  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
7482  break;
7483 
7484  default:
7485  ASSERT (FALSE);
7486  break;
7487  }
7488  }
7489 
7490  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
7491 
7492  //
7493  // A PTE just went from not present, not transition to
7494  // present. The share count and valid count must be
7495  // updated in the page table page which contains this PTE.
7496  //
7497 
7498  Pfn2 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PointerPde->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
7499  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7500  Pfn2->u2.ShareCount += 1;
7501  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7502 
7503  Page += 1;
7504  PointerPte += 1;
7505  NumberOfPages -= 1;
7506  Va += PAGE_SIZE;
7507  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
7508 
7509  //
7510  // Insert the physical view descriptor now that the page table page
7511  // hierarchy is in place. Note probes can find this descriptor immediately
7512  // once the working set mutex is released.
7513  //
7514 
7515  ASSERT (Process->PhysicalVadRoot != NULL);
7516 
7517  MiInsertNode ((PMMADDRESS_NODE)PhysicalView, Process->PhysicalVadRoot);
7518 
7519  UNLOCK_WS_AND_ADDRESS_SPACE (Thread, Process);
7520 
7521  ASSERT (BaseVa != NULL);
7522 
7523  BaseVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseVa + MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
7524 
7525  return BaseVa;
7526 
7527 ErrorReturn:
7528 
7529  ExFreePool (Vad);
7530  ExFreePool (PhysicalView);
7531 
7532  ExRaiseStatus (Status);
7533 }
7534 
7535 VOID
7536 MiUnmapLockedPagesInUserSpace (
7537  IN PVOID BaseAddress,
7538  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
7539  )
7540 
7541 /*++
7542 
7543 Routine Description:
7544 
7545  This routine unmaps locked pages which were previously mapped via
7546  a MmMapLockedPages function.
7547 
7548 Arguments:
7549 
7550  BaseAddress - Supplies the base address where the pages were previously
7551  mapped.
7552 
7553  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies a valid Memory Descriptor List which has
7554  been updated by MmProbeAndLockPages.
7555 
7556 Return Value:
7557 
7558  None.
7559 
7560 Environment:
7561 
7562  Kernel mode. APC_LEVEL or below.
7563 
7564 --*/
7565 
7566 {
7567  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
7568  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
7569  PMMPTE PointerPte;
7570  PMMPTE PointerPde;
7571 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
7572  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
7573 #endif
7574 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
7575  PMMPTE PointerPxe;
7576 #endif
7577  PVOID StartingVa;
7578  PVOID EndingVa;
7579  KIRQL OldIrql;
7580  PMMVAD Vad;
7581  PMMVAD PreviousVad;
7582  PMMVAD NextVad;
7583  PVOID TempVa;
7584  PETHREAD Thread;
7585  PEPROCESS Process;
7586  PMMPFN PageTablePfn;
7587  PFN_NUMBER PageTablePage;
7588  PVOID UsedPageTableHandle;
7589  MMPTE_FLUSH_LIST PteFlushList;
7590 
7591  PteFlushList.Count = 0;
7592 
7593  MmLockPageableSectionByHandle (ExPageLockHandle);
7594 
7595  StartingVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
7596  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
7597 
7598  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
7599  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (StartingVa,
7600  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
7601 
7602  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
7603 
7604  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
7605  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (BaseAddress);
7606 
7607  //
7608  // This was mapped into the user portion of the address space and
7609  // the corresponding virtual address descriptor must be deleted.
7610  //
7611  // Get the working set pushlock and the address creation mutex.
7612  //
7613 
7614  Thread = PsGetCurrentThread ();
7615  Process = PsGetCurrentProcessByThread (Thread);
7616 
7617  LOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7618 
7619  Vad = MiLocateAddress (BaseAddress);
7620 
7621  if ((Vad == NULL) || (Vad->u.VadFlags.VadType != VadDevicePhysicalMemory)) {
7622  UNLOCK_ADDRESS_SPACE (Process);
7623  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
7624  return;
7625  }
7626 
7627  PreviousVad = MiGetPreviousVad (Vad);
7628  NextVad = MiGetNextVad (Vad);
7629 
7630  StartingVa = MI_VPN_TO_VA (Vad->StartingVpn);
7631  EndingVa = MI_VPN_TO_VA_ENDING (Vad->EndingVpn);
7632 
7633  MiRemoveVadCharges (Vad, Process);
7634 
7635  //
7636  // Return commitment for page table pages if possible.
7637  //
7638 
7639  MiReturnPageTablePageCommitment (StartingVa,
7640  EndingVa,
7641  Process,
7642  PreviousVad,
7643  NextVad);
7644 
7645  LOCK_WS_UNSAFE (Thread, Process);
7646 
7647  MiPhysicalViewRemover (Process, Vad);
7648 
7649  MiRemoveVad (Vad, Process);
7650 
7651  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (BaseAddress);
7652  PageTablePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde);
7653  PageTablePfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTablePage);
7654 
7655  //
7656  // Get the PFN lock so we can safely decrement share and valid
7657  // counts on page table pages.
7658  //
7659 
7660  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7661 
7662  do {
7663 
7664  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
7665  break;
7666  }
7667 
7668  ASSERT64 (MiGetPdeAddress(PointerPte)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7669  ASSERT (MiGetPteAddress(PointerPte)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7670  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7671 
7672  //
7673  // Another PTE is being zeroed.
7674  //
7675 
7676  MI_DECREMENT_USED_PTES_BY_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle);
7677 
7678  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPte);
7679 
7680  if (PteFlushList.Count < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
7681  PteFlushList.FlushVa[PteFlushList.Count] = BaseAddress;
7682  PteFlushList.Count += 1;
7683  }
7684 
7685  MiDecrementShareCountInline (PageTablePfn, PageTablePage);
7686 
7687  PointerPte += 1;
7688  NumberOfPages -= 1;
7689  BaseAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseAddress + PAGE_SIZE);
7690  Page += 1;
7691 
7692  if ((MiIsPteOnPdeBoundary(PointerPte)) || (NumberOfPages == 0)) {
7693 
7694  if (PteFlushList.Count != 0) {
7695  MiFlushPteList (&PteFlushList);
7696  }
7697 
7698  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress(PointerPte - 1);
7699  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7700 
7701  //
7702  // If all the entries have been eliminated from the previous
7703  // page table page, delete the page table page itself. Likewise
7704  // with the page directory and parent pages.
7705  //
7706 
7707  if (MI_GET_USED_PTES_FROM_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle) == 0) {
7708  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Long != 0);
7709 
7710 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
7711  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (PointerPte - 1);
7712  MI_DECREMENT_USED_PTES_BY_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle);
7713 #endif
7714 
7715  TempVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPde);
7716  MiDeletePte (PointerPde,
7717  TempVa,
7718  FALSE,
7719  Process,
7720  NULL,
7721  NULL,
7722  OldIrql);
7723 
7724 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 3)
7725  if ((MiIsPteOnPpeBoundary(PointerPte)) || (NumberOfPages == 0)) {
7726 
7727  PointerPpe = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPde);
7728  ASSERT (PointerPpe->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
7729 
7730  //
7731  // If all the entries have been eliminated from the previous
7732  // page directory page, delete the page directory page too.
7733  //
7734 
7735  if (MI_GET_USED_PTES_FROM_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle) == 0) {
7736  ASSERT (PointerPpe->u.Long != 0);
7737 
7738 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
7739  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (PointerPde);
7740  MI_DECREMENT_USED_PTES_BY_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle);
7741 #endif
7742 
7743  TempVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPpe);
7744  MiDeletePte (PointerPpe,
7745  TempVa,
7746  FALSE,
7747  Process,
7748  NULL,
7749  NULL,
7750  OldIrql);
7751 
7752 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS >= 4)
7753  if ((MiIsPteOnPxeBoundary(PointerPte)) || (NumberOfPages == 0)) {
7754  PointerPxe = MiGetPdeAddress (PointerPde);
7755  ASSERT (PointerPxe->u.Long != 0);
7756  if (MI_GET_USED_PTES_FROM_HANDLE (UsedPageTableHandle) == 0) {
7757  TempVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte(PointerPxe);
7758  MiDeletePte (PointerPxe,
7759  TempVa,
7760  FALSE,
7761  Process,
7762  NULL,
7763  NULL,
7764  OldIrql);
7765  }
7766  }
7767 #endif
7768  }
7769  }
7770 #endif
7771  }
7772 
7773  if (NumberOfPages == 0) {
7774  break;
7775  }
7776 
7777  UsedPageTableHandle = MI_GET_USED_PTES_HANDLE (BaseAddress);
7778  PointerPde += 1;
7779  PageTablePage = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde);
7780  PageTablePfn = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageTablePage);
7781  }
7782 
7783  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
7784 
7785  if (PteFlushList.Count != 0) {
7786  MiFlushPteList (&PteFlushList);
7787  }
7788 
7789  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7790 
7791  UNLOCK_WS_AND_ADDRESS_SPACE (Thread, Process);
7792 
7793  ExFreePool (Vad);
7794 
7795  MmUnlockPageableImageSection (ExPageLockHandle);
7796 
7797  return;
7798 }
7799 
7800 #define MI_LARGE_PAGE_VA_SPACE ((ULONG64)8 * 1024 * 1024 * 1024) // Relatively arbitrary
7801 
7802 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
7803 
7804 PVOID MiLargeVaStart;
7805 ULONG MiLargeVaInUse [(MI_LARGE_PAGE_VA_SPACE / MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE) / 32];
7806 
7807 #endif
7808 
7809 VOID
7810 MiInitializeLargePageSupport (
7811  VOID
7812  )
7813 
7814 /*++
7815 
7816 Routine Description:
7817 
7818  This function is called once at system initialization.
7819 
7820 Arguments:
7821 
7822  None.
7823 
7824 Return Value:
7825 
7826  None.
7827 
7828 Environment:
7829 
7830  Kernel mode, INIT time. Resident available pages are not yet initialized,
7831  but everything else is.
7832 
7833 --*/
7834 
7835 {
7836 
7837 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=3)
7838 
7839  ULONG PageColor;
7840  KIRQL OldIrql;
7841  MMPTE TempPte;
7842  PMMPTE PointerPpe;
7843  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
7844  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
7845 
7846  MiLargeVaStart = (PVOID)-1;
7847 
7848  RtlInitializeBitMap (&MiLargeVaBitMap,
7849  MiLargeVaInUse,
7850  (ULONG) sizeof (MiLargeVaInUse) * 8);
7851 
7852  ASSERT (MmNonPagedPoolEnd != NULL);
7853 
7854  KeInitializeSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock);
7855 
7856 #if (_MI_PAGING_LEVELS>=4)
7857 
7858  PointerPpe = MiGetPxeAddress (MmNonPagedPoolEnd) + 1;
7859 
7860  while (PointerPpe->u.Long != 0) {
7861  PointerPpe += 1;
7862  }
7863 
7864  //
7865  // Allocate the top level extended page directory parent.
7866  //
7867 
7868  if (MiChargeCommitment (1, NULL) == FALSE) {
7869  RtlSetAllBits (&MiLargeVaBitMap);
7870  return;
7871  }
7872 
7873  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_LARGE_VA_PAGES, 1);
7874 
7875  ASSERT (PointerPpe->u.Long == 0);
7876  PointerPpe->u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
7877 
7878  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7879 
7880  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
7881  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
7882  }
7883 
7884  PageColor = MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_VA (VirtualAddress);
7885 
7886  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPage (PageColor);
7887 
7888  MiInitializePfn (PageFrameIndex, PointerPpe, 1);
7889 
7890  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7891 
7892  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte, PageFrameIndex, MM_READWRITE, PointerPpe);
7893 
7894  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
7895 
7896  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPpe, TempPte);
7897 
7898  PointerPpe = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPpe);
7899 
7900 #else
7901 
7902  PointerPpe = MiGetPpeAddress (MmNonPagedPoolEnd) + 1;
7903 
7904  while (PointerPpe->u.Long != 0) {
7905  PointerPpe += 1;
7906  }
7907 
7908 #endif
7909 
7910  MiLargeVaStart = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPpe (PointerPpe);
7911 
7912  NumberOfPages = (MI_LARGE_PAGE_VA_SPACE / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PPE);
7913 
7914  ASSERT (NumberOfPages != 0);
7915 
7916  if (MiChargeCommitment (NumberOfPages, NULL) == FALSE) {
7917  RtlSetAllBits (&MiLargeVaBitMap);
7918  return;
7919  }
7920 
7921  MM_TRACK_COMMIT (MM_DBG_COMMIT_LARGE_VA_PAGES, NumberOfPages);
7922 
7923  do {
7924 
7925  ASSERT (PointerPpe->u.Long == 0);
7926  PointerPpe->u.Long = MM_DEMAND_ZERO_WRITE_PTE;
7927 
7928  LOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7929 
7930  if (MmAvailablePages < MM_HIGH_LIMIT) {
7931  MiEnsureAvailablePageOrWait (NULL, OldIrql);
7932  }
7933 
7934  PageColor = MI_GET_PAGE_COLOR_FROM_VA (VirtualAddress);
7935 
7936  PageFrameIndex = MiRemoveZeroPage (PageColor);
7937 
7938  MiInitializePfn (PageFrameIndex, PointerPpe, 1);
7939 
7940  UNLOCK_PFN (OldIrql);
7941 
7942  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPte, PageFrameIndex, MM_READWRITE, PointerPpe);
7943 
7944  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPte);
7945 
7946  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPpe, TempPte);
7947 
7948  PointerPpe += 1;
7949 
7950  NumberOfPages -= 1;
7951 
7952  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
7953 
7954  RtlClearAllBits (&MiLargeVaBitMap);
7955 
7956 #else
7957 
7958  //
7959  // Initialize process tracking so that large page system PTE mappings
7960  // can be rippled during creation/deletion.
7961  //
7962 
7963  MiLargePageHyperPte = MiReserveSystemPtes (1, SystemPteSpace);
7964 
7965  if (MiLargePageHyperPte == NULL) {
7966  MiIssueNoPtesBugcheck (1, SystemPteSpace);
7967  }
7968 
7969  MiLargePageHyperPte->u.Long = 0;
7970 
7971  InitializeListHead (&MmProcessList);
7972 
7973  InsertTailList (&MmProcessList, &PsGetCurrentProcess()->MmProcessLinks);
7974 
7975 #endif
7976 
7977  return;
7978 }
7979 
7980 #if !defined (_WIN64)
7981 PMMPTE MiInitialSystemPageDirectory;
7982 #endif
7983 
7984 
7985 PVOID
7986 MiMapWithLargePages (
7987  IN PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex,
7988  IN PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages,
7989  IN ULONG Protection,
7990  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType
7991  )
7992 
7993 /*++
7994 
7995 Routine Description:
7996 
7997  This function maps the specified physical address into the non-pageable
7998  portion of the system address space using large TB entries. If the range
7999  cannot be mapped using large TB entries then NULL is returned and the
8000  caller will map it with small TB entries.
8001 
8002 Arguments:
8003 
8004  PageFrameIndex - Supplies the starting page frame index to map.
8005 
8006  NumberOfPages - Supplies the number of pages to map.
8007 
8008  Protection - Supplies the number of pages to map.
8009 
8010  CacheType - Supplies MmNonCached if the physical address is to be mapped
8011  as non-cached, MmCached if the address should be cached, and
8012  MmWriteCombined if the address should be cached and
8013  write-combined as a frame buffer which is to be used only by
8014  the video port driver. All other callers should use
8015  MmUSWCCached. MmUSWCCached is available only if the PAT
8016  feature is present and available.
8017 
8018  For I/O device registers, this is usually specified
8019  as MmNonCached.
8020 
8021 Return Value:
8022 
8023  Returns the virtual address which maps the specified physical addresses.
8024  The value NULL is returned if sufficient large virtual address space for
8025  the mapping could not be found.
8026 
8027 Environment:
8028 
8029  Kernel mode, Should be IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below, but unfortunately
8030  callers are coming in at DISPATCH_LEVEL and it's too late to change the
8031  rules now. This means you can never make this routine pageable.
8032 
8033 --*/
8034 
8035 {
8036  MMPTE TempPde;
8037  PMMPTE PointerPde;
8038  PMMPTE LastPde;
8039  PVOID BaseVa;
8040  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
8041  KIRQL OldIrql;
8042  LOGICAL IoMapping;
8043 #if defined(_WIN64)
8044  ULONG StartPosition;
8045  ULONG NumberOfBits;
8046 #else
8047  PMMPTE TargetPde;
8048  PMMPTE TargetPdeBase;
8049  PMMPTE PointerPdeBase;
8050  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectoryIndex;
8051  PEPROCESS Process;
8052  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
8053  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
8054 #endif
8055 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
8056  ULONG i;
8057  PMMPTE PaeTop;
8058 #endif
8059 
8060  ASSERT ((NumberOfPages % (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT)) == 0);
8061  ASSERT ((PageFrameIndex % (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT)) == 0);
8062 
8063 #ifdef _X86_
8064  if ((KeFeatureBits & KF_LARGE_PAGE) == 0) {
8065  return NULL;
8066  }
8067 #endif
8068 
8069  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, TRUE);
8070 
8071  IoMapping = !MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex);
8072 
8073 #if defined(_WIN64)
8074 
8075  NumberOfBits = (ULONG)(NumberOfPages / (MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE >> PAGE_SHIFT));
8076 
8077  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, &OldIrql);
8078 
8079  StartPosition = RtlFindClearBitsAndSet (&MiLargeVaBitMap,
8080  NumberOfBits,
8081  0);
8082 
8083  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, OldIrql);
8084 
8085  if (StartPosition == NO_BITS_FOUND) {
8086  return NULL;
8087  }
8088 
8089  BaseVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MiLargeVaStart + ((ULONG_PTR)StartPosition * MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE));
8090 
8091  if (IoMapping) {
8092 
8093  CacheAttribute = MiInsertIoSpaceMap (BaseVa,
8094  PageFrameIndex,
8095  NumberOfPages,
8096  CacheAttribute);
8097 
8098  if (CacheAttribute == MiNotMapped) {
8099  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, &OldIrql);
8100  RtlClearBits (&MiLargeVaBitMap, StartPosition, NumberOfBits);
8101  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, OldIrql);
8102  return NULL;
8103  }
8104  }
8105 
8106  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (BaseVa);
8107 
8108 #else
8109 
8110  PointerPde = MiReserveAlignedSystemPtes ((ULONG)NumberOfPages,
8111  SystemPteSpace,
8112  MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE);
8113 
8114  if (PointerPde == NULL) {
8115  return NULL;
8116  }
8117 
8118  ASSERT (BYTE_OFFSET (PointerPde) == 0);
8119 
8120  BaseVa = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPde);
8121  ASSERT (((ULONG_PTR)BaseVa & (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE - 1)) == 0);
8122 
8123  if (IoMapping) {
8124 
8125  CacheAttribute = MiInsertIoSpaceMap (BaseVa,
8126  PageFrameIndex,
8127  NumberOfPages,
8128  CacheAttribute);
8129 
8130  if (CacheAttribute == MiNotMapped) {
8131  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPde,
8132  NumberOfPages,
8133  SystemPteSpace);
8134  return NULL;
8135  }
8136  }
8137 
8138  PointerPde = MiGetPteAddress (PointerPde);
8139 
8140  PointerPdeBase = PointerPde;
8141 
8142 #endif
8143 
8144  MI_MAKE_VALID_PTE (TempPde,
8145  PageFrameIndex,
8146  Protection,
8147  PointerPde);
8148 
8149  MI_SET_PTE_DIRTY (TempPde);
8150  MI_SET_ACCESSED_IN_PTE (&TempPde, 1);
8151  MI_SET_GLOBAL_STATE (TempPde, 1);
8152  MI_MAKE_PDE_MAP_LARGE_PAGE (&TempPde);
8153 
8154  switch (CacheAttribute) {
8155 
8156  case MiNonCached:
8157  MI_DISABLE_LARGE_PTE_CACHING (TempPde);
8158  break;
8159 
8160  case MiCached:
8161  break;
8162 
8163  case MiWriteCombined:
8164  MI_SET_LARGE_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPde);
8165  break;
8166 
8167  default:
8168  ASSERT (FALSE);
8169  break;
8170  }
8171 
8172  LastPde = PointerPde + (NumberOfPages / (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE >> PAGE_SHIFT));
8173 
8174  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
8175 
8176 #if defined(_WIN64)
8177 
8178  while (PointerPde < LastPde) {
8179 
8180  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Long == 0);
8181 
8182  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPde, TempPde);
8183 
8184  TempPde.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber += (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8185 
8186  PointerPde += 1;
8187  }
8188 
8189 #else
8190 
8191  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
8192 
8193  LOCK_EXPANSION2 (OldIrql);
8194 
8195  NextEntry = MmProcessList.Flink;
8196 
8197  while (NextEntry != &MmProcessList) {
8198 
8199  Process = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry, EPROCESS, MmProcessLinks);
8200 
8201  // Two process states must be carefully handled here -
8202  //
8203  // 1. Processes that are just being created where they are still
8204  // initializing their page directory, etc.
8205  //
8206  // 2. Processes that are outswapped.
8207  //
8208 
8209  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED) {
8210 
8211  //
8212  // The process is further along in process creation or is still
8213  // outswapped. Either way, an update is already queued so our
8214  // current changes will be processed later anyway before the process
8215  // can run so no need to do anything here.
8216  //
8217 
8218  NOTHING;
8219  }
8220  else if (Process->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0] == 0) {
8221 
8222  //
8223  // This process is being created and there is no way to tell where
8224  // during creation it is (ie: it may be filling PDEs right now!).
8225  // So just mark the process as needing a PDE update at the
8226  // beginning of MmInitializeProcessAddressSpace.
8227  //
8228 
8229  PS_SET_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
8230  }
8231  else if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAPPED) {
8232 
8233  //
8234  // This process is outswapped. Even though the page directory
8235  // may still be in transition, the process must be inswapped
8236  // before it can run again, so just mark the process as needing
8237  // a PDE update at that time.
8238  //
8239 
8240  PS_SET_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
8241  }
8242  else {
8243 
8244  //
8245  // This process is resident so update the relevant PDEs in its
8246  // address space right now.
8247  //
8248 
8249  PointerPde = PointerPdeBase;
8250  TempPde.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
8251 
8252 #if !defined (_X86PAE_)
8253  PageDirectoryIndex = Process->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0] >> PAGE_SHIFT;
8254 #else
8255  //
8256  // The range cannot cross PAE PDPTE entries, but we do need to
8257  // locate which entry it does lie in.
8258  //
8259 
8260  PaeTop = Process->PaeTop;
8261 
8262  i = (((ULONG_PTR) PointerPde - PDE_BASE) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8263  ASSERT ((PaeTop + i)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
8264  PageDirectoryIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)((PaeTop + i)->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
8265 #endif
8266 
8267  TargetPdeBase = (PMMPTE) MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (
8268  CurrentProcess,
8269  PageDirectoryIndex);
8270 
8271  TargetPde = (PMMPTE)((PCHAR) TargetPdeBase + BYTE_OFFSET (PointerPde));
8272 
8273  while (PointerPde < LastPde) {
8274 
8275  ASSERT (TargetPde->u.Long != 0);
8276  ASSERT (TargetPde->u.Hard.Valid != 0);
8277 
8278  *TargetPde = TempPde;
8279 
8280  TempPde.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber += (MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8281 
8282  PointerPde += 1;
8283  TargetPde += 1;
8284  }
8285 
8286  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, TargetPdeBase);
8287  }
8288 
8289  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
8290  }
8291 
8292  UNLOCK_EXPANSION2 (OldIrql);
8293 
8294 #endif
8295 
8296  //
8297  // Force all processors to use the latest mappings.
8298  //
8299 
8300  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (3);
8301 
8302  return BaseVa;
8303 }
8304 
8305 
8306 VOID
8307 MiUnmapLargePages (
8308  IN PVOID BaseAddress,
8309  IN SIZE_T NumberOfBytes
8310  )
8311 
8312 /*++
8313 
8314 Routine Description:
8315 
8316  This function unmaps a range of physical addresses which were previously
8317  mapped via MiMapWithLargePages.
8318 
8319 Arguments:
8320 
8321  BaseAddress - Supplies the base virtual address where the physical
8322  address was previously mapped.
8323 
8324  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes which were mapped.
8325 
8326 Return Value:
8327 
8328  None.
8329 
8330 Environment:
8331 
8332  Kernel mode, Should be IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below, but unfortunately
8333  callers are coming in at DISPATCH_LEVEL and it's too late to change the
8334  rules now. This means you can never make this routine pageable.
8335 
8336 --*/
8337 
8338 {
8339  PMMPTE PointerPde;
8340  PMMPTE LastPde;
8341  KIRQL OldIrql;
8342 #if defined(_WIN64)
8343  ULONG StartPosition;
8344  ULONG NumberOfBits;
8345 #else
8346  PMMPTE RestorePde;
8347  PMMPTE TargetPde;
8348  PMMPTE TargetPdeBase;
8349  PMMPTE PointerPdeBase;
8350  PFN_NUMBER PageDirectoryIndex;
8351  PEPROCESS Process;
8352  PEPROCESS CurrentProcess;
8353  PLIST_ENTRY NextEntry;
8354 #endif
8355 #if defined (_X86PAE_)
8356  PMMPTE PaeTop;
8357  ULONG i;
8358 #endif
8359 
8360  ASSERT (NumberOfBytes != 0);
8361 
8362  ASSERT (((ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress % MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE) == 0);
8363  ASSERT ((NumberOfBytes % MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE) == 0);
8364 
8365 #if defined(_WIN64)
8366  NumberOfBits = (ULONG)(NumberOfBytes / MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE);
8367 
8368  StartPosition = (ULONG)(((ULONG_PTR)BaseAddress - (ULONG_PTR)MiLargeVaStart) / MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE);
8369 
8370  ASSERT (RtlAreBitsSet (&MiLargeVaBitMap, StartPosition, NumberOfBits) == TRUE);
8371 #endif
8372 
8373  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (BaseAddress);
8374 
8375  LastPde = PointerPde + (NumberOfBytes / MM_VA_MAPPED_BY_PDE);
8376 
8377 #if defined(_WIN64)
8378 
8379  while (PointerPde < LastPde) {
8380 
8381  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Hard.Valid != 0);
8382  ASSERT (PointerPde->u.Long != 0);
8383  ASSERT (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde));
8384 
8385  MI_WRITE_ZERO_PTE (PointerPde);
8386 
8387  PointerPde += 1;
8388  }
8389 
8390 #else
8391 
8392  PointerPdeBase = PointerPde;
8393 
8394  CurrentProcess = PsGetCurrentProcess ();
8395 
8396  LOCK_EXPANSION2 (OldIrql);
8397 
8398  NextEntry = MmProcessList.Flink;
8399 
8400  while (NextEntry != &MmProcessList) {
8401 
8402  Process = CONTAINING_RECORD (NextEntry, EPROCESS, MmProcessLinks);
8403 
8404  // Two process states must be carefully handled here -
8405  //
8406  // 1. Processes that are just being created where they are still
8407  // initializing their page directory, etc.
8408  //
8409  // 2. Processes that are outswapped.
8410  //
8411 
8412  if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED) {
8413 
8414  //
8415  // The process is further along in process creation or is still
8416  // outswapped. Either way, an update is already queued so our
8417  // current changes will be processed later anyway before the process
8418  // can run so no need to do anything here.
8419  //
8420 
8421  NOTHING;
8422  }
8423  else if (Process->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0] == 0) {
8424 
8425  //
8426  // This process is being created and there is no way to tell where
8427  // during creation it is (ie: it may be filling PDEs right now!).
8428  // So just mark the process as needing a PDE update at the
8429  // beginning of MmInitializeProcessAddressSpace.
8430  //
8431 
8432  PS_SET_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
8433  }
8434  else if (Process->Flags & PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_OUTSWAPPED) {
8435 
8436  //
8437  // This process is outswapped. Even though the page directory
8438  // may still be in transition, the process must be inswapped
8439  // before it can run again, so just mark the process as needing
8440  // a PDE update at that time.
8441  //
8442 
8443  PS_SET_BITS (&Process->Flags, PS_PROCESS_FLAGS_PDE_UPDATE_NEEDED);
8444  }
8445  else {
8446 
8447  //
8448  // This process is resident so update the relevant PDEs in its
8449  // address space right now.
8450  //
8451 
8452  PointerPde = PointerPdeBase;
8453 
8454 #if !defined (_X86PAE_)
8455  PageDirectoryIndex = Process->Pcb.DirectoryTableBase[0] >> PAGE_SHIFT;
8456 #else
8457  //
8458  // The range cannot cross PAE PDPTE entries, but we do need to
8459  // locate which entry it does lie in.
8460  //
8461 
8462  PaeTop = Process->PaeTop;
8463 
8464  i = (((ULONG_PTR) PointerPde - PDE_BASE) >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8465  ASSERT ((PaeTop + i)->u.Hard.Valid == 1);
8466  PageDirectoryIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)((PaeTop + i)->u.Hard.PageFrameNumber);
8467 #endif
8468 
8469  TargetPdeBase = (PMMPTE) MiMapPageInHyperSpaceAtDpc (
8470  CurrentProcess,
8471  PageDirectoryIndex);
8472 
8473  TargetPde = (PMMPTE)((PCHAR) TargetPdeBase + BYTE_OFFSET (PointerPde));
8474 
8475  RestorePde = MiInitialSystemPageDirectory + (PointerPde - (PMMPTE)PDE_BASE);
8476 
8477  while (PointerPde < LastPde) {
8478 
8479  ASSERT (TargetPde->u.Long != 0);
8480  ASSERT (TargetPde->u.Hard.Valid != 0);
8481  ASSERT (RestorePde->u.Long != 0);
8482  ASSERT (RestorePde->u.Hard.Valid != 0);
8483 
8484  *TargetPde = *RestorePde;
8485 
8486  PointerPde += 1;
8487  TargetPde += 1;
8488  RestorePde += 1;
8489  }
8490 
8491  MiUnmapPageInHyperSpaceFromDpc (CurrentProcess, TargetPdeBase);
8492  }
8493 
8494  NextEntry = NextEntry->Flink;
8495  }
8496 
8497  UNLOCK_EXPANSION2 (OldIrql);
8498 
8499 #endif
8500 
8501  //
8502  // Force all processors to use the latest mappings.
8503  //
8504 
8505  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (4);
8506 
8507 #if defined(_WIN64)
8508 
8509  ExAcquireSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, &OldIrql);
8510 
8511  RtlClearBits (&MiLargeVaBitMap, StartPosition, NumberOfBits);
8512 
8513  ExReleaseSpinLock (&MiLargePageLock, OldIrql);
8514 
8515 #else
8516 
8517  PointerPde = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPdeBase);
8518 
8519  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPde,
8520  (ULONG)(NumberOfBytes >> PAGE_SHIFT),
8521  SystemPteSpace);
8522 
8523 #endif
8524 
8525  return;
8526 }
8527 
8528 
8529 __out_bcount(NumberOfBytes) PVOID
8530 MmMapIoSpace (
8531  __in PHYSICAL_ADDRESS PhysicalAddress,
8532  __in SIZE_T NumberOfBytes,
8533  __in MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType
8534  )
8535 
8536 /*++
8537 
8538 Routine Description:
8539 
8540  This function maps the specified physical address into the non-pageable
8541  portion of the system address space.
8542 
8543 Arguments:
8544 
8545  PhysicalAddress - Supplies the starting physical address to map.
8546 
8547  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes to map.
8548 
8549  CacheType - Supplies MmNonCached if the physical address is to be mapped
8550  as non-cached, MmCached if the address should be cached, and
8551  MmWriteCombined if the address should be cached and
8552  write-combined as a frame buffer which is to be used only by
8553  the video port driver. All other callers should use
8554  MmUSWCCached. MmUSWCCached is available only if the PAT
8555  feature is present and available.
8556 
8557  For I/O device registers, this is usually specified
8558  as MmNonCached.
8559 
8560 Return Value:
8561 
8562  Returns the virtual address which maps the specified physical addresses.
8563  The value NULL is returned if sufficient virtual address space for
8564  the mapping could not be found.
8565 
8566 Environment:
8567 
8568  Kernel mode, Should be IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below, but unfortunately
8569  callers are coming in at DISPATCH_LEVEL and it's too late to change the
8570  rules now. This means you can never make this routine pageable.
8571 
8572 --*/
8573 
8574 {
8575  KIRQL OldIrql;
8576  CSHORT IoMapping;
8577  PMMPFN Pfn1;
8578  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
8579  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
8580  PFN_NUMBER LastPageFrameIndex;
8581  PMMPTE PointerPte;
8582  PVOID BaseVa;
8583  MMPTE TempPte;
8584  PMDL TempMdl;
8585  PFN_NUMBER MdlHack[(sizeof(MDL)/sizeof(PFN_NUMBER)) + 1];
8586  PVOID CallingAddress;
8587  PVOID CallersCaller;
8588  MI_PFN_CACHE_ATTRIBUTE CacheAttribute;
8589 
8590  //
8591  // For compatibility for when CacheType used to be passed as a BOOLEAN
8592  // mask off the upper bits (TRUE == MmCached, FALSE == MmNonCached).
8593  //
8594 
8595  CacheType &= 0xFF;
8596 
8597  if (CacheType >= MmMaximumCacheType) {
8598  return NULL;
8599  }
8600 
8601 #if !defined (_MI_MORE_THAN_4GB_)
8602  ASSERT (PhysicalAddress.HighPart == 0);
8603 #endif
8604 
8605  ASSERT (NumberOfBytes != 0);
8606 
8607  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (PhysicalAddress.LowPart,
8608  NumberOfBytes);
8609 
8610  //
8611  // See if the first frame is in the PFN database and if so, they all must
8612  // be. Note since the caller is mapping the frames, they must already be
8613  // locked so the PFN lock is not needed to protect against a hot-remove.
8614  //
8615 
8616  PageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)(PhysicalAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8617 
8618  IoMapping = (CSHORT) (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex));
8619 
8620  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, IoMapping);
8621 
8622  if (IoMapping) {
8623 
8624  //
8625  // If the size and start address are an exact multiple of the
8626  // minimum large page size, try to use large pages to map the request.
8627  //
8628 
8629  if (((PhysicalAddress.LowPart % MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE) == 0) &&
8630  ((NumberOfBytes % MM_MINIMUM_VA_FOR_LARGE_PAGE) == 0)) {
8631 
8632  BaseVa = MiMapWithLargePages (PageFrameIndex,
8633  NumberOfPages,
8634  MM_EXECUTE_READWRITE,
8635  CacheType);
8636 
8637  if (BaseVa != NULL) {
8638  goto Done;
8639  }
8640  }
8641 
8642  Pfn1 = NULL;
8643  }
8644  else {
8645  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
8646  }
8647 
8648  PointerPte = MiReserveSystemPtes ((ULONG)NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
8649 
8650  if (PointerPte == NULL) {
8651  return NULL;
8652  }
8653 
8654  BaseVa = (PVOID)MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (PointerPte);
8655 
8656  PageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)(PhysicalAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8657 
8658  if (Pfn1 == NULL) {
8659  CacheAttribute = MiInsertIoSpaceMap (BaseVa,
8660  PageFrameIndex,
8661  NumberOfPages,
8662  CacheAttribute);
8663 
8664  if (CacheAttribute == MiNotMapped) {
8665  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte, (ULONG) NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
8666  return NULL;
8667  }
8668  }
8669 
8670  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
8671 
8672  //
8673  // If a noncachable mapping is requested, none of the pages in the
8674  // requested MDL can reside in a large page. Otherwise we would be
8675  // creating an incoherent overlapping TB entry as the same physical
8676  // page would be mapped by 2 different TB entries with different
8677  // cache attributes.
8678  //
8679 
8680  LastPageFrameIndex = PageFrameIndex + NumberOfPages;
8681 
8682  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
8683 
8684  do {
8685 
8686  if (MI_PAGE_FRAME_INDEX_MUST_BE_CACHED (PageFrameIndex)) {
8687  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
8688  MiNonCachedCollisions += 1;
8689  if (Pfn1 == NULL) {
8690  MiRemoveIoSpaceMap (BaseVa, NumberOfPages);
8691  }
8692  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte,
8693  (ULONG) NumberOfPages,
8694  SystemPteSpace);
8695  return NULL;
8696  }
8697 
8698  PageFrameIndex += 1;
8699 
8700  } while (PageFrameIndex < LastPageFrameIndex);
8701 
8702  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
8703 
8704  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
8705  }
8706 
8707  BaseVa = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseVa + BYTE_OFFSET(PhysicalAddress.LowPart));
8708 
8709  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
8710 
8711  switch (CacheAttribute) {
8712 
8713  case MiNonCached:
8714  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
8715  break;
8716 
8717  case MiCached:
8718  break;
8719 
8720  case MiWriteCombined:
8721  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
8722  break;
8723 
8724  default:
8725  ASSERT (FALSE);
8726  break;
8727  }
8728 
8729 #if defined(_X86_)
8730 
8731  //
8732  // Set the physical range to the proper caching type. If the PAT feature
8733  // is supported, then we just use the caching type in the PTE. Otherwise
8734  // modify the MTRRs if applicable.
8735  //
8736  // Note if the cache request is for cached or noncached, don't waste
8737  // an MTRR on this range because the PTEs can be encoded to provide
8738  // equivalent functionality.
8739  //
8740 
8741  if ((MiWriteCombiningPtes == FALSE) && (CacheAttribute == MiWriteCombined)) {
8742 
8743  //
8744  // If the address is an I/O space address, use MTRRs if possible.
8745  //
8746 
8747  NTSTATUS Status;
8748 
8749  //
8750  // If the address is a memory address, don't risk using MTRRs because
8751  // other pages in the range are likely mapped with differing attributes
8752  // in the TB and we must not add a conflicting range.
8753  //
8754 
8755  if (Pfn1 != NULL) {
8756  MiReleaseSystemPtes(PointerPte, NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
8757  return NULL;
8758  }
8759 
8760  //
8761  // Since the attribute may have been overridden (due to a collision
8762  // with a prior exiting mapping), make sure the CacheType is also
8763  // consistent before editing the MTRRs.
8764  //
8765 
8766  CacheType = MmWriteCombined;
8767 
8768  Status = KeSetPhysicalCacheTypeRange (PhysicalAddress,
8769  NumberOfBytes,
8770  CacheType);
8771 
8772  if (!NT_SUCCESS(Status)) {
8773 
8774  //
8775  // There's still a problem, fail the request.
8776  //
8777 
8778  ASSERT (Pfn1 == NULL);
8779  MiRemoveIoSpaceMap (BaseVa, NumberOfPages);
8780  MiReleaseSystemPtes(PointerPte, NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
8781  return NULL;
8782  }
8783 
8784  //
8785  // Override the write combine (weak UC) bits in the PTE and
8786  // instead use a cached attribute. This is because the processor
8787  // will use the least cachable (ie: functionally safer) attribute
8788  // of the PTE & MTRR to use - so specifying fully cached for the PTE
8789  // ensures that the MTRR value will win out.
8790  //
8791 
8792  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
8793  }
8794 #endif
8795 
8796  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
8797 
8798  PageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)(PhysicalAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8799  ASSERT ((Pfn1 == MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex)) || (Pfn1 == NULL));
8800 
8801  OldIrql = HIGH_LEVEL;
8802 
8803  MI_PREPARE_FOR_NONCACHED (CacheAttribute);
8804 
8805  do {
8806  ASSERT (PointerPte->u.Hard.Valid == 0);
8807  if (Pfn1 != NULL) {
8808 
8809  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount != 0) ||
8810  ((Pfn1->u3.e1.Rom == 1) && (CacheType == MmCached)));
8811 
8812  TempPte = ValidKernelPte;
8813 
8814  MI_ADD_EXECUTE_TO_VALID_PTE_IF_PAE (TempPte);
8815 
8816  switch (Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute) {
8817 
8818  case MiCached:
8819  if (CacheAttribute != MiCached) {
8820 
8821  //
8822  // The caller asked for a noncached or writecombined
8823  // mapping, but the page is already mapped cached by
8824  // someone else. Override the caller's request in
8825  // order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
8826  //
8827 
8828  MiCacheOverride[0] += 1;
8829  }
8830  break;
8831 
8832  case MiNonCached:
8833  if (CacheAttribute != MiNonCached) {
8834 
8835  //
8836  // The caller asked for a cached or writecombined
8837  // mapping, but the page is already mapped noncached
8838  // by someone else. Override the caller's request
8839  // in order to keep the TB page attribute coherent.
8840  //
8841 
8842  MiCacheOverride[1] += 1;
8843  }
8844  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
8845  break;
8846 
8847  case MiWriteCombined:
8848  if (CacheAttribute != MiWriteCombined) {
8849 
8850  //
8851  // The caller asked for a cached or noncached
8852  // mapping, but the page is already mapped
8853  // writecombined by someone else. Override the
8854  // caller's request in order to keep the TB page
8855  // attribute coherent.
8856  //
8857 
8858  MiCacheOverride[2] += 1;
8859  }
8860  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
8861  break;
8862 
8863  case MiNotMapped:
8864 
8865  //
8866  // This better be for a page allocated with
8867  // MmAllocatePagesForMdl. Otherwise it might be a
8868  // page on the freelist which could subsequently be
8869  // given out with a different attribute !
8870  //
8871 
8872 #if defined (_MI_MORE_THAN_4GB_)
8873  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME) ||
8874  (Pfn1->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_4GB_RECLAIM) ||
8875  (Pfn1->PteAddress == (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR)(X64K | 0x1)));
8876 #else
8877  ASSERT ((Pfn1->u4.PteFrame == MI_MAGIC_AWE_PTEFRAME) ||
8878  (Pfn1->PteAddress == (PVOID) (ULONG_PTR)(X64K | 0x1)));
8879 #endif
8880 
8881  if (OldIrql == HIGH_LEVEL) {
8882  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
8883  }
8884 
8885  switch (CacheAttribute) {
8886 
8887  case MiCached:
8888  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiCached;
8889  break;
8890 
8891  case MiNonCached:
8892  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiNonCached;
8893  MI_DISABLE_CACHING (TempPte);
8894  break;
8895 
8896  case MiWriteCombined:
8897  Pfn1->u3.e1.CacheAttribute = MiWriteCombined;
8898  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (TempPte);
8899  break;
8900 
8901  default:
8902  ASSERT (FALSE);
8903  break;
8904  }
8905  break;
8906 
8907  default:
8908  ASSERT (FALSE);
8909  break;
8910  }
8911  Pfn1 += 1;
8912  }
8913  TempPte.u.Hard.PageFrameNumber = PageFrameIndex;
8914  MI_WRITE_VALID_PTE (PointerPte, TempPte);
8915  PointerPte += 1;
8916  PageFrameIndex += 1;
8917  NumberOfPages -= 1;
8918  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
8919 
8920  if (OldIrql != HIGH_LEVEL) {
8921  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
8922  }
8923 
8924 Done:
8925 
8926  if (MmTrackPtes & 0x1) {
8927 
8928  RtlGetCallersAddress (&CallingAddress, &CallersCaller);
8929 
8930  TempMdl = (PMDL) MdlHack;
8931  TempMdl->MappedSystemVa = BaseVa;
8932 
8933  PageFrameIndex = (PFN_NUMBER)(PhysicalAddress.QuadPart >> PAGE_SHIFT);
8934  *(PPFN_NUMBER)(TempMdl + 1) = PageFrameIndex;
8935 
8936  TempMdl->StartVa = (PVOID)(PAGE_ALIGN((ULONG_PTR)PhysicalAddress.QuadPart));
8937  TempMdl->ByteOffset = BYTE_OFFSET(PhysicalAddress.LowPart);
8938  TempMdl->ByteCount = (ULONG)NumberOfBytes;
8939 
8940  CacheAttribute = MI_TRANSLATE_CACHETYPE (CacheType, IoMapping);
8941 
8942  MiInsertPteTracker (TempMdl,
8943  1,
8944  IoMapping,
8945  CacheAttribute,
8946  CallingAddress,
8947  CallersCaller);
8948  }
8949 
8950  return BaseVa;
8951 }
8952 
8953 VOID
8954 MmUnmapIoSpace (
8955  __in_bcount(NumberOfBytes) PVOID BaseAddress,
8956  __in SIZE_T NumberOfBytes
8957  )
8958 
8959 /*++
8960 
8961 Routine Description:
8962 
8963  This function unmaps a range of physical addresses which were previously
8964  mapped via an MmMapIoSpace function call.
8965 
8966 Arguments:
8967 
8968  BaseAddress - Supplies the base virtual address where the physical
8969  address was previously mapped.
8970 
8971  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes which were mapped.
8972 
8973 Return Value:
8974 
8975  None.
8976 
8977 Environment:
8978 
8979  Kernel mode, Should be IRQL of APC_LEVEL or below, but unfortunately
8980  callers are coming in at DISPATCH_LEVEL and it's too late to change the
8981  rules now. This means you can never make this routine pageable.
8982 
8983 --*/
8984 
8985 {
8986  ULONG i;
8987  PMMPTE PointerPte;
8988  PMMPTE PointerPde;
8989  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
8990  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
8991  PVOID VaFlushList[MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT];
8992 
8993  ASSERT (NumberOfBytes != 0);
8994 
8995  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (BaseAddress, NumberOfBytes);
8996 
8997  if (MmTrackPtes & 0x1) {
8998  MiRemovePteTracker (NULL, BaseAddress, NumberOfPages);
8999  }
9000 
9001  PointerPde = MiGetPdeAddress (BaseAddress);
9002 
9003  if (MI_PDE_MAPS_LARGE_PAGE (PointerPde) == 0) {
9004 
9005  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (BaseAddress);
9006 
9007  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
9008 
9009  if (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
9010 
9011  //
9012  // The PTEs must be invalidated and the TB flushed *BEFORE*
9013  // removing the I/O space map. This is because another
9014  // thread can immediately map the same I/O space with another
9015  // set of PTEs (and conflicting TB attributes) before we
9016  // call MiReleaseSystemPtes.
9017  //
9018 
9019  MiZeroMemoryPte (PointerPte, NumberOfPages);
9020 
9021  if (NumberOfPages == 1) {
9022  MI_FLUSH_SINGLE_TB (BaseAddress, TRUE);
9023  }
9024  else if (NumberOfPages < MM_MAXIMUM_FLUSH_COUNT) {
9025 
9026  for (i = 0; i < NumberOfPages; i += 1) {
9027  VaFlushList[i] = BaseAddress;
9028  BaseAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseAddress + PAGE_SIZE);
9029  }
9030 
9031  MI_FLUSH_MULTIPLE_TB ((ULONG)NumberOfPages, &VaFlushList[0], TRUE);
9032  BaseAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)BaseAddress - (i * PAGE_SIZE));
9033  }
9034  else {
9035  MI_FLUSH_ENTIRE_TB (5);
9036  }
9037 
9038  MiRemoveIoSpaceMap (BaseAddress, NumberOfPages);
9039  }
9040 
9041  MiReleaseSystemPtes (PointerPte, (ULONG)NumberOfPages, SystemPteSpace);
9042  }
9043  else {
9044 
9045  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPde) +
9046  MiGetPteOffset (BaseAddress);
9047 
9048  if (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
9049  MiRemoveIoSpaceMap (BaseAddress, NumberOfPages);
9050  }
9051 
9052  //
9053  // There is a race here because the I/O space mapping entry has been
9054  // removed but the TB has not yet been flushed (nor have the PDEs
9055  // been invalidated). Another thread could request a map in between
9056  // the above removal and the below invalidation. If this map occurs
9057  // where a driver provides the wrong page attribute it will not be
9058  // detected. This is not worth closing as it is a driver bug anyway
9059  // and you really can't always stop them from hurting themselves if
9060  // they are determined to do so. Note the alternative of invalidating
9061  // first isn't attractive because then the same PTEs could be
9062  // immediately reallocated and the new owner might want to add an
9063  // I/O space entry before this thread got to remove his. So additional
9064  // lock serialization would need to be added. Not worth it.
9065  //
9066 
9067  MiUnmapLargePages (BaseAddress, NumberOfBytes);
9068  }
9069 
9070  return;
9071 }
9072 
9073 PVOID
9074 MiAllocateContiguousMemory (
9075  IN SIZE_T NumberOfBytes,
9076  IN PFN_NUMBER LowestAcceptablePfn,
9077  IN PFN_NUMBER HighestAcceptablePfn,
9078  IN PFN_NUMBER BoundaryPfn,
9079  IN MEMORY_CACHING_TYPE CacheType,
9080  PVOID CallingAddress
9081  )
9082 
9083 /*++
9084 
9085 Routine Description:
9086 
9087  This function allocates a range of physically contiguous non-paged
9088  pool. It relies on the fact that non-paged pool is built at
9089  system initialization time from a contiguous range of physical
9090  memory. It allocates the specified size of non-paged pool and
9091  then checks to ensure it is contiguous as pool expansion does
9092  not maintain the contiguous nature of non-paged pool.
9093 
9094  This routine is designed to be used by a driver's initialization
9095  routine to allocate a contiguous block of physical memory for
9096  issuing DMA requests from.
9097 
9098 Arguments:
9099 
9100  NumberOfBytes - Supplies the number of bytes to allocate.
9101 
9102  LowestAcceptablePfn - Supplies the lowest page frame number
9103  which is valid for the allocation.
9104 
9105  HighestAcceptablePfn - Supplies the highest page frame number
9106  which is valid for the allocation.
9107 
9108  BoundaryPfn - Supplies the page frame number multiple the allocation must
9109  not cross. 0 indicates it can cross any boundary.
9110 
9111  CacheType - Supplies the type of cache mapping that will be used for the
9112  memory.
9113 
9114  CallingAddress - Supplies the calling address of the allocator.
9115 
9116 Return Value:
9117
