14797 
14798 VOID
14799 MmEnablePAT (
14800  VOID
14801  )
14802 
14803 /*++
14804 
14805 Routine Description:
14806 
14807  This routine enables the page attribute capability for individual PTE
14808  mappings.
14809 
14810 Arguments:
14811 
14812  None.
14813 
14814 Return Value:
14815 
14816  None.
14817 
14818 Environment:
14819 
14820  Kernel mode.
14821 
14822 --*/
14823 {
14824  ULONG i;
14825  MMPTE PteContents;
14826 
14827  MiWriteCombiningPtes = TRUE;
14828 
14829  //
14830  // The attribute table is statically initialized with write combining being
14831  // equivalent to noncached. Once all the processors have booted as we don't
14832  // know if they will all have a PAT (or equivalent functionality) until
14833  // then, we can override the PTE maps as below.
14834  //
14835  // Note if the machine cannot support all the attribute types to main
14836  // memory, then the MmProtectToPteMask table will already have been
14837  // modified in MiInitializeCacheOverrides. If so, then nothing more
14838  // needs to be done here.
14839  //
14840 
14841  if (MiAllMainMemoryMustBeCached == TRUE) {
14842 
14843  //
14844  // The table has already been updated.
14845  //
14846 
14847  return;
14848  }
14849 
14850  for (i = MM_WRITECOMBINE + 1; i < 32; i += 1) {
14851  PteContents.u.Long = MmProtectToPteMask[i];
14852  MI_SET_PTE_WRITE_COMBINE (PteContents);
14853  MmProtectToPteMask[i] = PteContents.u.Long;
14854  }
14855 }
14856 
14857 LOGICAL
14858 MmIsSystemAddressLocked (
14859  IN PVOID VirtualAddress
14860  )
14861 
14862 /*++
14863 
14864 Routine Description:
14865 
14866  This routine determines whether the specified system address is currently
14867  locked.
14868 
14869  This routine should only be called for debugging purposes, as it is not
14870  guaranteed upon return to the caller that the address is still locked.
14871  (The address could easily have been trimmed prior to return).
14872 
14873 Arguments:
14874 
14875  VirtualAddress - Supplies the virtual address to check.
14876 
14877 Return Value:
14878 
14879  TRUE if the address is locked. FALSE if not.
14880 
14881 Environment:
14882 
14883  DISPATCH LEVEL or below. No memory management locks may be held.
14884 
14885 --*/
14886 {
14887  PMMPFN Pfn1;
14888  KIRQL OldIrql;
14889  PMMPTE PointerPte;
14890  PFN_NUMBER PageFrameIndex;
14891 
14892  if (IS_SYSTEM_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress) == FALSE) {
14893  return FALSE;
14894  }
14895 
14896  if (MI_IS_PHYSICAL_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress)) {
14897  return TRUE;
14898  }
14899 
14900  //
14901  // Hyperspace and page maps are not treated as locked down.
14902  //
14903 
14904  if (MI_IS_PROCESS_SPACE_ADDRESS (VirtualAddress) == TRUE) {
14905  return FALSE;
14906  }
14907 
14908  PointerPte = MiGetPteAddress (VirtualAddress);
14909 
14910  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14911 
14912  if (MiIsAddressValid (VirtualAddress, TRUE) == FALSE) {
14913  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14914  return FALSE;
14915  }
14916 
14917  PageFrameIndex = MI_GET_PAGE_FRAME_FROM_PTE (PointerPte);
14918 
14919  //
14920  // Note that the mapped page may not be in the PFN database. Treat
14921  // this as locked.
14922  //
14923 
14924  if (!MI_IS_PFN (PageFrameIndex)) {
14925  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14926  return TRUE;
14927  }
14928 
14929  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (PageFrameIndex);
14930 
14931  //
14932  // Check for the page being locked by reference.
14933  //
14934 
14935  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount > 1) {
14936  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14937  return TRUE;
14938  }
14939 
14940  if (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount > Pfn1->u2.ShareCount) {
14941  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14942  return TRUE;
14943  }
14944 
14945  //
14946  // Check whether the page is locked into the working set.
14947  //
14948 
14949  if (Pfn1->u1.Event == NULL) {
14950  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14951  return TRUE;
14952  }
14953 
14954  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
14955 
14956  return FALSE;
14957 }
14958 
14959 LOGICAL
14960 MmAreMdlPagesLocked (
14961  IN PMDL MemoryDescriptorList
14962  )
14963 
14964 /*++
14965 
14966 Routine Description:
14967 
14968  This routine determines whether the pages described by the argument
14969  MDL are currently locked.
14970 
14971  This routine should only be called for debugging purposes, as it is not
14972  guaranteed upon return to the caller that the pages are still locked.
14973 
14974 Arguments:
14975 
14976  MemoryDescriptorList - Supplies the memory descriptor list to check.
14977 
14978 Return Value:
14979 
14980  TRUE if ALL the pages described by the argument MDL are locked.
14981  FALSE if not.
14982 
14983 Environment:
14984 
14985  DISPATCH LEVEL or below. No memory management locks may be held.
14986 
14987 --*/
14988 {
14989  PFN_NUMBER NumberOfPages;
14990  PPFN_NUMBER Page;
14991  PVOID VirtualAddress;
14992  PMMPFN Pfn1;
14993  KIRQL OldIrql;
14994 
14995  //
14996  // We'd like to assert that MDL_PAGES_LOCKED is set but can't because
14997  // some drivers have privately constructed MDLs and they never set the
14998  // bit properly.
14999  //
15000 
15001  if ((MemoryDescriptorList->MdlFlags & (MDL_IO_SPACE | MDL_SOURCE_IS_NONPAGED_POOL)) != 0) {
15002  return TRUE;
15003  }
15004 
15005  VirtualAddress = (PVOID)((PCHAR)MemoryDescriptorList->StartVa +
15006  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteOffset);
15007 
15008  NumberOfPages = ADDRESS_AND_SIZE_TO_SPAN_PAGES (VirtualAddress,
15009  MemoryDescriptorList->ByteCount);
15010 
15011  Page = (PPFN_NUMBER)(MemoryDescriptorList + 1);
15012 
15013  LOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
15014 
15015  do {
15016 
15017  if (*Page == MM_EMPTY_LIST) {
15018 
15019  //
15020  // There are no more locked pages.
15021  //
15022 
15023  break;
15024  }
15025 
15026  //
15027  // Note that the mapped page may not be in the PFN database. Treat
15028  // this as locked.
15029  //
15030 
15031  if (MI_IS_PFN (*Page)) {
15032 
15033  Pfn1 = MI_PFN_ELEMENT (*Page);
15034 
15035  //
15036  // Check for the page being locked by reference
15037  //
15038  // - or -
15039  //
15040  // whether the page is locked into the working set.
15041  //
15042 
15043  if ((Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount <= Pfn1->u2.ShareCount) &&
15044  (Pfn1->u3.e2.ReferenceCount <= 1) &&
15045  (Pfn1->u1.Event != NULL)) {
15046 
15047  //
15048  // The page is not locked by reference or in a working set,
15049  // see if it is in nonpaged pool.
15050  //
15051 
15052  if ((Pfn1->u3.e1.PageLocation == ActiveAndValid) &&
15053  (*Page >= MiStartOfInitialPoolFrame) &&
15054  (*Page <= MiEndOfInitialPoolFrame)) {
15055 
15056  //
15057  // This is initial nonpaged pool.
15058  //
15059 
15060  NOTHING;
15061  }
15062  else {
15063  VirtualAddress = MiGetVirtualAddressMappedByPte (Pfn1->PteAddress);
15064  if ((VirtualAddress >= MmNonPagedPoolExpansionStart) &&
15065  (VirtualAddress < MmNonPagedPoolEnd)) {
15066 
15067  //
15068  // This is expansion nonpaged pool.
15069  //
15070 
15071  NOTHING;
15072  }
15073  else if ((VirtualAddress >= MmSpecialPoolStart) &&
15074  (VirtualAddress < MmSpecialPoolEnd) &&
15075  (MmSpecialPoolStart != NULL) &&
15076  ((MmQuerySpecialPoolBlockType (VirtualAddress) &
15077  BASE_POOL_TYPE_MASK) == NonPagedPool)) {
15078  NOTHING;
15079  }
15080  else {
15081  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
15082  return FALSE;
15083  }
15084  }
15085  }
15086  }
15087 
15088  Page += 1;
15089  NumberOfPages -= 1;
15090  } while (NumberOfPages != 0);
15091 
15092  UNLOCK_PFN2 (OldIrql);
15093 
15094  return TRUE;
15095 }
